{\fs11}[HORN HONKING]{\r}

20
00:04:55,830 --> 00:04:58,380
弗雷迪 去叫辆马车来
{\fs11}[MRS. EYNSFORD-HILL] Freddy, go and find a cab.{\r}

21
00:04:58,580 --> 00:05:00,670
你想让我得肺炎吗？
{\fs11}Do you want me to catch pneumonia?{\r}

22
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:08,800
男：当心点儿 笨蛋
{\fs11}MAN: Watch out, daffy.{\r}

23
00:05:09,010 --> 00:05:11,220
他居然叫我是笨蛋
{\fs11}[IN COCKNEY ACCENT] He calls me a daffy.{\r}

24
00:05:12,310 --> 00:05:15,230
别光站在那儿 弗雷迪 去叫辆出租车来
{\fs11}Don't just stand there, Freddy. Go and find a cab.{\r}

25
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:17,690
好的 我这就去叫 我这就去叫车
{\fs11}AII right, I'II get it. I'II get it.{\r}

26
00:05:18,730 --> 00:05:20,730
男：我都被淋湿了
{\fs11}MAN: I'm getting wet.{\r}

27
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:24,530
[费雷迪的口哨声]
{\fs11}[FREDDY WHISTLES]{\r}

28
00:05:24,740 --> 00:05:26,400
男：抱歉
{\fs11}MAN: I'm so sorry.{\r}

29
00:05:31,370 --> 00:05:32,660
[咕噜声]
{\fs11}[GRUNTS]{\r}

30
00:05:33,450 --> 00:05:36,710
走路要看路 先生 走路要看路啊
{\fs11}Look where you're going, dear. Look where you're going.{\r}

31
00:05:36,910 --> 00:05:38,290
真是太抱歉了
{\fs11}I'm so sorry.{\r}

32
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,290
两束紫罗兰掉进泥水里了
{\fs11}Two bunches of violets trod in the mud.{\r}

33
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:42,290
这可是一天的收入
{\fs11}A full day's wages.{\r}

34
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:43,630
弗雷迪
{\fs11}EYNSFORD-HILL: Freddy.{\r}

35
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:45,670
弗雷迪 还不快去叫辆出租车
{\fs11}Freddy, go and find a cab.{\r}

36
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:47,510
好的 妈妈
{\fs11}Yes, Mother.{\r}

37
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:51,760
噢 他是你儿子 对吧？
{\fs11}Oh, he's your son, is he?{\r}

38
00:05:51,970 --> 00:05:54,220
噢 您要是愿意像一位母亲应该做的那样替他赔我
{\fs11}Well, if you'd done your duty by him as a mother should,{\r}

39
00:05:54,430 --> 00:05:56,350
你可不能任他就这样糟蹋了一个可怜女孩儿的花儿
{\fs11}you wouldn't let him spoil a poor girl's flowers{\r}

40
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,850
却什么都不赔就这么跑了啊
{\fs11}and then run away without paying.{\r}

41
00:05:58,060 --> 00:05:59,980
噢 接着做自己的生意去吧 姑娘
{\fs11}Oh, go about your business, my girl.{\r}

42
00:06:00,190 --> 00:06:03,110
要是你不赔钱那就别想离开这儿
{\fs11}And you wouldn't go off without paying either.{\r}

43
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:07,030
有两束紫罗兰掉进泥水里了
{\fs11}Two bunches of violets trod in the mud.{\r}

44
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,910
我的天
{\fs11}Good heavens.{\r}

45
00:06:10,110 --> 00:06:12,410
- 先生 您看这雨像是要停了吗？ - 我恐怕还要下
{\fs11}- Sir, is there any sign of it stopping? - I'm afraid not.{\r}

46
00:06:12,620 --> 00:06:14,160
- 现在越下越大了 - 噢 天哪
{\fs11}- It's worse than before. - Oh, dear.{\r}

47
00:06:14,370 --> 00:06:16,830
如果越下越大的话 那就表示雨快停了
{\fs11}lf it's worse, it's a sign it's nearly over.{\r}

48
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:19,660
高兴点吧 上校 买一束可怜女孩儿的花吧
{\fs11}Cheer up, captain. Buy a flower off a poor girl.{\r}

49
00:06:19,870 --> 00:06:21,170
抱歉 我没零钱
{\fs11}I'm sorry, I haven't any change.{\r}

50
00:06:21,380 --> 00:06:23,840
噢 半克朗我还是能找开的 给 这只要2便士 <font color=#FF7F00>[克朗 英国旧币单位 =0.25镑=5先令=60便士 ]</font>
{\fs11}Oh, I can change half a crown. Here, take this for tuppence.{\r}

51
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:25,670
我已经说了 非常抱歉 我没有...
{\fs11}I told you, I'm awfully sorry, I haven't--{\r}

52
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:27,300
噢 等等 噢 找到了
{\fs11}Oh, wait a minute. Oh, yes.{\r}

53
00:06:27,510 --> 00:06:29,670
这儿有三个1便士的硬币 给你吧
{\fs11}Here's three ha'pence, if that's any use to you.{\r}

54
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,800
谢谢您 先生
{\fs11}Thank you, sir.{\r}

55
00:06:39,230 --> 00:06:41,520
听着 你得当心点儿 收了钱最好给他一朵花
{\fs11}Here, you be careful. Better give him a flower for it.{\r}

56
00:06:41,730 --> 00:06:43,440
在那柱子后边有个家伙
{\fs11}There is a bloke here behind that pillar{\r}

57
00:06:43,650 --> 00:06:46,900
把你说的每句话都记下了
{\fs11}taking down every blessed word you're saying.{\r}

58
00:06:50,030 --> 00:06:52,530
我同一位绅士说话又不算做了什么错事
{\fs11}I ain't done nothing wrong by speaking to the gentleman.{\r}

59
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:55,410
我有权在街边卖花
{\fs11}I've a right to sell flowers if I keep off the curb.{\r}

60
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:57,700
我可是个品行端正的女孩儿 请大家帮帮我
{\fs11}I'm a respectable girl, so help me.{\r}

61
00:06:57,910 --> 00:07:00,960
我除了求他从我这里买一朵花儿之外再没说别的
{\fs11}I never spoke to him except to ask him to buy a flower off me.{\r}

62
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:02,830
男1：- 别再说了 - 怎么这么吵？
{\fs11}MAN 1 : Don't start. - What's all the noise?{\r}

63
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:04,290
好像有个侦探要抓他
{\fs11}There's a tec taking her down.{\r}

64
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:05,840
我靠双手正直的生活着
{\fs11}I'm making an honest living.{\r}

65
00:07:06,050 --> 00:07:07,250
男2：是谁在那儿大喊大叫的？
{\fs11}MAN 2: Who's doing all that shouting?{\r}

66
00:07:07,460 --> 00:07:09,510
- 这是怎么回事？ - 嗯...
{\fs11}- Where is it coming from? ELIZA: Well...{\r}

67
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:12,930
噢 先生 别让他控告我 他们不知道那对我意味着什么
{\fs11}Oh, sir, don't let him charge me. They don't know what it means to me.{\r}

68
00:07:13,140 --> 00:07:15,600
他们会毁掉我的名誉让我流落街头…
{\fs11}They'II take away me character and drive me on the streets{\r}

69
00:07:15,810 --> 00:07:17,220
只因为我同一位绅士说了话
{\fs11}for speaking to gentlemen.{\r}

70
00:07:17,430 --> 00:07:19,100
慢着 慢着 慢着
{\fs11}There, there, there.{\r}

71
00:07:19,310 --> 00:07:21,690
谁要伤害你 你这个傻女孩儿？你把我当成什么人了？
{\fs11}Who's hurting you, you silly girl? What you take me for?{\r}

72
00:07:21,890 --> 00:07:23,690
我向圣经起誓 我一个字儿也没说过
{\fs11}On my Bible oath, I never spoke a word.{\r}

73
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:25,400
闭嘴 别说了 我看上去像是警察吗？
{\fs11}Shut up. Do I look like a policeman?{\r}

74
00:07:25,610 --> 00:07:27,230
那你干嘛记下我说的话？
{\fs11}Then what did you take down me words for?{\r}

75
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:28,900
我怎么知道你有没有乱写呢？
{\fs11}How do I know you took me down right?{\r}

76
00:07:29,110 --> 00:07:32,030
让我看看你都是怎么记的
{\fs11}You just show me what you wrote about me.{\r}

77
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:35,780
伊莉莎：噢
{\fs11}ELIZA: Oh.{\r}

78
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:40,790
这是什么？这根本就是不正常的字
{\fs11}What's that? That ain't proper writing.{\r}

79
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,540
- 我看不懂 - 我可以
{\fs11}- I can't read it. - I can.{\r}

80
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:47,960
“我说 上校 请买一束可怜女孩儿的花吧”
{\fs11}"I say, captain, now buy a flower off a poor girl."{\r}

81
00:07:50,050 --> 00:07:53,130
噢 就因为我叫了他“上校”
{\fs11}Oh, it's because I called him "captain."{\r}

82
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:54,380
哦 我没有冒犯的意思
{\fs11}Oh, I meant no harm.{\r}

83
00:07:54,590 --> 00:07:57,220
先生 求您不要让他就因为那样一个词就控告我
{\fs11}Sir, don't let him lay a charge against me for a word like that.{\r}

84
00:07:57,430 --> 00:07:58,890
我不会指控的
{\fs11}I'II make no charge.{\r}

85
00:07:59,100 --> 00:08:01,890
真的吗 先生 如果你是位侦探 你没必要保护我
{\fs11}Really, sir, if you are a detective, you needn't begin protecting me{\r}

86
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:04,850
免受一位年轻女士的骚扰 除非我要求你那样做
{\fs11}against molestation from young women until I ask you.{\r}

87
00:08:05,060 --> 00:08:07,610
谁都知道这个女孩没有恶意
{\fs11}Anyone could tell the girl meant no harm.{\r}

88
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:09,400
他可不是什么侦探 他是位绅士
{\fs11}He ain't no tec. He's a gentleman.{\r}

89
00:08:09,610 --> 00:08:10,650
看他穿的靴子
{\fs11}Look at his boots.{\r}

90
00:08:10,860 --> 00:08:12,690
你们都是从塞尔西来的吧？
{\fs11}How are all your people down at Selsey?{\r}

91
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:15,240
谁跟你说我们是从塞尔西来的？
{\fs11}Who told you my people come from Selsey?{\r}

92
00:08:15,450 --> 00:08:17,450
别介意 但他们确实 <i>告诉<i> 我了
{\fs11}Never mind. They do.{\r}

93
00:08:17,660 --> 00:08:19,240
你怎么会到东面这么远的地方来？
{\fs11}How do you come to be up so far east?{\r}

94
00:08:19,450 --> 00:08:22,330
你出生在里森 格鲁夫吧
{\fs11}You were born in Lisson Grove.{\r}

95
00:08:22,540 --> 00:08:26,040
噢 我离开里森 格鲁夫又怎么不对了？
{\fs11}Oh, what harm is there my leaving Lisson Grove?{\r}

96
00:08:26,250 --> 00:08:29,170
那儿甚至连猪都住不下去 而且每周我都得花4到6镑？？
{\fs11}lt weren't fit for a pig to live in and I had to pay 4 and 6 a week--{\r}

97
00:08:29,380 --> 00:08:31,000
随便你住哪儿 可不要再大吵大嚷了
{\fs11}Live where you like, but stop that noise.{\r}

98
00:08:31,210 --> 00:08:34,590
行了 行了 他不会抓你了 你有权住在自己想待的地方
{\fs11}Come, come, he can't touch you. You've a right to live where you please.{\r}

99
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:36,970
- 我是个品行端正的女孩儿 我是认真的 - 是的 没错 没错
{\fs11}- I'm a good girl, I am. - Yes, yes, yes.{\r}

100
00:08:37,180 --> 00:08:38,680
说下我是从哪儿来的？
{\fs11}Where do I come from?{\r}

101
00:08:38,890 --> 00:08:39,930
豪斯敦 <font color=#FF7F00>[英国城市]</font>
{\fs11}Hoxton.{\r}

102
00:08:40,140 --> 00:08:42,600
噢 谁说不是呢？ 啊 你什么都知道啊 说得一点没错
{\fs11}Well, who said I didn't? Blimey, you know everything, you do.{\r}

103
00:08:42,810 --> 00:08:45,890
这位先生 你能替我叫一辆出租车吗？
{\fs11}You, sir, do you think you could find me a taxi?{\r}

104
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:48,560
不知道你有没有注意到 雨已经停了
{\fs11}I don't know whether you've noticed, but it's stopped raining.{\r}

105
00:08:48,770 --> 00:08:50,860
你可以搭乘一辆去汉普顿法院的公共汽车
{\fs11}You can get a motor bus to Hampton Court.{\r}

106
00:08:51,070 --> 00:08:52,610
对了 那正是你住的地方吧 说得没错吧？
{\fs11}Well, that's where you live, isn't it?{\r}

107
00:08:52,820 --> 00:08:54,490
真是无礼
{\fs11}What impertinence.{\r}

108
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:58,160
嘿 说说他又是从哪儿来的吧 你好像能预言的样子
{\fs11}Hey, tell him where he comes from, you wanna go fortune-telling.{\r}

109
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:01,700
切尔滕纳姆 <font color=#FF7F00>[英格兰西南部城市]</font>
{\fs11}Cheltenham,{\r}

110
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:03,870
哈罗 <font color=#FF7F00>[伦敦市郊地名]</font>
{\fs11}Harrow,{\r}

111
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:08,830
剑桥还有 呃 印度？
{\fs11}Cambridge and, uh, lndia?{\r}

112
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,450
极为正确
{\fs11}Quite right.{\r}

113
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:12,840
啊 他不是侦探 他就是个爱管闲事的
{\fs11}Blimey, he ain't a tec, he's a blooming busybody.{\r}

114
00:09:13,050 --> 00:09:16,170
容我问一句 先生 你是靠在音乐厅里表演这个为生的吗？
{\fs11}lf I may ask, sir, do you do this sort of thing for a living at a music hall?{\r}

115
00:09:16,380 --> 00:09:18,430
嗯 我也曾考虑过 说不定有一天我会的
{\fs11}Well, I have thought of it. Perhaps I will one day.{\r}

116
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:21,300
他才不是什么绅士 否则怎么会欺负一个可怜的女孩儿
{\fs11}He's no gentleman. He ain't, to interfere with a poor girl.{\r}

117
00:09:21,510 --> 00:09:23,180
我能问一下 你是怎么做到的吗？
{\fs11}How do you do it, may I ask?{\r}

118
00:09:23,390 --> 00:09:26,180
简单来说就是语音学 研究语音的科学
{\fs11}Simple phonetics. The science of speech.{\r}

119
00:09:26,390 --> 00:09:28,900
那是我的专业 也是我的爱好
{\fs11}That's my profession. Also my hobby.{\r}

120
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:31,860
任何人都能通过口音辨认出一个人是爱尔兰人还是约克郡人
{\fs11}Anyone can spot an lrishman or a Yorkshireman by his brogue,{\r}

121
00:09:32,070 --> 00:09:34,150
但是我可以将一个人的生活地点缩小到6英里的范围内
{\fs11}but I can place a man within six miles.{\r}

122
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:36,400
而在伦敦我可以缩小到2英里
{\fs11}I can place him within two miles in London.{\r}

123
00:09:36,610 --> 00:09:38,280
有时甚至可以缩小到两条街
{\fs11}Sometimes within two streets.{\r}

124
00:09:38,490 --> 00:09:40,910
真该为自己感到羞耻 懦夫
{\fs11}Ought to be ashamed of himself, unmanly coward.{\r}

125
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:42,160
靠这个也可以谋生吗？
{\fs11}ls there a living in that?{\r}

126
00:09:42,370 --> 00:09:43,410
噢 是的 可以说过得还相当不错
{\fs11}Oh, yes, quite a fat one.{\r}

127
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:45,910
让他忙他自己的吧 别再缠着我这个可怜的女孩儿了
{\fs11}Let him mind his own business and leave a poor girl--{\r}

128
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:49,420
你这女人！马上停止发出这可憎的哭声
{\fs11}Woman! Cease this detestable boohooing instantly{\r}

129
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:52,420
要不就另外找个同情你的地方待着去
{\fs11}or else seek the shelter of some other place of worship.{\r}

130
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:56,300
只要我愿意 我有权待在这儿 跟你一样
{\fs11}I have a right to be here if I like, same as you.{\r}

131
00:09:56,510 --> 00:09:59,090
发出这样叫人厌恶与不舒服噪音的女人
{\fs11}Woman who utters such disgusting and depressing noises{\r}

132
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,680
没有权利出现在任何地方 连活着的权利都没有
{\fs11}has no right to be anywhere. No right to live.{\r}

133
00:10:01,890 --> 00:10:03,680
别忘了你是个有灵魂的人
{\fs11}Remember that you're a human being with a soul{\r}

134
00:10:03,890 --> 00:10:06,430
上天让你能够开口说话
{\fs11}and the divine gift of articulate speech.{\r}

135
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:07,810
你的母语
{\fs11}That your native language{\r}

136
00:10:08,020 --> 00:10:10,600
莎士比亚 米尔顿 还有圣经都是用的这种语言
