00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:45,570
我能有幸和您面对面的说上一句话吗？
{\fs11}Might I have the pleasure of a word with you face-to-face?{\r}

403
00:27:45,780 --> 00:27:48,080
噢 不 不 不 这个女孩儿我昨天晚上就记录过了
{\fs11}Oh, no, no, no. This is the girl I jotted down last night.{\r}

404
00:27:48,290 --> 00:27:51,250
她对我已经没用了 我已经得到了想要的关于里森 格鲁夫一带方言的所有记录
{\fs11}She's no use. I've got all the records I want of the Lisson Grove lingo.{\r}

405
00:27:51,460 --> 00:27:53,250
我可不想在她身上再浪费一个录音筒了
{\fs11}I'm not gonna waste another cylinder on that.{\r}

406
00:27:53,460 --> 00:27:55,000
现在 你请出去吧 我不想见到你
{\fs11}Now, be off with you. I don't want you.{\r}

407
00:27:55,210 --> 00:27:58,130
别那么无礼 你都还不知道我为什么来呢
{\fs11}Don't be so saucy. You ain't heard what I come for yet.{\r}

408
00:27:58,340 --> 00:27:59,880
你没告诉他我是乘出租车来的吗？
{\fs11}Did you tell him I come in a taxi?{\r}

409
00:28:00,090 --> 00:28:01,130
别说这些了 女孩儿
{\fs11}Nonsense, girl.{\r}

410
00:28:01,340 --> 00:28:04,220
你认为像希金斯先生这样的绅士会在意你是怎么来的吗？
{\fs11}What do you think a gentleman like Mr. Higgins cares what you came in?{\r}

411
00:28:04,430 --> 00:28:06,180
噢 我们都是有自尊心的
{\fs11}Oh, we are proud.{\r}

412
00:28:06,390 --> 00:28:08,180
噢 他不打算给教我了 他反悔了
{\fs11}Well, he ain't above giving lessons. Not him.{\r}

413
00:28:08,390 --> 00:28:09,470
他之前说要教我的
{\fs11}I heard him say so.{\r}

414
00:28:09,680 --> 00:28:11,730
好吧 我可不是来这儿 听你们说这些客气话的
{\fs11}Well, I ain't come here to ask for any compliment,{\r}

415
00:28:11,940 --> 00:28:14,480
要不是因为我的钱不够的话 我也不会来这儿
{\fs11}and if my money's not good enough, I can go elsewhere.{\r}

416
00:28:14,690 --> 00:28:16,020
不够什么？
{\fs11}Good enough for what?{\r}

417
00:28:16,230 --> 00:28:18,900
付你的还是够了
{\fs11}Good enough for you.{\r}

418
00:28:19,320 --> 00:28:21,820
现在 你明白了吗？我是来学习的 听清楚了
{\fs11}Now you know, don't you? I'm come to have lessons, I am.{\r}

419
00:28:22,030 --> 00:28:23,990
我还会付学费 别搞错了
{\fs11}And to pay for them too. Make no mistake.{\r}

420
00:28:24,570 --> 00:28:26,280
噢...
{\fs11}Well...{\r}

421
00:28:26,490 --> 00:28:29,160
你希望我怎么回答你？
{\fs11}And what do you expect me to say?{\r}

422
00:28:29,700 --> 00:28:33,160
好吧 如果你还算是位绅士的话 我想 你该先请我坐下
{\fs11}Well, if you was a gentleman, you might ask me to sit down, I think.{\r}

423
00:28:33,370 --> 00:28:36,380
我不是说过了吗 我是来照顾你生意的？
{\fs11}Don't I tell you I'm bringing you business?{\r}

424
00:28:36,580 --> 00:28:38,840
皮克林 我们是该请这个货物进来坐下
{\fs11}Pickering, should we ask this baggage to sit down{\r}

425
00:28:39,050 --> 00:28:41,170
还是把她从窗户扔出去呢？
{\fs11}or shall we just throw her out of the window?{\r}

426
00:28:41,380 --> 00:28:42,760
啊噢！我可不叫什么货物
{\fs11}Ow! I won't be called a baggage.{\r}

427
00:28:42,970 --> 00:28:45,680
何况我还像任何一位女士那样要付给你学费
{\fs11}Not when I've offered to pay like any lady.{\r}

428
00:28:46,680 --> 00:28:48,260
你为什么要这样做呢 小姑娘？
{\fs11}PICKERING: What do you want, my girl?{\r}

429
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:54,640
我...我希望自己能像一位女士一样在花店里工作
{\fs11}I-- I want to be a lady in a flower shop{\r}

430
00:28:54,850 --> 00:28:57,190
而不是在托特纳姆考特路的街角卖花
{\fs11}instead of selling at the corner of Tottenham Court Road.{\r}

431
00:28:57,400 --> 00:29:00,020
但除非我说话能更有教养些 否则他们是不会要我的
{\fs11}But they won't take me unless I can talk more genteel.{\r}

432
00:29:00,230 --> 00:29:02,690
他说过他会教我 所以 我就来了
{\fs11}He said he could teach me. Well, here I am.{\r}

433
00:29:02,900 --> 00:29:04,950
我准备付钱给他 也不要他白教我
{\fs11}Ready to pay him, not asking any favor.{\r}

434
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:07,530
可他却当我是垃圾一样的对待我
{\fs11}And he treats me as if I was dirt.{\r}

435
00:29:07,740 --> 00:29:11,950
我知道你上课收多少钱 我愿意掏钱
{\fs11}I know what lessons cost as well as you do, and I'm ready to pay.{\r}

436
00:29:14,620 --> 00:29:16,170
付多少钱？
{\fs11}How much?{\r}

437
00:29:16,370 --> 00:29:18,460
现在你说话了
{\fs11}Now you're talking.{\r}

438
00:29:18,670 --> 00:29:21,300
趁还可以反悔 我想你还是别吹牛了
{\fs11}I thought you'd come off it when you saw a chance of getting back{\r}

439
00:29:21,500 --> 00:29:22,840
昨天晚上你那样作践我
{\fs11}a bit of what you chucked at me.{\r}

440
00:29:23,050 --> 00:29:25,920
- 你现在有一位客人 不是吗 嗯？ - 坐下吧
{\fs11}- You'd had a drop in, hadn't you, eh? - Sit down.{\r}

441
00:29:26,130 --> 00:29:27,890
如果你打算为此道歉的话...
{\fs11}lf you're going to make a compliment of it--{\r}

442
00:29:28,090 --> 00:29:30,180
坐下！
{\fs11}Sit down!{\r}

443
00:29:30,390 --> 00:29:32,970
坐下 丫头 照我说的做
{\fs11}Sit down, girl. Do as you're told.{\r}

444
00:29:33,180 --> 00:29:34,430
你叫什么名字？
{\fs11}What's your name?{\r}

445
00:29:34,640 --> 00:29:37,060
伊莉莎 杜利特
{\fs11}Eliza Doolittle.{\r}

446
00:29:37,270 --> 00:29:39,770
你能坐下吗 杜利特小姐？
{\fs11}Won't you sit down, Miss Doolittle?{\r}

447
00:29:41,900 --> 00:29:43,320
噢
{\fs11}Oh.{\r}

448
00:29:43,570 --> 00:29:45,860
我当然会不介意
{\fs11}I don't mind if I do.{\r}

449
00:29:47,070 --> 00:29:51,780
说说吧 你打算为接受这些课程付我多少钱？
{\fs11}Now, how much do you propose to pay me for these lessons?{\r}

450
00:29:51,990 --> 00:29:53,410
嗯 我是知道行情的
{\fs11}Oh, I know what's right.{\r}

451
00:29:53,620 --> 00:29:56,370
我的一位女士的朋友上法语课的花费是一小时18便士
{\fs11}A lady friend of mine gets French lessons for 1 8 pence an hour{\r}

452
00:29:56,580 --> 00:29:58,620
是由一位真正的法国绅士教的
{\fs11}from a real French gentleman.{\r}

453
00:29:58,830 --> 00:30:00,880
噢 就凭你总不好意思也要收一样的价钱吧
{\fs11}Well, you wouldn't have the face to ask me the same{\r}

454
00:30:01,090 --> 00:30:03,630
只不过教我自己的母语 就收我学法语的价钱
{\fs11}for teaching me my own language as you would for French.{\r}

455
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:05,340
所以我最多出1个先令
{\fs11}So I won't give more than a shilling.{\r}

456
00:30:05,550 --> 00:30:07,510
随便你要不要
{\fs11}Take it or leave it.{\r}

457
00:30:09,430 --> 00:30:14,060
你知道吗 皮克林 如果你不把1先令仅仅当做1先令来看
{\fs11}Do you know, Pickering, if you think of a shilling not as a simple shilling{\r}

458
00:30:14,270 --> 00:30:17,020
而是从这个女孩儿的收入百分比来看
{\fs11}but as a percentage of this girl's income,{\r}

459
00:30:17,230 --> 00:30:21,060
这几乎相当于
{\fs11}it works out as fully equivalent{\r}

460
00:30:21,690 --> 00:30:24,690
一位百万富翁拿出了60到70镑
{\fs11}of 60 or 70 pounds from a millionaire.{\r}

461
00:30:24,900 --> 00:30:28,200
以圣乔治名起誓 这太多了 这是我收的最多的一次
{\fs11}By George, it's enormous. lt's the biggest offer I ever had.{\r}

462
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:30,570
60镑？
{\fs11}Sixty pounds?{\r}

463
00:30:30,780 --> 00:30:33,030
你们在说什么？我上哪儿能弄来60镑？
{\fs11}What are you talking about? Where would I get 60 pounds?{\r}

464
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:34,450
我根本没说过要付你60镑
{\fs11}I never offered you 60 pounds.{\r}

465
00:30:34,660 --> 00:30:36,830
- 把嘴闭上 - 可我根本没有60镑
{\fs11}- Hold your tongue. - But I ain't got 60 pounds.{\r}

466
00:30:37,040 --> 00:30:38,410
别哭了 傻丫头
{\fs11}Don't cry, you silly girl.{\r}

467
00:30:38,620 --> 00:30:40,960
坐下吧 没人想碰你的钱
{\fs11}Sit down. Nobody's going to touch your money.{\r}

468
00:30:41,170 --> 00:30:43,040
要是你还是继续痛哭流涕个没完
{\fs11}Somebody's going to touch you with a broomstick{\r}

469
00:30:43,250 --> 00:30:45,590
有人就要用笤帚打你了 坐下！
{\fs11}if you don't stop sniveling. Sit down!{\r}

470
00:30:45,800 --> 00:30:47,510
[停止了哭泣]
{\fs11}[STOPS CRYING]{\r}

471
00:30:49,340 --> 00:30:51,970
噢 不知道的还以为你是我父亲
{\fs11}Oh, anybody would think you was my father.{\r}

472
00:30:52,180 --> 00:30:54,850
要是我真要教你 我会比两个爸爸还要厉害
{\fs11}lf I decide to teach you, I'II be worse than two fathers to you.{\r}

473
00:30:55,060 --> 00:30:56,060
[伊莉莎的鼻子吸气声]
{\fs11}[ELIZA SNIFFLES]{\r}

474
00:30:56,270 --> 00:30:57,560
给你
{\fs11}Here.{\r}

475
00:30:57,770 --> 00:31:00,060
- 给我这个干嘛？ - 擦擦眼泪吧
{\fs11}- What's this for? - To wipe your eyes.{\r}

476
00:31:00,270 --> 00:31:03,060
把脸上弄湿了的地方都擦擦吧
{\fs11}To wipe any part of your face that feels moist.{\r}

477
00:31:03,270 --> 00:31:05,730
记住 这就是你的手绢而这就是你的袖子
{\fs11}And remember, that's your handkerchief and that's your sleeve.{\r}

478
00:31:05,940 --> 00:31:07,530
别把它们搞混了
{\fs11}And don't confuse the one with the other{\r}

479
00:31:07,740 --> 00:31:09,320
要是你想成为一名女店员的话
{\fs11}if you want to become a lady in a shop.{\r}

480
00:31:09,530 --> 00:31:11,610
您跟她那样讲没用 希金斯先生
{\fs11}lt's no use to talk to her like that, Mr. Higgins.{\r}

481
00:31:11,820 --> 00:31:13,160
她根本不明白你在说什么
{\fs11}She doesn't understand you.{\r}

482
00:31:13,370 --> 00:31:17,080
- 噢 把手绢给我 - 这手绢是他给我的 不是你
{\fs11}Here, give the handkerchief to me. He give it to me, not to you.{\r}

483
00:31:17,290 --> 00:31:19,160
希金斯 我很好奇
{\fs11}Higgins, I'm interested.{\r}

484
00:31:19,370 --> 00:31:21,870
你夸口说你能让她变得像公爵夫人一般
{\fs11}What about your boast that you could pass her off as a duchess{\r}

485
00:31:22,080 --> 00:31:23,420
出席大使招待舞会 嗯？
{\fs11}at the Embassy Ball, eh?{\r}

486
00:31:23,630 --> 00:31:26,420
如果你真能办到 我得说你就是这个世界上最伟大的老师
{\fs11}I'II say you're the greatest teacher alive if you can make that good.{\r}

487
00:31:26,630 --> 00:31:30,380
我打赌你办不到 否则这个试验的所有的费用由我承担
{\fs11}I'II bet you all the expenses of the experiment that you can't do it.{\r}

488
00:31:30,590 --> 00:31:32,510
甚至连她的学费我也一并支付
{\fs11}I'II even pay for the lessons.{\r}

489
00:31:32,720 --> 00:31:35,470
噢 您真好 谢谢您 上校
{\fs11}Oh, you're real good. Thank you, captain.{\r}

490
00:31:36,850 --> 00:31:40,020
要知道 这赌注很难拒绝
{\fs11}You know, it's almost irresistible.{\r}

491
00:31:41,520 --> 00:31:43,690
她的品味如此低俗
{\fs11}She's so deliciously low.{\r}

492
00:31:43,900 --> 00:31:45,360
如此肮脏可怖
{\fs11}So horribly dirty.{\r}

493
00:31:45,570 --> 00:31:46,610
我才不脏
{\fs11}I ain't dirty.{\r}

494
00:31:46,820 --> 00:31:48,940
我来之前洗过脸还有手 真的
{\fs11}I washed my face and hands before I come, I did.{\r}

495
00:31:49,150 --> 00:31:50,190
我愿意同您打这个赌
{\fs11}I'II take it.{\r}

496
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:53,360
我会将她从贫民区的邋遢女孩儿变为一位公爵夫人
{\fs11}I'II make a duchess of this draggle-tailed guttersnipe.{\r}

497
00:31:53,570 --> 00:31:57,200
今天就开始 现在 此时此刻起 皮尔斯太太 带她出去把她弄干净
{\fs11}We'II start today. Now. This moment. Take her away and clean her.{\r}

498
00:31:57,410 --> 00:31:59,200
要是洗不掉的就用砂纸
{\fs11}Sandpaper if it won't come off any other way.{\r}

499
00:31:59,410 --> 00:32:01,460
- 现在厨房里还有火吗？ - 是的 不过...
{\fs11}- Is there a good fire in the kitchen? - Yes, but--{\r}

500
00:32:01,660 --> 00:32:04,040
把她所有的衣服都拿去 烧了 给她订做新的
{\fs11}Take all her clothes, burn them, and order new ones.{\r}

501
00:32:04,250 --> 00:32:06,340
在新衣服送来之前先用牛皮纸把她裹起来
{\fs11}Just wrap her in brown paper till they come.{\r}

502
00:32:06,960 --> 00:32:10,380
你这样太不绅士了 你怎么能这样说话
{\fs11}You're no gentleman. You're not to talk of such things.{\r}

503
00:32:10,590 --> 00:32:12,010
我可是个品行端正的女孩儿 我是认真的
{\fs11}I'm a good girl, I am.{\r}

504
00:32:12,220 --> 00:32:15,430
我也知道你是什么样的人 真的
{\fs11}And I know what the likes of you are, I do.{\r}

505
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:18,890
你这种贫民区出来的人用不着在我们面前装什么矜持 年轻的小姐
{\fs11}We want none of your slum prudery here, young woman.{\r}

506
00:32:19,100 --> 00:32:21,220
你只要学会让自己的举止像一位公爵夫人就可以了
{\fs11}You've got to learn to behave like a duchess.{\r}

507
00:32:21,430 --> 00:32:22,680
现在带她出去 皮尔斯太太
{\fs11}Now take her away, Mrs. Pearce.{\r}

508
00:32:22,890 --> 00:32:24,600
要是她跟你捣乱的话 你就好好教训她
{\fs11}lf she gives you any trouble, wallop her.{\r}

509
00:32:24,810 --> 00:32:26,690
我会叫警察的 我发誓
{\fs11}I'II call the police, I will.{\r}

510
00:32:26,900 --> 00:32:28,440
我没地方让她住
{\fs11}I've got no place to put her.{\r}

511
00:32:28,650 --> 00:32:31,280
- 这样吧 让她住在垃圾箱里 - 啊噢!
{\fs11}- Well, put her in the dustbin. - Ow!{\r}

512
00:32:31,490 --> 00:32:33,650
别这样 希金斯 你这样太不近情理了
{\fs11}Come, Higgins, be reasonable.{\r}

513
00:32:33,860 --> 00:32:36,030
你必须合乎情理一点儿 希金斯先生 我说真的
{\fs11}You must be reasonable, Mr. Higgins, really, you must.{\r}

514
00:32:36,240 --> 00:32:38,870
你不可以像这样作践别人
{\fs11}You can't walk over everybody like this.{\r}

515
00:32:41,540 --> 00:32:43,210
我吗？
{\fs11}I?{\r}

516
00:32:43,410 --> 00:32:45,080
我有作践别人？
{\fs11}Walk over everybody?{\r}

517
00:32:45,290 --> 00:32:47,540
我亲爱的皮尔斯太太 还有我亲爱的皮克林
{\fs11}My dear Mrs. Pearce, my dear Pickering.{\r}

518
00:32:47,750 --> 00:32:49,540
我从没想过要作践谁
{\fs11}I had no intention of walking over anybody.{\r}

519
00:32:49,750 --> 00:32:52,590
我只是觉得我们应该对这个可怜的姑娘更好一点
{\fs11}I merely suggested we should be kind to this poor girl.{\r}

520
00:32:52,800 --> 00:32:54,630
我表达得不太清楚
{\fs11}I didn't express myself clearly{\r}

521
00:32:54,840 --> 00:32:57,590
因为我不希望不符合她的品味
{\fs11}because I didn't wish to hurt her delicacy.{\r}

522
00:32:57,800 --> 00:32:58,850
或者是你们的
{\fs11}Or yours.{\r}

523
00:32:59,060 --> 00:33:02,140
可是 先生 您不能就这样把一个女孩儿带回来
{\fs11}But, sir, you can't take a girl up like that{\r}

524
00:33:02,350 --> 00:33:04,730
就好像你在海滩上捡了块石头一样
{\fs11}as if you were picking up a pebble on the beach.{\r}

525
00:33:04,940 --> 00:33:06,000
为什么不行？
{\fs11}Why not?{\r}

526
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:07,400
为什么不行？

527
00:33:07,610 --> 00:33:09,060
因为您一点都不了解她
{\fs11}But you don't know anything about her.{\r}

528
00:33:09,270 --> 00:33:11,980
她的父母呢？她说不定已经结婚了
{\fs11}What about her parents? She may be married.{\r}

529
00:33:12,190 --> 00:33:13,570
接着说
{\fs11}Garn.{\r}

530
00:33:13,780 --> 00:33:17,320
看呐 要是这个女孩儿能正确的说出“说下去”
{\fs11}There. As the girl very properly says, "Garn."{\r}

531
00:33:17,530 --> 00:33:19,120
有谁会和我结婚？
{\fs11}Who'd marry me?{\r}

532
00:33:21,700 --> 00:33:24,080
我以圣乔治之名起誓 伊莉莎
{\fs11}By George, Eliza.{\r}

533
00:33:24,290 --> 00:33:29,670
大街上会布满了因你而自杀的男人们的尸体
{\fs11}The streets will be strewn with the bodies of men{\r}

534
00:33:29,880 --> 00:33:31,920
在我将你重新打造之前
{\fs11}shooting themselves for your sake before I'm done with you.{\r}

535
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:35,340
听着 我要离开这儿
{\fs11}Here. I'm going.{\r}

536
00:33:35,550 --> 00:33:37,430
他在说胡话 绝对是这样
{\fs11}He's off his chump, he is.{\r}

537
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:40,140
- 我可不想让这样的蠢货教我 - 噢 疯子 我是吗？
{\fs11}- I don't want no barmies teaching me. - Oh, mad, am I?{\r}

538
00:33:40,350 --> 00:33:42,470
那好 皮尔斯太太 别打电话订什么新衣服了
{\fs11}AII right, don't ring up and order those clothes.{\r}

539
00:33:42,680 --> 00:33:44,890
- 把她扔出去 - 不 希金斯先生 我可不能这样做
{\fs11}- Throw her out. - Stop, Mr. Higgins, I won't allow it.{\r}

540
00:33:45,100 --> 00:33:46,230
回家去找你父母吧 丫头
{\fs11}Go home to your parents.{\r}

541
00:33:46,440 --> 00:33:48,060
我没有父母
{\fs11}I ain't got no parents.{\r}

542
00:33:48,270 --> 00:33:49,860
你听见了吧 她没有父母
{\fs11}There you are. She ain't got no parents.{\r}

543
00:33:50,060 --> 00:33:51,520
有什么好奇怪的？没人会想要她
{\fs11}What's all the fuss? Nobody wants her.{\r}

544
00:33:51,730 --> 00:33:53,690
她对任何人都是废物 除了我 带她上楼去
{\fs11}She's no use to anybody but me. Take her upstairs.{\r}

545
00:33:53,900 --> 00:33:56,150
您打算拿她怎么办？让她做什么活儿付给她钱吗？
{\fs11}But what's to become of her? ls she to be paid anything?{\r}

546
00:33:56,360 --> 00:33:58,320
噢 麻烦您理智一点儿 先生
{\fs11}Oh, do be sensible, sir.{\r}

547
00:33:58,530 --> 00:34:00,910
她要钱干什么？她有的吃穿就够了
{\fs11}What would she do with money? She'II have food and clothes.{\r}

548
00:34:01,120 --> 00:34:02,700
要是你给她钱 她就只会拿去喝酒
{\fs11}She'II only drink if you give her money.{\r}

549
00:34:02,910 --> 00:34:04,200
噢 你真是个畜生 这是在胡说
{\fs11}Oh, you are a brute. It's a lie.{\r}

550
00:34:04,410 --> 00:34:06,620
从来就没人见过我喝酒
{\fs11}Nobody ever saw the sign of liquor on me.{\r}

551
00:34:06,830 --> 00:34:09,790
噢 先生 您是位绅士 求您让他别这样说我
{\fs11}Oh, sir, you're a gentleman. Don't let him speak to me like that.{\r}

552
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:12,960
你有没有想过希金斯 这个女孩儿也是有感情的？
{\fs11}Does it occur to you, Higgins, the girl has some feelings?{\r}

553
00:34:13,170 --> 00:34:16,470
噢 不 我没想过 我们可不用担心她的感受
{\fs11}Oh, no, I don't think so. No feelings we need worry about.{\r}

554
00:34:16,670 --> 00:34:17,720
嗯 你有吗 伊莉莎？
{\fs11}Well, have you, Eliza?{\r}

555
00:34:17,930 --> 00:34:20,260
我同任何人一样有自己的感情
{\fs11}I got my feelings same as anyone else.{\r}

556
00:34:20,470 --> 00:34:23,640
希金斯先生 我想我必须得知道这个女孩儿在这儿要待多久
{\fs11}Mr. Higgins, I must know on what terms the girl is to be here.{\r}

557
00:34:23,850 --> 00:34:26,270
等你教完她 要拿她怎么办？
{\fs11}What's to become of her when you've finished your teaching?{\r}

558
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:28,060
您必须得看得更远一点儿 先生
{\fs11}You must look ahead a little, sir.{\r}

559
00:34:28,270 --> 00:34:30,400
要是我们把她送回贫民区会怎样 皮尔斯太太？
{\fs11}What's to become of her if we leave her in the gutter?{\r}

560
00:34:30,610 --> 00:34:33,860
- 请回答我 皮尔斯太太 - 那是她自己的事 用不着你管
{\fs11}- Answer me that, Mrs. Pearce. - That's her own business, not yours.{\r}

561
00:34:34,070 --> 00:34:37,150
等我把她教完 我们就把她扔回去 之后就是她自己的事了
{\fs11}When I'm done, we'II throw her back, then it will be her own business again.{\r}

562
00:34:37,360 --> 00:34:38,650
这样就没问题了吧 不是吗？
{\fs11}That will be all right, won't it?{\r}

563
00:34:38,860 --> 00:34:41,530
你根本就没有同情心
{\fs11}You've no feeling heart in you.{\r}

564
00:34:41,740 --> 00:34:44,240
你除了你自己什么都不关心
{\fs11}You don't care for nothing but yourself.{\r}

565
00:34:44,450 --> 00:34:46,910
我受够了 我现在就要走 我是认真的
{\fs11}I've had enough of this. I'm going, I am.{\r}

566
00:34:47,120 --> 00:34:49,000
你该为自己感到羞耻
{\fs11}You ought to be ashamed of yourself, you ought.{\r}

567
00:34:49,210 --> 00:34:51,460
吃点儿巧克力吧 伊莉莎
{\fs11}Have some chocolates, Eliza.{\r}

568
00:34:57,470 --> 00:34:59,050
我怎么知道这里边都放了什么？
{\fs11}How do I know what might be in them?{\r}

569
00:34:59,260 --> 00:35:02,590
我听说有女孩儿被像你这样的人下了药
{\fs11}I've heard of girls being drugged by the likes of you.{\r}

570
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:04,810
为表示我的善意
{\fs11}Pledge of good faith.{\r}

571
00:35:05,010 --> 00:35:07,220
我吃一半
{\fs11}I'II take one half{\r}

572
00:35:07,430 --> 00:35:09,480
你吃另外一半
{\fs11}and you take the other.{\r}

573
00:35:12,810 --> 00:35:15,860
你可以得到很多盒的巧克力 每天都你都会得到好几筒
{\fs11}You'II have boxes of them, barrels of them every day.{\r}

574
00:35:16,070 --> 00:35:18,400
你可以拿它们当饭吃 嗯？
{\fs11}You'II live on them, eh?{\r}

575
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:21,200
我并不想吃 只是出于淑女的礼貌
{\fs11}I wouldn't have ate it, only I'm too ladylike{\r}

576
00:35:21,410 --> 00:35:22,660
所以才没把它吐出来
{\fs11}to take it out of my mouth.{\r}

577
00:35:22,870 --> 00:35:23,910
想想吧 伊莉莎
{\fs11}Think of it, Eliza.{\r}

578
00:35:24,120 --> 00:35:29,160
想想巧克力 出租车还有黄金和钻石
{\fs11}Think of chocolates and taxis and gold and diamonds.{\r}

579
00:35:29,370 --> 00:35:32,620
啊噢！我可不想要什么黄金还有钻石
{\fs11}Ow! I don't want no gold and no diamonds.{\r}

580
00:35:32,830 --> 00:35:34,540
我可是个品行端正的女孩儿 我是认真的
{\fs11}I'm a good girl, I am.{\r}

581
00:35:34,750 --> 00:35:38,000
希金斯 看来我必须介入 皮尔斯太太是对的
{\fs11}Higgins, I really must interfere. Mrs. Pearce is quite right.{\r}

582
00:35:38,210 --> 00:35:40,840
要是让这个女孩儿在你手里待上6个月
{\fs11}lf this girl's gonna put herself in your hands for six months{\r}

583
00:35:41,050 --> 00:35:42,430
进行所谓的教学试验
{\fs11}for an experiment in teaching,{\r}

584
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:46,010
她必须清楚的知道自己是在做什么
{\fs11}she must understand thoroughly what she's doing.{\r}

585
00:35:46,260 --> 00:35:48,220
希金斯：嗯
{\fs11}HIGGINS: Mm.{\r}

586
00:35:48,430 --> 00:35:51,770
伊莉莎 今后的6个月你将待在这儿
{\fs11}Eliza, you are to stay here for the next six months{\r}

587
00:35:51,980 --> 00:35:56,980
学习如何像一位花店店员一样拥有美丽的谈吐
{\fs11}learning how to speak beautifully, like a lady in a florist shop.{\r}

588
00:35:57,190 --> 00:35:59,110
如果你有好好做的话
{\fs11}lf you're good and do whatever you're told,{\r}

589
00:35:59,320 --> 00:36:02,320
你就能睡在卧室里 还能得到很多好吃的
{\fs11}you shall sleep in a proper bedroom, have lots to eat{\r}

590
00:36:02,530 --> 00:36:06,200
还会给你钱去买巧克力 让你出入都乘坐出租车
{\fs11}and money to buy chocolates and take rides in taxis.{\r}

591
00:36:06,410 --> 00:36:08,620
但要是你不听话偷懒的话
{\fs11}But if you are naughty and idle,{\r}

592
00:36:08,830 --> 00:36:11,580
你就得跟厨房里的黑蟑螂们睡在一起
{\fs11}you shall sleep in the back kitchen amongst the black beetles{\r}

593
00:36:11,790 --> 00:36:15,210
还要被皮尔斯太太用笤帚打
{\fs11}and be walloped by Mrs. Pearce with a broomstick.{\r}

594
00:36:16,170 --> 00:36:17,670
6个月之后
{\fs11}At the end of six months,{\r}

595
00:36:17,880 --> 00:36:20,170
你将被带到白金汉宫
{\fs11}you shall be taken to Buckingham Palace{\r}

596
00:36:20,380 --> 00:36:23,930
坐在车里 打扮得漂漂亮亮的
{\fs11}in a carriage, beautifully dressed.{\r}

597
00:36:24,140 --> 00:36:26,890
要是被国王发现你不是个淑女
{\fs11}lf the king finds out that you're not a lady,{\r}

598
00:36:27,100 --> 00:36:29,260
警察就会把你关进伦敦塔
{\fs11}the police will take you to the Tower of London{\r}

599
00:36:29,470 --> 00:36:31,270
在那里砍掉你的脑袋
{\fs11}where your head will be cut off{\r}

600
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:34,390
以警告其他自以为是的卖花儿女孩儿
{\fs11}as a warning to other presumptuous flower girls.{\r}

601
00:36:35,480 --> 00:36:39,820
但要是你没被揭穿 你就会得到
{\fs11}But if you are not found out, you shall have a present{\r}

602
00:36:40,030 --> 00:36:43,860
7镑6先令的奖金并成为一名女店员
{\fs11}of seven and six to start life with as a lady in a shop.{\r}

603
00:36:44,570 --> 00:36:46,410
要是你决绝这个提议
{\fs11}lf you refuse this offer,{\r}

604
00:36:46,620 --> 00:36:50,870
你无疑就是最不领情的 坏女孩儿
{\fs11}you will be the most ungrateful, wicked girl{\r}

605
00:36:51,080 --> 00:36:55,620
连天使都要为你落泪
{\fs11}and the angels will weep for you.{\r}

606
00:36:59,710 --> 00:37:01,250
现在你满意了吧 皮克林？
{\fs11}Now, are you satisfied, Pickering?{\r}

607
00:37:01,460 --> 00:37:03,260
我不明白你在说什么
{\fs11}I don't understand what you're talking about.{\r}

608
00:37:03,470 --> 00:37:05,680
噢 我还要怎样解释才能让她明白 皮尔斯太太？
{\fs11}Oh, could I put it more plainly or fairly, Mrs. Pearce?{\r}

609
00:37:05,890 --> 00:37:06,930
跟我来吧 伊莉莎
{\fs11}Come with me, Eliza.{\r}

610
00:37:07,140 --> 00:37:09,550
没错 皮尔斯太太 就那样把她拖到浴室去
{\fs11}That's right, Mrs. Pearce. Bundle her off to the bathroom.{\r}

611
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:11,930
你真是太欺负人了
{\fs11}You're a great bully, you are.{\r}

612
00:37:12,140 --> 00:37:14,850
要是我不愿意我就会离开这儿 我才不要让别人打我
{\fs11}I won't stay here if I don't like it. I won't let nobody wallop me.{\r}

613
00:37:15,060 --> 00:37:16,100
别顶嘴 丫头
{\fs11}Don't answer back, girl.{\r}

614
00:37:16,310 --> 00:37:19,270
伊莉莎：我要是不知道自己是为什么来的 我才不会来这儿呢
{\fs11}ELIZA: lf I'd known what I was letting myself in for, I wouldn't have come here.{\r}

615
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:21,900
我一直都是个品行端正的女孩儿 我才 我才不会被你骗呢
{\fs11}I've always been a good girl, I am, and I won't be put upon.{\r}

616
00:37:22,110 --> 00:37:23,150
在6个月内
{\fs11}ln six months--{\r}

617
00:37:23,360 --> 00:37:25,320
如果她有一双好耳朵还有一根灵巧的舌头 甚至只要3个月就行
{\fs11}ln three if she has a good ear and a quick tongue.{\r}

618
00:37:25,530 --> 00:37:27,910
我要带她去任何地方 让她扮谁都行
{\fs11}--I'II take her anywhere and I'II pass her off as anything.{\r}

619
00:37:28,120 --> 00:37:31,370
我能将这个不幸的野丫头变成一位王后
{\fs11}I'II make a queen of that barbarous wretch.{\r}

620
00:37:32,290 --> 00:37:34,290
[水流声]
{\fs11}[WATER RUNNING]{\r}

621
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:39,460
伊莉莎：我这辈子都没有洗过澡
{\fs11}ELIZA: I've never had a bath in my life.{\r}

622
00:37:39,670 --> 00:37:41,040
现在你可以真正的洗一回了
{\fs11}Not what you'd call a proper one.{\r}

623
00:37:41,250 --> 00:37:45,340
要知道 如果你仪表不干净的话 你也不可能成为一位有内涵的好女孩儿
{\fs11}You know, you can't be a nice girl inside if you're dirty outside.{\r}

624
00:37:45,550 --> 00:37:49,050
你就住这儿 这里就是你的卧室
{\fs11}I'II have to put you in here. This will be your bedroom.{\r}

625
00:37:52,560 --> 00:37:57,890
噢 我可不能睡在这儿 太太 这儿对我这样的人来说太好了
{\fs11}Oh, I couldn't sleep here, missus. lt's too good for the likes of me.{\r}

626
00:37:59,020 --> 00:38:00,940
这儿的东西我敢都不敢碰
{\fs11}I should be afraid to touch anything.{\r}

627
00:38:01,150 --> 00:38:04,030
我现在还不是公爵夫人呢 你知道吗？
{\fs11}I ain't a duchess yet, you know?{\r}

628
00:38:09,200 --> 00:38:12,080
噢 这是什么 这是你们洗衣服的地方吗？
{\fs11}Oh, what's this? This where you wash clothes?{\r}

629
00:38:12,290 --> 00:38:13,990
这是我们自己洗澡的地方 伊莉莎
{\fs11}This is where we wash ourselves, Eliza.{\r}

630
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:15,910
现在我正要给你洗澡
{\fs11}And where I'm going to wash you.{\r}

631
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:20,040
你打算让我进那里边 然后把我弄得全身湿透？
{\fs11}You expect me to get into that and wet myself all over?{\r}

632
00:38:20,250 --> 00:38:21,670
我不要
{\fs11}Not me.{\r}

633
00:38:27,840 --> 00:38:29,880
我宁可死
{\fs11}I shall catch my death.{\r}

634
00:38:31,970 --> 00:38:34,100
过来
{\fs11}Come along now.{\r}

635
00:38:34,310 --> 00:38:36,930
过来吧 把身上的衣服脱掉
{\fs11}Come along. Take your clothes off.{\r}

636
00:38:38,730 --> 00:38:41,230
别磨蹭了 丫头 听话 把衣服脱掉
{\fs11}Come on, girl, do as you're told. Take your clothes off.{\r}

637
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:45,110
- 快来 帮我把这些拿掉 - 啊噢！不 我不要
{\fs11}- Here, come on, help me take these. - Ow! No, I won't.{\r}

638
00:38:45,320 --> 00:38:46,990
皮尔斯：- 都过来帮忙 - 不 我不要
{\fs11}PEARCE: Come out of that. - No, I won't.{\r}

639
00:38:47,190 --> 00:38:48,740
皮尔斯：- 都来帮忙啊 - 不！
{\fs11}PEARCE: Everyone. - No!{\r}

640
00:38:48,950 --> 00:38:51,870
我不要 把你们的手拿开
{\fs11}I won't. Take your hands off me.{\r}

641
00:38:52,070 --> 00:38:53,120
- 不要 噢 我的天
{\fs11}- No. PEARCE: Oh, dear.{\r}

642
00:38:53,330 --> 00:38:54,660
不 啊噢！
{\fs11}No. Ow!{\r}

643
00:38:55,040 --> 00:38:58,080
- 不 我不要洗澡 让我走 伊莉莎 别动
{\fs11}- No, I won't. Let go. PEARCE: Eliza, keep still.{\r}

644
00:38:58,290 --> 00:39:02,500
[伊莉莎在哭泣]
{\fs11}[ELIZA CRYING]{\r}

645
00:39:05,590 --> 00:39:08,590
[哭泣]
{\fs11}[CRYING]{\r}

646
00:39:09,430 --> 00:39:10,590
皮尔斯：- 就洗个澡 - 不
{\fs11}PEARCE: Take a bath. - No!{\r}

647
00:39:10,800 --> 00:39:12,760
不要！
{\fs11}No!{\r}

648
00:39:12,970 --> 00:39:14,890
我是个品行端正的女孩儿 我是认真的
{\fs11}I'm a good girl, I am.{\r}

649
00:39:15,100 --> 00:39:17,720
皮尔斯：噢 要是你不洗澡的话 他们不会喜欢你身上的味道的
{\fs11}PEARCE: Well, they won't like the smell of you if you don't have a bath.{\r}

650
00:39:17,930 --> 00:39:20,730
伊莉莎：这不行 这太不像话了
{\fs11}ELIZA: lt ain't right. lt ain't decent.{\r}

651
00:39:20,940 --> 00:39:22,900
别拿走我的外套
{\fs11}Let go of my coat.{\r}

652
00:39:23,110 --> 00:39:26,820
[伊莉莎尖叫]
{\fs11}[ELIZA SCREAMING]{\r}

653
00:39:27,030 --> 00:39:28,360
伊莉莎：把你的手拿开
{\fs11}ELIZA: Take your hands off me.{\r}

654
00:39:28,570 --> 00:39:30,200
皮尔斯：过来吧
{\fs11}PEARCE: Come here.{\r}

655
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:31,740
伊莉莎：- 不 - 我不会伤害你的
{\fs11}ELIZA: No. PEARCE: I won't hurt you.{\r}

656
00:39:31,950 --> 00:39:34,530
伊莉莎：让我走
{\fs11}ELIZA: Let me go.{\r}

657
00:39:34,740 --> 00:39:36,580
放手
{\fs11}Take your hands off me.{\r}

658
00:39:36,790 --> 00:39:39,750
我是个品行端正的女孩儿 我是认真的
{\fs11}I'm a good girl, I am.{\r}

659
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:42,750
我说了 放手
{\fs11}Take your hands off me, you hear.{\r}

660
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:45,750
皮尔斯：伊莉莎 我不会放手的
{\fs11}PEARCE: Eliza, I won't have it.{\r}

661
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:49,510
我不会伤害你的
{\fs11}I wouldn't hurt you.{\r}

662
00:39:52,390 --> 00:39:53,930
希金斯 恕我无礼
{\fs11}Higgins, forgive the bluntness,{\r}

663
00:39:54,140 --> 00:39:57,350
既然我也参与此事 我认为自己应该对这个姑娘负责
{\fs11}but if I'm to be in this business, I shall feel responsible for the girl.{\r}

664
00:39:57,560 --> 00:39:59,810
我希望你清楚不能
{\fs11}I hope it's clearly understood that no advantage{\r}

665
00:40:00,020 --> 00:40:01,270
占她任何便宜
{\fs11}is to be taken of her position.{\r}

666
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:04,020
什么 那种事？好吧 我可以向你保证
{\fs11}What, that thing? Sacred, I assure you.{\r}

667
00:40:04,230 --> 00:40:05,810
拜托 希金斯 你明白我的意思
{\fs11}Come now, Higgins, you know what I mean.{\r}

668
00:40:06,020 --> 00:40:07,190
这可不是什么小事儿
{\fs11}This is no trifling matter.{\r}

669
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:10,690
对女人们而言你是一个有着良好品行的男人吧？
{\fs11}Are you a man of good character where women are concerned?{\r}

670
00:40:11,740 --> 00:40:13,360
你有见过对女人们而言
{\fs11}Have you ever met a man of good character{\r}

671
