<i>只要一点点</i>
{\fs11}With a little bit{\r}

839
00:50:30,480 --> 00:50:42,530
<i>只要一点点天赐的好运</i>
{\fs11}With a little bit of bloomin' luck{\r}

840
00:50:49,960 --> 00:50:51,380
您的信 先生
{\fs11}The mail, sir.{\r}

841
00:50:51,590 --> 00:50:53,500
是账单的话就付钱 是邀请函的话就推掉
{\fs11}Pay the bills and say no to the invitations.{\r}

842
00:50:53,710 --> 00:50:57,720
伊莉莎：A
{\fs11}ELIZA: A.{\r}

843
00:50:57,920 --> 00:51:13,440
A
{\fs11}A.{\r}

844
00:51:17,990 --> 00:51:19,780
[大喷嚏]
{\fs11}[SNEEZES]{\r}

845
00:51:32,080 --> 00:51:35,460
A
{\fs11}A.{\r}

846
00:51:35,670 --> 00:51:39,340
A!
{\fs11}A!{\r}

847
00:51:39,550 --> 00:51:41,720
您不能再这样训练那丫头了
{\fs11}You simply cannot go on working the girl this way.{\r}

848
00:51:41,930 --> 00:51:44,100
让她翻来覆去的念字母表
{\fs11}Making her say her alphabet over and over{\r}

849
00:51:44,300 --> 00:51:47,100
从太阳升起直到落下 甚至吃饭的时候都不停
{\fs11}from sunup to sundown, even during meals.{\r}

850
00:51:47,310 --> 00:51:49,640
您这样会把自己累坏的 要什么时候才能结束啊？
{\fs11}You'II exhaust yourself. When will it stop?{\r}

851
00:51:49,850 --> 00:51:51,690
当然直到她能正确念出来为止
{\fs11}When she does it properly, of course.{\r}

852
00:51:51,900 --> 00:51:53,520
还有什么吗 皮尔斯太太?
{\fs11}ls that all, Mrs. Pearce?{\r}

853
00:51:53,730 --> 00:51:54,770
这里还有一封信
{\fs11}There's another letter{\r}

854
00:51:54,980 --> 00:51:57,020
是那个名叫厄斯拉 D 瓦林福德的美国富翁寄来的
{\fs11}from that American millionaire, Ezra D. Wallingford.{\r}

855
00:51:57,230 --> 00:51:59,530
他是希望你能去他的 <i>道德重塑社团</i> 做演讲
{\fs11}He still wants you to lecture for his Moral Reform League.{\r}

856
00:51:59,740 --> 00:52:00,780
噢 好吧 把它扔掉
{\fs11}Yes, well, throw it away.{\r}

857
00:52:00,990 --> 00:52:02,740
这是他写给您的第三封信了
{\fs11}lt's the third letter he's written you, sir.{\r}

858
00:52:02,950 --> 00:52:04,740
- 您总得给个答复吧 - 好吧
{\fs11}- You should at least answer it. - AII right.{\r}

859
00:52:04,950 --> 00:52:07,620
把它放在桌子上吧 皮尔斯太太 我会试着给他回信的
{\fs11}Leave it on the desk, Mrs. Pearce. I'II try and get to it.{\r}

860
00:52:10,330 --> 00:52:12,920
如果您愿意的话 先生 楼下有一位清洁工
{\fs11}lf you please, sir, there's a dustman downstairs,{\r}

861
00:52:13,130 --> 00:52:15,630
自称阿尔弗雷德 P 杜利特 想要见您
{\fs11}Alfred P. Doolittle, who wants to see you.{\r}

862
00:52:15,840 --> 00:52:17,920
他说她女儿在您这儿
{\fs11}He says you have his daughter here.{\r}

863
00:52:18,130 --> 00:52:20,010
我早就跟你说过
{\fs11}PICKERING: I say.{\r}

864
00:52:20,220 --> 00:52:21,670
嗯 让那个无赖上来
{\fs11}Well, send the blackguard up.{\r}

865
00:52:21,880 --> 00:52:24,050
他也许不是个无赖 希金斯
{\fs11}PICKERING: He may not be a blackguard, Higgins.{\r}

866
00:52:24,260 --> 00:52:26,390
胡说 他当然是个无赖 皮克林
{\fs11}Nonsense. Of course he's a blackguard, Pickering.{\r}

867
00:52:26,600 --> 00:52:29,720
不管他是不是 我恐怕他会给我们找麻烦的
{\fs11}Whether he is or not, I'm afraid we'II have some trouble with him.{\r}

868
00:52:29,930 --> 00:52:30,980
不 我不这么认为
{\fs11}No, I think not.{\r}

869
00:52:31,180 --> 00:52:34,310
即便有什么麻烦 那也是我找他麻烦 而不是他找我
{\fs11}Any trouble to be had, he'II have it with me, not I with him.{\r}

870
00:52:37,150 --> 00:52:39,320
杜利特到了 先生
{\fs11}Doolittle, sir.{\r}

871
00:52:44,950 --> 00:52:46,160
希金斯教授？
{\fs11}Professor Higgins?{\r}

872
00:52:46,370 --> 00:52:48,030
希金斯：过来吧
{\fs11}HIGGINS: Here.{\r}

873
00:52:48,240 --> 00:52:49,790
哪儿？
{\fs11}Where?{\r}

874
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:51,870
噢 早上好 先生
{\fs11}Oh, good morning, governor.{\r}

875
00:52:52,080 --> 00:52:56,040
我来是为件非常重要的事的 先生
{\fs11}I come about a very serious matter, governor.{\r}

876
00:52:58,590 --> 00:53:01,170
在豪恩斯洛长大
{\fs11}Brought up in Hounslow.{\r}

877
00:53:01,380 --> 00:53:04,180
母亲是威尔士人 我想
{\fs11}Mother Welsh, I should think.{\r}

878
00:53:04,380 --> 00:53:05,720
你想要什么 杜利特？
{\fs11}What is it you want, Doolittle?{\r}

879
00:53:05,930 --> 00:53:08,600
我想要回我女儿 就是这样 明白了吗？
{\fs11}I want my daughter, that's what I want, you see?{\r}

880
00:53:08,810 --> 00:53:11,020
嗯 当然是这样 你是她父亲 对吗？
{\fs11}Well, of course you do. You're her father, aren't you?{\r}

881
00:53:11,220 --> 00:53:13,600
我很高兴看到你还有那么点儿亲情
{\fs11}I'm glad to see you have a spark of family feeling left.{\r}

882
00:53:13,810 --> 00:53:15,940
她就在里边 好的 马上把她带走吧
{\fs11}She's in there. Yes, take her away at once.{\r}

883
00:53:16,690 --> 00:53:18,150
什么？
{\fs11}What?{\r}

884
00:53:18,360 --> 00:53:19,400
把她带走
{\fs11}Take her away.{\r}

885
00:53:19,610 --> 00:53:22,110
你认为我会替你照看女儿吗？
{\fs11}Do you think I am going to keep your daughter for you?{\r}

886
00:53:22,320 --> 00:53:25,030
噢 这样做合理吗 先生？
{\fs11}Now, is this reasonable, governor?{\r}

887
00:53:25,240 --> 00:53:28,240
这样占别人便宜公平吗？
{\fs11}ls it fairity to take advantage of a man like that?{\r}

888
00:53:28,450 --> 00:53:30,370
这个女孩儿是我的 你占有了她
{\fs11}The girl belongs to me. You got her.{\r}

889
00:53:30,580 --> 00:53:31,830
我该怎么办？
{\fs11}Where do I come in?{\r}

890
00:53:32,040 --> 00:53:36,250
你怎么胆敢上这儿勒索我
{\fs11}How dare you come here and attempt to blackmail me.{\r}

891
00:53:36,460 --> 00:53:38,330
也许就是你故意把她送这儿来的
{\fs11}You sent her here on purpose.{\r}

892
00:53:38,540 --> 00:53:42,090
噢 你怎么可以这样指控别人 先生
{\fs11}Now, don't take a man up like that, governor.{\r}

893
00:53:42,300 --> 00:53:43,420
警察自然会指控你
{\fs11}The police shall take you up.{\r}

894
00:53:43,630 --> 00:53:46,510
这是有预谋的 以威胁手段进行勒索的阴谋
{\fs11}This is a plan, a plot to extort money by threats.{\r}

895
00:53:46,720 --> 00:53:48,550
我要打电话报警
{\fs11}I shall telephone the police.{\r}

896
00:53:48,760 --> 00:53:52,100
我有问你要过一个子儿吗？
{\fs11}Have I asked you for a brass farthing?{\r}

897
00:53:52,310 --> 00:53:55,940
让旁边的这位绅士来评评理 我哪怕有一个字提到钱了吗？
{\fs11}I'II leave it to this gentleman here. Have I said a word about money?{\r}

898
00:53:56,140 --> 00:53:57,940
那你来是为什么？
{\fs11}What else did you come for?{\r}

899
00:53:58,150 --> 00:53:59,770
嗯...
{\fs11}Well...{\r}

900
00:53:59,980 --> 00:54:02,190
一个醉鬼来能为什么？
{\fs11}What would a bloke come for?{\r}

901
00:54:02,400 --> 00:54:04,400
做人得讲道理 先生
{\fs11}Be human, governor.{\r}

902
00:54:04,610 --> 00:54:06,700
[笑声]
{\fs11}[LAUGHS]{\r}

903
00:54:09,370 --> 00:54:12,080
阿尔弗雷德 你是故意把她送到这儿来的
{\fs11}Alfred, you sent her here on purpose.{\r}

904
00:54:12,290 --> 00:54:13,950
相信我 先生 我没有那样做
{\fs11}So help me, governor, I never did.{\r}

905
00:54:14,160 --> 00:54:15,540
那你怎么知道她在这儿？
{\fs11}Then how did you know she was here?{\r}

906
00:54:15,750 --> 00:54:18,460
我会告诉你的 先生 如果你能让我说的话
{\fs11}I'd tell you, governor, if you'd only let me get a word in.{\r}

907
00:54:18,670 --> 00:54:21,590
我这就要告诉你 我正想要告诉你
{\fs11}I'm willing to tell you. I'm wanting to tell you.{\r}

908
00:54:21,800 --> 00:54:24,090
我正迫不及待的要告诉你
{\fs11}I'm waiting to tell you.{\r}

909
00:54:25,380 --> 00:54:26,420
你看 皮克林
{\fs11}You know, Pickering,{\r}

910
00:54:26,630 --> 00:54:29,430
这家伙确实有点语言天赋
{\fs11}this chap's got a certain natural gift of rhetoric.{\r}

911
00:54:29,640 --> 00:54:32,430
请注意他说话时如林中鸟叫般的节奏
{\fs11}Observe the rhythm of his native woodnotes wild.{\r}

912
00:54:32,640 --> 00:54:34,720
“我这就要告诉你 我正想要告诉你
{\fs11}"I'm willing to tell you. I'm wanting to tell you.{\r}

913
00:54:34,930 --> 00:54:39,140
我正迫不及待的要告诉你”这就是他变形的威尔士口音
{\fs11}I'm waiting to tell you." That's the Welsh strain in him.{\r}

914
00:54:39,350 --> 00:54:41,980
要不是你把她送来的你怎么知道伊莉莎在这儿？
{\fs11}How did you know Eliza was here if you didn't send her?{\r}

915
00:54:42,190 --> 00:54:45,190
嗯 她送信说要取走她的行李 我正好听说了
{\fs11}Well, she sent back for her luggage and I got to hear about it.{\r}

916
00:54:45,400 --> 00:54:48,610
还说所有的衣服她都不要了
{\fs11}She said she didn't want no clothes.{\r}

917
00:54:48,820 --> 00:54:50,410
听到这些我会怎么想 先生？
{\fs11}What was I to think from that, governor?{\r}

918
00:54:50,620 --> 00:54:53,660
请问你 作为一位父亲 我会怎么想？
{\fs11}I ask you, as a parent, what was I to think?{\r}

919
00:54:53,870 --> 00:54:57,790
那么你是来趁她还活着赶来救她的吗 嗯？
{\fs11}So you came here to rescue her from worse than death, eh?{\r}

920
00:54:58,000 --> 00:54:59,460
没错 先生 正是这样
{\fs11}Just so, governor, that's right.{\r}

921
00:54:59,670 --> 00:55:00,750
那好
{\fs11}Yes.{\r}

922
00:55:00,960 --> 00:55:02,580
皮尔斯太太
{\fs11}Mrs. Pearce.{\r}

923
00:55:02,790 --> 00:55:05,750
皮尔斯太太 伊莉莎的父亲要带她走了
{\fs11}Mrs. Pearce, Eliza's father has come to take her away.{\r}

924
00:55:05,960 --> 00:55:07,090
把她交给他 好吗？
{\fs11}Give her to him, will you?{\r}

925
00:55:07,300 --> 00:55:11,510
噢 等等 先生 等等
{\fs11}Now, wait a minute, governor, wait a minute.{\r}

926
00:55:11,720 --> 00:55:14,600
你我都是男人 不是吗？
{\fs11}You and me is men of the world, ain't we?{\r}

927
00:55:14,810 --> 00:55:17,350
噢 我们都是男人 不是吗？
{\fs11}Oh, men of the world, are we?{\r}

928
00:55:17,560 --> 00:55:20,940
- 好吧 你先出去 皮尔斯太太 - 我确实也是那样想的 先生
{\fs11}- Yes, you better go, Mrs. Pearce. - I think so indeed, sir.{\r}

929
00:55:21,150 --> 00:55:22,190
嘿 先生
{\fs11}Here, governor.{\r}

930
00:55:22,400 --> 00:55:26,070
我本以为你是抱着某种想法
{\fs11}I've took a sort of a fancy to you and--{\r}

931
00:55:26,280 --> 00:55:27,860
[笑声]
{\fs11}[LAUGHS]{\r}

932
00:55:29,110 --> 00:55:32,200
如果你想要这个女孩儿 那好吧 我也就不坚持要把她带回去了
{\fs11}lf you want the girl, well, I ain't so set on having her back home again,{\r}

933
00:55:32,410 --> 00:55:35,700
不过我还是得把话说清楚
{\fs11}but what I might be open to is an arrangement.{\r}

934
00:55:35,910 --> 00:55:38,250
我所要求的不过是一位父亲正当的权利
{\fs11}AII I ask is my rights as a father.{\r}

935
00:55:38,460 --> 00:55:42,170
即便是这世上就你最后一个男人 您也不会指望我什么都不要就让她跟你走吧
{\fs11}You're the last man alive to expect me to let her go for nothing.{\r}

936
00:55:42,380 --> 00:55:45,540
噢 我看得出您是那种正直的人 先生
{\fs11}Oh, I can see you're one of the straight sort, governor.{\r}

937
00:55:45,750 --> 00:55:48,670
因此 您觉得5张1英镑的对您来说算什么？
{\fs11}So, what's a 5-pound note to you?{\r}

938
00:55:48,880 --> 00:55:51,550
我的伊莉莎总值这个价吧？
{\fs11}And what's Eliza to me?{\r}

939
00:55:51,760 --> 00:55:53,220
我想应该让你知道 杜利特
{\fs11}I think you ought to know, Doolittle,{\r}

940
00:55:53,430 --> 00:55:56,350
这位希金斯先生把你女儿接到这里 用意是绝对高尚的
{\fs11}that Mr. Higgins' intentions are entirely honorable.{\r}

941
00:55:56,560 --> 00:55:58,270
当然是这样 先生
{\fs11}Of course they are, governor.{\r}

942
00:55:58,480 --> 00:56:00,980
要不是这样 我会要50镑的
{\fs11}lf I thought they wasn't, I'd ask 50.{\r}

943
00:56:01,190 --> 00:56:04,270
你的意思是说你打算以50镑卖掉你的女儿？
{\fs11}Do you mean to say you'd sell your daughter for 50 pounds?{\r}

944
00:56:04,480 --> 00:56:05,980
你连一点道德都没有吗 伙计？
{\fs11}Have you no morals, man?{\r}

945
00:56:07,690 --> 00:56:10,440
不 不 我可买不起它们 先生
{\fs11}No, no, I can't afford them, governor.{\r}

946
00:56:10,650 --> 00:56:12,780
要是您跟我一样穷 你也会这样的
{\fs11}Neither could you if you was as poor as me.{\r}

947
00:56:12,990 --> 00:56:14,410
我想提醒你们 我并没有什么恶意
{\fs11}Not that I mean any harm, mind you.{\r}

948
00:56:14,620 --> 00:56:17,450
但既然伊莉莎可以得到一些好处的话
{\fs11}But if Eliza is gonna have a bit out of this,{\r}

949
00:56:17,660 --> 00:56:19,870
那我为什么不能呢 嗯？
{\fs11}why not me too, eh?{\r}

950
00:56:20,080 --> 00:56:21,120
为什么不能呢？
{\fs11}Why not?{\r}

951
00:56:21,330 --> 00:56:25,790
噢 从我的角度来看
{\fs11}Well, look at it my way.{\r}

952
00:56:26,000 --> 00:56:28,960
我是什么？我问你 我是什么？
{\fs11}What am I? I ask you, what am I?{\r}

953
00:56:29,170 --> 00:56:31,590
我是个不值得可怜的人 就是这样
{\fs11}I'm one of the undeserving poor, that's what I am.{\r}

954
00:56:31,800 --> 00:56:33,680
现在 想想看这对一个男人意味着什么
{\fs11}Now, think what that means to a man.{\r}

955
00:56:33,890 --> 00:56:38,060
这意味着他一生都要同中产阶级所谓的道德观对抗
{\fs11}lt means he's up against middle-class morality for all of time.{\r}

956
00:56:38,260 --> 00:56:40,560
不论发生什么 我想要的就只是得到点儿好处
{\fs11}lf there's anything going and I puts in for a bit of it,{\r}

957
00:56:40,770 --> 00:56:41,850
结果往往都是这样
{\fs11}it's always the same story.{\r}

958
00:56:42,060 --> 00:56:44,810
“你不配接受救济 所以不会给你”
{\fs11}"You're undeserving so you can't have it."{\r}

959
00:56:45,020 --> 00:56:48,020
可我真的需要 就如同那些最需要救济的寡妇一样
{\fs11}But my needs is as great as the most deserving widows{\r}

960
00:56:48,230 --> 00:56:51,240
她们每周都能从6个不同的慈善团体得到救济金
{\fs11}that ever got money out of six different charities in one week{\r}

961
00:56:51,440 --> 00:56:53,570
只因为死了同一个丈夫
{\fs11}for the death of the same husband.{\r}

962
00:56:53,780 --> 00:56:57,450
我要的不应该比一个需要救济的人少 而是更多
{\fs11}I don't need less than a deserving man, I need more.{\r}

963
00:56:57,660 --> 00:56:59,830
我吃得不比他少
{\fs11}I don't eat less hearty than he does.{\r}

964
00:57:00,040 --> 00:57:02,830
此外我还要喝酒 很多的酒
{\fs11}And I drink, oh, a lot more.{\r}

965
00:57:03,040 --> 00:57:06,880
我实话跟你说吧 我不是装作需要救济
{\fs11}I'm playing straight with you. I ain't pretending to be deserving.{\r}

966
00:57:07,090 --> 00:57:09,130
不 我不需要救济
{\fs11}No, I'm undeserving.{\r}

967
00:57:09,340 --> 00:57:11,340
我是说即便没有救济也可以生活
{\fs11}And I mean to go on being undeserving.{\r}

968
00:57:11,550 --> 00:57:13,260
可我也喜欢接受救济 这就是事实
{\fs11}I like it, and that's the truth.{\r}

969
00:57:13,470 --> 00:57:17,300
不过占便宜是人的天性
{\fs11}But will you take advantage of a man's nature{\r}

970
00:57:17,510 --> 00:57:19,390
你会不付出代价就将别人的女儿带走吧
{\fs11}to do him out of the price of his own daughter,{\r}

971
00:57:19,600 --> 00:57:24,020
想想他是怎样一手抚养 用自己的汗水供她吃穿
{\fs11}what he's brought up, fed and clothed by the sweat of his brow{\r}

972
00:57:24,230 --> 00:57:25,560
直到她长大到
{\fs11}till she's growed big enough{\r}

973
00:57:25,770 --> 00:57:29,610
你们两位绅士对她有了兴趣？
{\fs11}to be interesting to you two gentlemen?{\r}

974
00:57:29,820 --> 00:57:34,320
噢 这样5镑都还不合理吗？你们想想看吧
{\fs11}Well, is 5 pounds unreasonable? I put it to you.{\r}

975
00:57:34,530 --> 00:57:36,740
你们看着办吧
{\fs11}And I leave it to you.{\r}

976
00:57:39,030 --> 00:57:42,450
你知道吗 皮克林 要是我们能把这个人训练3个月
{\fs11}You know, Pickering, if we took this man in hand for three months,{\r}

977
00:57:42,660 --> 00:57:44,460
他就可以选择进入内阁
{\fs11}he could choose between a seat in the cabinet{\r}

978
00:57:44,660 --> 00:57:47,250
或是威尔士的任一所教堂供职
{\fs11}and a popular pulpit in Wales.{\r}

979
00:57:47,460 --> 00:57:48,960
我们最好给他5镑
{\fs11}We'd better give him a fiver.{\r}

980
00:57:49,170 --> 00:57:51,130
我恐怕他不会拿去好好用的
{\fs11}He'II make bad use of it, I'm afraid.{\r}

981
00:57:51,340 --> 00:57:53,260
噢 我不会的 先生 请相信我 我不会的
{\fs11}Oh, not me, governor. So help me, I won't.{\r}

982
00:57:53,470 --> 00:57:55,840
只是为了让我和我太太能好好喝一台
{\fs11}Just one good spree for myself and the missus.{\r}

983
00:57:56,050 --> 00:57:59,140
给我们的生活增添点乐趣 同时也让别人有活儿可干
{\fs11}Giving pleasure to ourselves and employment to others.{\r}

984
00:57:59,350 --> 00:58:02,010
您会满意的知道 您的钱并没有被浪费掉的
{\fs11}And satisfaction to you to know it ain't been thrown away.{\r}

985
00:58:02,220 --> 00:58:03,430
您不可能把它用在比这更好的地方了
{\fs11}You couldn't spend it better.{\r}

986
00:58:03,640 --> 00:58:06,270
噢 真是没救了 给他10镑吧
{\fs11}Oh, this is irresistible. Let's give him 1 0.{\r}

987
00:58:06,480 --> 00:58:09,190
不 我太太可不知道该怎么花掉这10镑 先生
{\fs11}No, the missus wouldn't have the heart to spend 1 0, governor.{\r}

988
00:58:09,400 --> 00:58:10,980
10镑可太多了
{\fs11}Ten pounds is a lot of money.{\r}

989
00:58:11,190 --> 00:58:14,900
会让人觉得该精打细算 这样就没有快乐了
{\fs11}Makes a man feel prudent-like, and then goodbye to happiness.{\r}

990
00:58:15,110 --> 00:58:19,410
不 你只要给我要的数目就好 先生 不要少给1个便士 也不要多给1个便士
{\fs11}No, you give me what I ask, governor. Not a penny less, not a penny more.{\r}

991
00:58:19,620 --> 00:58:22,580
我实在不支持这种不道德的事 杜利特
{\fs11}I rather draw the line at encouraging this sort of immorality, Doolittle.{\r}

992
00:58:22,790 --> 00:58:24,620
你为什么不跟你所谓的那位太太结婚呢 嗯？
{\fs11}Why don't you marry that missus of yours, eh?{\r}

993
00:58:24,830 --> 00:58:27,790
毕竟 婚姻没那么可怕吧 你之前也同伊莉莎的母亲结过婚
{\fs11}After all, marriage isn't so frightening. You married Eliza's mother.{\r}

994
00:58:28,000 --> 00:58:29,790
谁告诉你我结过婚 先生？
{\fs11}Who told you that, governor?{\r}

995
00:58:30,000 --> 00:58:33,840
噢 没人告诉我 是我自己推断的
{\fs11}Well, nobody told me. I concluded, naturally.{\r}

996
00:58:37,050 --> 00:58:38,800
要是我们再听这人多说一分钟
{\fs11}lf we listen to this man for another minute,{\r}

997
00:58:39,010 --> 00:58:40,390
我们自己的正义感就要消失殆尽了
{\fs11}we shall have no convictions left.{\r}

998
00:58:40,600 --> 00:58:43,220
- 5镑对吧 我记得你说你要 - 谢谢您 先生 谢谢
{\fs11}- Five pounds, I think you said. - Thank you, governor, thank you.{\r}

999
00:58:43,430 --> 00:58:44,680
你确定你不要10镑？
{\fs11}Are you sure you won't have 1 0?{\r}

1000
00:58:44,890 --> 00:58:48,520
- 不 不 也许下次吧 - 我再也不要了 我再也不要了 我再也不要了
{\fs11}- No, no, perhaps another time. - I won't, I won't, I won't.{\r}

1001
00:58:48,730 --> 00:58:50,230
我没听明白 女士
{\fs11}I beg your pardon, miss.{\r}

1002
00:58:50,440 --> 00:58:53,070
伊莉莎：我再也不要念这些该死的元音了
{\fs11}ELIZA: I won't say those ruddy vowels one more time.{\r}

1003
00:58:53,270 --> 00:58:55,070
啊 是伊莉莎
{\fs11}Blimey, it's Eliza.{\r}

1004
00:58:55,280 --> 00:58:57,740
噢 我从没想过 她弄干净了会是这样好看
{\fs11}Well, I never thought she'd clean up so good-looking.{\r}

1005
00:58:57,950 --> 00:58:59,780
她真是给我挣脸 对吧 先生？
{\fs11}She does me credit, don't she, governor?{\r}

1006
00:58:59,990 --> 00:59:02,370
嘿 你来这儿干什么？
{\fs11}Here, what you doing here?{\r}

1007
00:59:02,580 --> 00:59:04,080
噢 现在起 你别再说了
{\fs11}Now, now, you hold your tongue.{\r}

1008
00:59:04,290 --> 00:59:07,330
在这些绅士面前把你的嘴闭上
{\fs11}And don't you give these gentlemen none of your lip.{\r}

1009
00:59:07,540 --> 00:59:09,250
要是她给您惹了什么麻烦 先生
{\fs11}lf you have any trouble with her, governor,{\r}

1010
00:59:09,460 --> 00:59:10,830
就用皮带好好抽她几下
{\fs11}give her a few licks of the strap.{\r}

1011
00:59:11,040 --> 00:59:13,380
这样她就会学乖了
{\fs11}That's the way to improve her mind.{\r}

1012
00:59:13,590 --> 00:59:15,000
嗯 早安了 绅士们
{\fs11}Well, good morning, gentlemen.{\r}

1013
00:59:15,210 --> 00:59:17,510
- 加油 伊莉莎 - 啊!
{\fs11}- Cheerio, Eliza. - Mah!{\r}

1014
00:59:19,970 --> 00:59:21,010
你可算是碰见了
{\fs11}There's a man for you.{\r}

1015
00:59:21,220 --> 00:59:23,760
一位最优秀的哲学天才
{\fs11}A philosophical genius of the first water.{\r}

1016
00:59:23,970 --> 00:59:27,140
皮尔斯太太 回信给厄斯拉 瓦林福德先生
{\fs11}Mrs. Pearce, write to Mr. Ezra Wallingford{\r}

1017
00:59:27,350 --> 00:59:28,770
告诉他如果他想找一位演说家
{\fs11}and tell him if he wants a lecturer{\r}

1018
00:59:28,980 --> 00:59:30,810
可以同阿尔弗雷德 P 杜利特先生联系
{\fs11}to get in touch with Mr. Alfred P. Doolittle,{\r}

1019
00:59:31,020 --> 00:59:33,610
一位普通的清洁工 英国最具创新的道德学家之一
{\fs11}a common dustman, one of the most original moralists in England.{\r}

1020
00:59:33,820 --> 00:59:34,900
好的 先生
{\fs11}Yes, sir.{\r}

1021
00:59:35,110 --> 00:59:36,980
嘿 他来这里干嘛？
{\fs11}Here, what did he come for?{\r}

1022
00:59:37,190 --> 00:59:38,240
念你的元音去
{\fs11}Say your vowels.{\r}

1023
00:59:38,440 --> 00:59:40,200
我会念元音 我来之前就会念了
{\fs11}I know my vowels. I knew them before I come.{\r}

1024
00:59:40,410 --> 00:59:41,530
如果你会念了 那就念念看
{\fs11}lf you know them, say them.{\r}

1025
00:59:41,740 --> 00:59:44,490
- Ahyee e iyee ow you
{\fs11}[IN COCKNEY ACCENT] A, E, I, O, U.{\r}

1026
00:59:44,700 --> 00:59:45,950
停下
{\fs11}Stop.{\r}

1027
00:59:46,160 --> 00:59:48,330
- A, E, I, O, U
{\fs11}A, E, I, O, U.{\r}

1028
00:59:48,540 --> 00:59:51,330
我就是这么念的 A, E, I, O, U
{\fs11}[IN COCKNEY ACCENT] That's what said, A, E, I, O, U.{\r}

1029
00:59:51,540 --> 00:59:53,130
我都念了三天了
{\fs11}That's what I been saying for three days{\r}

1030
00:59:53,330 --> 00:59:54,460
我再也不想念了
{\fs11}and I won't say them no more.{\r}

1031
00:59:54,670 --> 00:59:57,670
我知道这很难 杜利特小姐 不过你要理解
{\fs11}I know it's difficult, Miss Doolittle, but try to understand.{\r}

1032
00:59:57,880 --> 00:59:59,340
解释是没用的 皮克林
{\fs11}There's no use explaining, Pickering.{\r}

1033
00:59:59,550 --> 01:00:02,130
作为一名军人 你很清楚 她现在需要的就是训练
{\fs11}As a military man, you know that. Drilling is what she needs.{\r}

1034
01:00:02,340 --> 01:00:04,970
现在起 别理她 否则就会转而向你寻求同情
{\fs11}Now, leave her alone or she'II be turning to you for sympathy.{\r}

1035
01:00:05,180 --> 01:00:08,220
那好吧 如果你坚持的话 不过请你对她耐心点儿 希金斯
{\fs11}Very well, if you insist, but have a little patience with her, Higgins.{\r}

1036
01:00:08,430 --> 01:00:09,810
当然
{\fs11}Of course.{\r}

1037
01:00:10,020 --> 01:00:11,390
现在念“A”
{\fs11}Now say "A."{\r}

1038
01:00:11,600 --> 01:00:13,650
你根本就没长心 绝对没有
{\fs11}You ain't got no heart, you ain't.{\r}

1039
01:00:13,860 --> 01:00:20,070
- A - A
{\fs11}- A. - A.{\r}

1040
01:00:20,280 --> 01:00:21,360
伊莉莎
{\fs11}Eliza.{\r}

1041
01:00:21,570 --> 01:00:25,450
我向你保证 今天之内你必须把你的元音念正确
{\fs11}I promise you, you'II say your vowels correctly before this day is out{\r}

1042
01:00:25,660 --> 01:00:28,040
否则就没有午餐 没有晚餐
{\fs11}or there'II be no lunch, no dinner{\r}

1043
01:00:28,240 --> 01:00:31,160
也没有巧克力
{\fs11}and no chocolates.{\r}

1044
01:00:41,380 --> 01:00:45,680
<i>你等着吧 亨利 希金斯 你等着吧</i>
{\fs11}[SINGING] Just you wait, Henry Higgins Just you wait{\r}

1045
01:00:45,890 --> 01:00:50,180
<i>你会后悔的 可到那时就算你哭得一塌糊涂也太晚了</i>
{\fs11}You'II be sorry But your tears will be too late{\r}

1046
01:00:50,390 --> 01:00:52,520
<i>等你破产了 而我有钱了</i>
{\fs11}You'II be broke And I'II have money{\r}

1047
01:00:52,730 --> 01:00:54,810
<i>我会帮你吗？ 别开玩笑了</i>
{\fs11}Will I help you? Don't be funny{\r}

1048
01:00:55,020 --> 01:00:59,570
<i>你等着吧 亨利 希金斯 你等着吧</i>
{\fs11}Just you wait, Henry Higgins Just you wait{\r}

1049
01:00:59,780 --> 01:01:03,700
<i>你等着吧 亨利 希金斯 等你得了病</i>
{\fs11}Just you wait, Henry Higgins, Till you're sick{\r}

1050
01:01:03,910 --> 01:01:08,240
<i>尖叫着 快去请医生的时候</i>
{\fs11}And you screams To fetch a doctor double-quick{\r}

1051
01:01:08,450 --> 01:01:12,910
<i>我会马上出发 直奔剧院</i>
{\fs11}I'II be off a second later And go straight to the theatre{\r}

1052
01:01:13,120 --> 01:01:17,380
<i>呵 呵 呵 亨利 希金斯 你等着吧</i>
{\fs11}Ho, ho, ho, Henry Higgins Just you wait{\r}

1053
01:01:18,500 --> 01:01:21,710
<i>噢呵 亨利 希金斯</i>
{\fs11}Ooh, Henry Higgins{\r}

1054
01:01:21,920 --> 01:01:26,510
<i>你等着吧 等我们去海里游泳</i>
{\fs11}Just you wait Until we're swimmin' in the sea{\r}

1055
01:01:26,930 --> 01:01:30,180
<i>噢呵 亨利 希金斯</i>
{\fs11}Ooh, Henry Higgins{\r}

1056
01:01:30,390 --> 01:01:34,770
<i>你抽筋了 就在离我不远的地方</i>
{\fs11}And you gets a cramp A little ways from me{\r}

1057
01:01:34,980 --> 01:01:36,850
<i>就在你大叫你就要被淹死了的时候</i>
{\fs11}When you yell you're gonna drown{\r}

1058
01:01:37,060 --> 01:01:39,190
<i>我会穿好衣服回城去</i>
{\fs11}I'II get dressed and go to town{\r}

1059
01:01:39,400 --> 01:01:44,070
<i>呵 呵 呵 亨利 希金斯</i>
{\fs11}Ho, ho, ho, Henry Higgins{\r}

1060
01:01:44,280 --> 01:01:48,700
<i>你等着吧</i>
{\fs11}Just you wait{\r}

1061
01:01:50,830 --> 01:01:53,700
<i>有一天我会成为贵妇</i>
{\fs11}One day I'II be famous{\r}

1062
01:01:53,910 --> 01:01:56,250
<i>言行举止适当又高贵</i>
{\fs11}I'II be proper and prim{\r}

1063
01:01:56,460 --> 01:01:58,750
<i>三天两头就去圣 詹姆斯教堂</i>
{\fs11}Go to St. James so often{\r}

1064
01:01:58,960 --> 01:02:01,550
<i>我会称它圣 吉姆教堂</i>
{\fs11}I will call it St. Jim{\r}

1065
01:02:02,210 --> 01:02:04,920
<i>有一天晚上国王会说：</i>
{\fs11}One evening the king will say:{\r}

