01:28:20,710 --> 01:28:25,040
但我相信是他们把那个老太太“送走”了
{\fs11}But it's my belief they done the old woman in.{\r}

1476
01:28:25,710 --> 01:28:27,380
把她“送走”了？
{\fs11}MRS. HIGGINS: Done her in?{\r}

1477
01:28:27,590 --> 01:28:29,380
是啊 上帝保佑
{\fs11}Yes, Lord love you.{\r}

1478
01:28:29,590 --> 01:28:31,880
她怎么可能死于流行感冒
{\fs11}Why should she die of influenza{\r}

1479
01:28:32,090 --> 01:28:35,930
之前那年她得了白喉都挺过来了？
{\fs11}when she come through diphtheria right enough the year before?{\r}

1480
01:28:36,140 --> 01:28:38,810
当时她脸色都变成那种深蓝色了
{\fs11}Fairly blue with it, she was.{\r}

1481
01:28:39,020 --> 01:28:40,890
他们全都以为她已经死了
{\fs11}They all thought she was dead.{\r}

1482
01:28:41,100 --> 01:28:45,360
可我父亲 不停地朝她喉咙里灌杜松子酒
{\fs11}But my father, he kept ladling gin down her throat.{\r}

1483
01:28:45,570 --> 01:28:47,480
[希金斯在呻吟]
{\fs11}[HIGGINS GROANS]{\r}

1484
01:28:50,150 --> 01:28:51,950
然后她突然就活过来了
{\fs11}Then she come to so sudden,{\r}

1485
01:28:52,160 --> 01:28:54,240
还把勺子的勺碗咬了下来
{\fs11}she bit the bowl off the spoon.{\r}

1486
01:28:54,450 --> 01:28:55,490
[弗雷迪在笑]
{\fs11}[FREDDY LAUGHS]{\r}

1487
01:28:55,700 --> 01:28:56,990
我的天
{\fs11}Dear me.{\r}

1488
01:28:58,540 --> 01:29:01,540
所以 一个有这么大力气的女人怎么
{\fs11}Now, what call would a woman with that strength in her{\r}

1489
01:29:01,750 --> 01:29:04,250
可能死于流行感冒？
{\fs11}have to die of influenza?{\r}

1490
01:29:04,460 --> 01:29:09,500
为什么原本用来给她买新草帽的钱现在成了我的？
{\fs11}What become of her new straw hat that should have come to me?{\r}

1491
01:29:09,710 --> 01:29:11,050
[听不见的对话]
{\fs11}[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]{\r}

1492
01:29:11,260 --> 01:29:14,380
有人把它省下来了
{\fs11}Somebody pinched it.{\r}

1493
01:29:15,050 --> 01:29:16,970
所以要我说
{\fs11}And what I say is,{\r}

1494
01:29:17,180 --> 01:29:20,600
他们就是这样不断地省下钱 然后把她“送走”了
{\fs11}them that's pinched it done her in.{\r}

1495
01:29:20,810 --> 01:29:24,190
把她“送走”了？你是说 把她“送走”了？
{\fs11}Done her in? Done her in, did you say?{\r}

1496
01:29:24,400 --> 01:29:26,230
这是什么意思？
{\fs11}Whatever does it mean?{\r}

1497
01:29:26,440 --> 01:29:28,320
噢 这是个新的说法
{\fs11}Oh, that's the new small talk.{\r}

1498
01:29:28,520 --> 01:29:31,030
把某个人“送走”就相当于把他们杀掉
{\fs11}To do somebody in means to kill them.{\r}

1499
01:29:31,240 --> 01:29:34,860
可你不会真的认为你姑妈是被谋杀的吧？
{\fs11}But you surely don't believe your aunt was killed?{\r}

1500
01:29:35,070 --> 01:29:36,370
怎么不会？
{\fs11}Do I not?{\r}

1501
01:29:36,570 --> 01:29:41,870
他们为了一根帽针的钱也不会让她活着 更别说是帽子
{\fs11}Them she lived with would have killed her for a hatpin, let alone a hat.{\r}

1502
01:29:42,080 --> 01:29:44,790
可你父亲的办法也不对
{\fs11}But it can't have been right for your father{\r}

1503
01:29:45,000 --> 01:29:47,250
像那样朝她喉咙里灌烈性酒
{\fs11}to pour spirits down her throat like that.{\r}

1504
01:29:47,460 --> 01:29:49,340
那样也许会杀了她了
{\fs11}lt might have killed her.{\r}

1505
01:29:49,550 --> 01:29:50,800
不可能
{\fs11}Not her.{\r}

1506
01:29:51,010 --> 01:29:53,630
杜松子酒对她来说就像母乳一样
{\fs11}Gin was mother's milk to her.{\r}

1507
01:29:53,840 --> 01:29:57,180
而且 他朝自己的喉咙里也灌了不少
{\fs11}Besides, he poured so much down his own throat,{\r}

1508
01:29:57,390 --> 01:29:59,180
他知道这样做有好处
{\fs11}he knew the good of it.{\r}

1509
01:29:59,390 --> 01:30:01,220
你是说他喝醉了？
{\fs11}Do you mean that he drank?{\r}

1510
01:30:01,430 --> 01:30:04,430
喝醉 照我说 还差得远
{\fs11}Drank, my word, something chronic.{\r}

1511
01:30:05,600 --> 01:30:07,730
[弗雷迪在笑]
{\fs11}[FREDDY LAUGHING]{\r}

1512
01:30:07,940 --> 01:30:11,360
嘿 你偷偷笑什么呢？
{\fs11}Here, what are you sniggering at?{\r}

1513
01:30:11,570 --> 01:30:12,820
那个新说法
{\fs11}lt's the new small talk.{\r}

1514
01:30:13,030 --> 01:30:15,150
你说得太有趣了
{\fs11}You do it so awfully well.{\r}

1515
01:30:15,360 --> 01:30:19,490
噢 要是我说的没错 那你又偷偷笑什么呢？
{\fs11}Well, if I was doing it proper, what was you sniggering at?{\r}

1516
01:30:19,700 --> 01:30:21,740
我说了什么不该说的话吗？
{\fs11}Have I said anything I oughtn't?{\r}

1517
01:30:21,950 --> 01:30:23,790
希金斯：噢 不
{\fs11}HIGGINS: Oh, no.{\r}

1518
01:30:24,000 --> 01:30:25,540
没有 亲爱的
{\fs11}Not at all, my dear.{\r}

1519
01:30:25,750 --> 01:30:28,000
噢 不管怎样 您真是太宽容了
{\fs11}Well, lots of mercy, anyhow.{\r}

1520
01:30:30,000 --> 01:30:31,040
我一直都这么说...
{\fs11}What I always say--{\r}

1521
01:30:31,250 --> 01:30:34,050
我不知道在下一场比赛开始前 还有没有时间可以下注
{\fs11}I don't know whether there's time before the next race to place a bet.{\r}

1522
01:30:34,260 --> 01:30:36,470
- 走吧 亲爱的 - 我可不那么认为
{\fs11}- But come, my dear. MRS. HIGGINS: I don't suppose so.{\r}

1523
01:30:36,680 --> 01:30:38,010
我在7号下了注
{\fs11}I have a bet on Number 7.{\r}

1524
01:30:38,220 --> 01:30:40,010
要是您也会选它的话我会很高兴的
{\fs11}I should be so happy if you would take it.{\r}

1525
01:30:40,220 --> 01:30:42,600
这样您就会更加喜欢这场比赛
{\fs11}You'II enjoy the race ever so much more.{\r}

1526
01:30:42,810 --> 01:30:43,890
你真是太好了
{\fs11}That's very kind of you.{\r}

1527
01:30:44,100 --> 01:30:46,730
- 他的名字叫多弗 - 走吧 亲爱的
{\fs11}- His name is Dover. PICKERING: Come along, my dear.{\r}

1528
01:30:50,310 --> 01:30:53,980
