{\fs11}ALL [SINGING]: There they are again Lining up to run{\r}

1529
01:30:54,190 --> 01:30:57,740
<i>他们紧握缰绳 做好了比赛的准备</i>
{\fs11}Now they're holding steady They are ready for it{\r}

1530
01:30:57,950 --> 01:31:02,950
<i>看呐 比赛开始了</i>
{\fs11}Look, it has begun{\r}

1531
01:31:03,160 --> 01:31:05,040
[万马奔腾]
{\fs11}[HORSES GALLOPING]{\r}

1532
01:31:07,670 --> 01:31:08,710
加油
{\fs11}Come on.{\r}

1533
01:31:08,920 --> 01:31:11,380
加油啊 多弗 加油
{\fs11}Come on, Dover. Come on.{\r}

1534
01:31:11,590 --> 01:31:13,420
加油 多弗
{\fs11}Come on, Dover.{\r}

1535
01:31:13,630 --> 01:31:15,300
加油
{\fs11}Come on.{\r}

1536
01:31:18,800 --> 01:31:20,590
加油 多弗！
{\fs11}[IN COCKNEY ACCENT] Come on, Dover!{\r}

1537
01:31:20,800 --> 01:31:23,010
把你漂亮的屁股抬高点儿！
{\fs11}Move your blooming ass!{\r}

1538
01:31:24,020 --> 01:31:25,770
[所有人在笑]
{\fs11}[ALL MURMURING]{\r}

1539
01:31:25,980 --> 01:31:28,850
男：别慌 亲爱的 是啊
{\fs11}MAN: Don't upset yourself, my dear. WOMAN: Please.{\r}

1540
01:31:29,520 --> 01:31:31,310
噢 我的天
{\fs11}Oh, my dear.{\r}

1541
01:31:45,950 --> 01:31:47,250
你不是认真的吧 亨利
{\fs11}You're not serious, Henry.{\r}

1542
01:31:47,460 --> 01:31:49,580
你不会带算带她出席大使招待舞会吧？
{\fs11}You don't expect to take her to the Embassy Ball?{\r}

1543
01:31:49,790 --> 01:31:51,250
你不认为她已经准备好了吗？
{\fs11}Don't you think she's ready for it?{\r}

1544
01:31:51,460 --> 01:31:53,750
亲爱的 亨利 她那样子只配上货船
{\fs11}Dear, Henry, she's ready for a canal barge.{\r}

1545
01:31:53,960 --> 01:31:56,050
嗯 她的语言也许还需要再加强一下 不过...
{\fs11}Well, her language may need a little refining, but--{\r}

1546
01:31:56,260 --> 01:31:57,300
噢 我说真的 亨利
{\fs11}Oh, really, Henry.{\r}

1547
01:31:57,510 --> 01:31:59,760
要是你不清楚这整个计划有多么的不可能
{\fs11}lf you cannot see how impossible this whole project is,{\r}

1548
01:31:59,970 --> 01:32:01,720
那你绝对是在拿她耍孩子气
{\fs11}then you must be absolutely potty about her.{\r}

1549
01:32:01,930 --> 01:32:05,060
我建议你放弃 不要再让你自己还有这个女孩儿继续下去了
{\fs11}I advise you to give it up and not put yourself and this girl through more.{\r}

1550
01:32:05,260 --> 01:32:08,020
放弃？这是我所经历过的最为使人着迷的冒险
{\fs11}Give it up? It's the most fascinating venture I've ever undertaken.{\r}

1551
01:32:08,230 --> 01:32:11,310
皮克林和我从早忙到晚都为了它 里边倾注着我们的心血
{\fs11}Pickering and I are at it from morning till night. lt fills our whole lives.{\r}

1552
01:32:11,520 --> 01:32:14,900
教伊莉莎 同伊莉莎说话 听伊莉莎说话 打扮伊莉莎
{\fs11}Teaching Eliza, talking to Eliza, listening to Eliza, dressing Eliza.{\r}

1553
01:32:15,110 --> 01:32:16,530
什么？
{\fs11}What?{\r}

1554
01:32:16,730 --> 01:32:20,200
你们就像两个孩子在玩着你们活的玩偶
{\fs11}You're a pretty pair of babies playing with your live doll.{\r}

1555
01:32:20,400 --> 01:32:22,070
车来了
{\fs11}Here's the car.{\r}

1556
01:33:30,430 --> 01:33:32,430
弗雷迪：我说 先生...
{\fs11}FREDDY: I say, sir...{\r}

1557
01:33:42,900 --> 01:33:43,950
晚上好 先生
{\fs11}Good evening, sir.{\r}

1558
01:33:44,160 --> 01:33:45,240
晚餐准备好了吗？我饿坏了
{\fs11}Dinner ready? I'm famished.{\r}

1559
01:33:45,450 --> 01:33:46,570
马上为您准备 先生
{\fs11}lmmediately, sir.{\r}

1560
01:33:46,780 --> 01:33:49,450
皮尔斯：晚上好 希金斯教授
{\fs11}PEARCE: Good evening, Professor Higgins.{\r}

1561
01:34:06,550 --> 01:34:11,100
<i>当她说起 她的姑妈怎样咬断了勺子</i>
{\fs11}[SINGING] When she mentioned How her aunt bit off the spoon{\r}

1562
01:34:11,310 --> 01:34:15,020
<i>她完全把我迷住了</i>
{\fs11}She completely done me in{\r}

1563
01:34:15,230 --> 01:34:19,110
<i>我的心已踏上 前往月球的旅程</i>
{\fs11}And my heart went on a journey To the moon{\r}

1564
01:34:19,320 --> 01:34:24,440
<i>当她讲到自己父亲 还有杜松子酒</i>
{\fs11}When she told about her father And the gin{\r}

1565
01:34:24,650 --> 01:34:29,160
<i>我从未见过 比这更为迷人的胡闹</i>
{\fs11}And I never saw A more enchanting farce{\r}

1566
01:34:29,370 --> 01:34:33,580
<i>当她叫喊着： “把你漂亮的...”</i>
{\fs11}Than the moment when she shouted: "Move your blooming--"{\r}

1567
01:34:34,870 --> 01:34:36,960
- 有什么事 先生？ - 杜利特小姐在吗？
{\fs11}- Yes, sir? - Is Miss Doolittle in?{\r}

1568
01:34:37,170 --> 01:34:39,920
- 我该怎么通报呢？ - 弗雷迪 埃恩斯福德-希尔
{\fs11}- Whom shall I say is calling? - Freddy Eynsford-Hill.{\r}

1569
01:34:40,130 --> 01:34:42,000
噢 要是她想不起我是谁
{\fs11}Oh, if she doesn't remember who I am,{\r}

1570
01:34:42,210 --> 01:34:45,170
就跟她说我就是那个对着她偷偷笑的人
{\fs11}tell her I'm the chap who was sniggering at her.{\r}

1571
01:34:45,380 --> 01:34:46,420
好的 先生
{\fs11}Yes, sir.{\r}

1572
01:34:46,630 --> 01:34:48,680
- 能帮我把这个交给她吗？ - 好的 先生
{\fs11}- And will you give her these? - Yes, sir.{\r}

1573
01:34:48,890 --> 01:34:50,010
您要进来吗？
{\fs11}Wouldn't you like to come in?{\r}

1574
01:34:50,220 --> 01:34:51,930
他们正在用晚餐 您可以先等一下
{\fs11}They're having dinner, but you may wait.{\r}

1575
01:34:52,140 --> 01:34:55,390
不 不用 谢谢 我就是来她住的这条街上喝一杯的
{\fs11}No. No, thank you. I want to drink in the street where she lives.{\r}

1576
01:34:55,600 --> 01:34:57,640
好的 先生
{\fs11}Yes, sir.{\r}

1577
01:35:04,150 --> 01:35:09,740
<i>我过去常在 这条街上散步</i>
{\fs11}I have often walked Down this street before{\r}

1578
01:35:09,950 --> 01:35:15,370
<i>过去脚下的人行道 总是那样的平稳</i>
{\fs11}But the pavement always stayed Beneath my feet before{\r}

1579
01:35:15,580 --> 01:35:21,000
<i>可忽然间 我弹起几层楼高</i>
{\fs11}AII at once am I Several stories high{\r}

1580
01:35:21,210 --> 01:35:26,920
<i>只因为知道这条街上 有你住着</i>
{\fs11}Knowing I'm on the street Where you live{\r}

1581
01:35:27,130 --> 01:35:32,680
<i>市中心里 有丁香树吗？</i>
{\fs11}Are there lilac trees ln the heart of town?{\r}

1582
01:35:32,890 --> 01:35:38,390
<i>在市里的任一个地方 你能听到百灵的鸣叫吗？</i>
{\fs11}Can you hear a lark ln any other part of town?{\r}

1583
01:35:38,600 --> 01:35:44,190
<i>有什么地方会从每道门里 都弥散出诱人的魔力吗？</i>
{\fs11}Does enchantment pour Out of every door?{\r}

1584
01:35:44,400 --> 01:35:50,070
<i>没有 只有有在这条 有你住的街上</i>
{\fs11}No, it's just on the street Where you live{\r}

1585
01:35:50,530 --> 01:35:55,620
<i>噢 这飘然的感觉</i>
{\fs11}And, oh, the towering feeling{\r}

1586
01:35:55,830 --> 01:36:01,960
<i>只因为知道你就在不远处</i>
{\fs11}Just to know somehow you are near{\r}

1587
01:36:02,170 --> 01:36:06,960
<i>那是种难以抗拒的感觉</i>
{\fs11}The overpowering feeling{\r}

1588
01:36:07,170 --> 01:36:13,180
<i>或许在下一秒 你就会出现在我眼前</i>
{\fs11}That any second You may suddenly appear{\r}

1589
01:36:13,390 --> 01:36:19,020
<i>即便人们停下看着我 也不会打扰到我</i>
{\fs11}People stop and stare They don't bother me{\r}

1590
01:36:19,230 --> 01:36:24,940
<i>因为在这个星球上除了这儿 别的地方 我都不愿意停留</i>
{\fs11}For there's nowhere else on earth That I would rather be{\r}

1591
01:36:25,150 --> 01:36:28,150
<i>任时光流逝</i>
{\fs11}Let the time go by{\r}

1592
01:36:28,360 --> 01:36:34,410
<i>我也不在乎 只要我能留在 </i>
{\fs11}I won't care if I can be here{\r}

1593
01:36:34,620 --> 01:36:40,660
<i>这条有你住的街上</i>
{\fs11}On the street where you live{\r}

1594
01:36:40,870 --> 01:36:42,120
皮尔斯：噢 先生
{\fs11}PEARCE: Oh, sir.{\r}

1595
01:36:45,250 --> 01:36:46,880
我很抱歉的转告您 先生
{\fs11}I'm terribly sorry, sir.{\r}

1596
01:36:47,090 --> 01:36:50,090
杜利特小姐说她不想见任何人 再也不想
{\fs11}Miss Doolittle says she doesn't want to see anyone ever again.{\r}

1597
01:36:50,300 --> 01:36:53,470
- 这是为什么？她真是叫人不敢相信 - 她就是这么对我说的 先生
{\fs11}- But why? She was unbelievable. - So I've been told, sir.{\r}

1598
01:36:53,680 --> 01:36:55,260
您还要我再转达什么吗？
{\fs11}ls there any further message?{\r}

1599
01:36:55,470 --> 01:36:57,510
好的 告诉她我会等她
{\fs11}Yes. Tell her that I'II wait.{\r}

1600
01:36:57,720 --> 01:37:00,100
噢 那可能要好几天 先生 甚至好几个星期
{\fs11}Oh, but it might be days, sir, even weeks.{\r}

1601
01:37:00,310 --> 01:37:03,480
你难道看不出来吗？我很乐意等
{\fs11}But don't you see? I'II be happier here.{\r}

1602
01:37:11,780 --> 01:37:17,280
<i>即便人们停下看着我 也不会打扰到我</i>
{\fs11}People stop and stare They don't bother me{\r}

1603
01:37:17,700 --> 01:37:23,370
<i>因为在这个星球上除了这儿 别的地方 我都不愿意停留</i>
{\fs11}For there's nowhere else on earth That I would rather be{\r}

1604
01:37:23,580 --> 01:37:26,710
<i>任时光流逝</i>
{\fs11}Let the time go by{\r}

1605
01:37:26,920 --> 01:37:34,010
<i>我也不在乎 只要我能留在</i>
{\fs11}I won't care if I can be here{\r}

1606
01:37:34,220 --> 01:37:42,060
<i>这条有你住的街上</i>
{\fs11}On the street where you live{\r}

1607
01:37:47,310 --> 01:37:50,020
说真的 希金斯 再这样继续下去是不人道的
{\fs11}lt really is, Higgins. lt's inhuman to continue.{\r}

1608
01:37:50,230 --> 01:37:52,860
你有意识到在6个星期的时间里 你还要教多少东西给这个可怜的姑娘吗？
{\fs11}You realize what you've got to teach this poor girl in six weeks?{\r}

1609
01:37:53,070 --> 01:37:54,450
你得教会她走路 说话
{\fs11}Teach her to walk, talk,{\r}

1610
01:37:54,660 --> 01:37:56,700
该怎样向公爵 勋爵 主教 大使表示问候
{\fs11}address a duke, a lord, a bishop, an ambassador.{\r}

1611
01:37:56,910 --> 01:37:58,870
这完全是不可能的
{\fs11}lt's absolutely impossible.{\r}

1612
01:37:59,080 --> 01:38:02,410
希金斯 我要告诉你 我决定取消这次的打赌
{\fs11}Higgins, I'm trying to tell you that I want to call off the bet.{\r}

1613
01:38:02,620 --> 01:38:04,830
我知道你是个固执的人 我也是
{\fs11}I know you're a stubborn man, but so am I.{\r}

1614
01:38:05,040 --> 01:38:06,710
这个试验结束了
{\fs11}This experiment is over.{\r}

1615
01:38:06,920 --> 01:38:09,130
除非国王下令
{\fs11}And nothing short of an order from the king{\r}

1616
01:38:09,340 --> 01:38:11,340
才能迫使我放弃
{\fs11}could force me to recant.{\r}

1617
01:38:11,550 --> 01:38:13,130
现在 如果你能原谅的话
{\fs11}Now, if you'II excuse me.{\r}

1618
01:38:13,340 --> 01:38:15,800
你明白吗 希金斯 打赌取消了
{\fs11}You understand, Higgins, it's over.{\r}

1619
01:38:16,010 --> 01:38:17,260
希金斯
{\fs11}Higgins.{\r}

1620
01:38:17,470 --> 01:38:20,050
希金斯 要是今晚在使馆里发生任何意外
{\fs11}Higgins, if there's any mishap at the embassy tonight,{\r}

1621
01:38:20,260 --> 01:38:22,720
要是让杜利特小姐陷入任何窘境
{\fs11}if Miss Doolittle suffers any embarrassment whatever,{\r}

1622
01:38:22,930 --> 01:38:24,140
这只能记在你的头上
{\fs11}it'II be on your head alone.{\r}

1623
01:38:24,350 --> 01:38:25,440
伊莉莎什么都可以做到
{\fs11}Eliza can do anything.{\r}

1624
01:38:25,640 --> 01:38:27,270
要是她被揭穿了呢？想想阿斯科特赛马会的事儿吧
{\fs11}Suppose she's discovered? Remember Ascot.{\r}

1625
01:38:27,480 --> 01:38:29,230
要是她又犯了别的什么可怕的错误呢？
{\fs11}Suppose she makes another ghastly mistake?{\r}

1626
01:38:29,440 --> 01:38:32,940
在舞会上可不会有马 皮克林
{\fs11}There will be no horses at the ball, Pickering.{\r}

1627
01:38:34,240 --> 01:38:36,240
想想看要是那样会有多可怕
{\fs11}PICKERING: Think how agonizing it would be.{\r}

1628
01:38:36,450 --> 01:38:39,200
噢 要是今晚真的发生什么 我自己也不知道该怎么办
{\fs11}Oh, if anything happened tonight, I don't know what I'd do.{\r}

1629
01:38:39,410 --> 01:38:40,910
你照样还可以回你的部队去
{\fs11}You could always rejoin your regiment.{\r}

1630
01:38:41,120 --> 01:38:42,740
这不是草率行事的时候 希金斯
{\fs11}This is no time for flippancy, Higgins.{\r}

1631
01:38:42,950 --> 01:38:44,910
6个星期来你训练这个女孩儿的方式
{\fs11}The way you've driven the girl the last six weeks{\r}

1632
01:38:45,120 --> 01:38:47,250
都相当的不体面
{\fs11}has exceeded all bounds of common decency.{\r}

1633
01:38:47,460 --> 01:38:49,040
看在上帝的面上 别踱来踱去了
{\fs11}For God's sake, stop pacing up and down.{\r}

1634
01:38:49,250 --> 01:38:50,340
你就不能找个地方坐下吗？
{\fs11}Can't you settle somewhere?{\r}

1635
01:38:50,540 --> 01:38:52,170
喝点儿淡酒 它能让你紧张的神经缓和下来
{\fs11}Have some port. lt'II quieten your nerves.{\r}

1636
01:38:52,380 --> 01:38:54,760
我可不紧张
{\fs11}I'm not nervous.{\r}

1637
01:38:55,300 --> 01:38:57,970
- 酒在哪儿？ - 就在钢琴上
{\fs11}- Where is it? - On the piano.{\r}

1638
01:38:59,090 --> 01:39:00,470
- 车来了 先生 - 噢 很好
{\fs11}- The car is here, sir. - Oh, good.{\r}

1639
01:39:00,680 --> 01:39:01,850
- 通知杜利特小姐 - 好的
{\fs11}- Tell Miss Doolittle. - Yes.{\r}

1640
01:39:02,060 --> 01:39:05,390
告诉杜利特小姐 我敢说那件该死的礼服根本不合适
{\fs11}Tell Miss Doolittle indeed. I bet you that damned gown doesn't fit.{\r}

1641
01:39:05,600 --> 01:39:07,810
我警告过你不要找那些法国设计师
{\fs11}I warned you about these French designers.{\r}

1642
01:39:08,020 --> 01:39:11,020
我们应该去找一家英国店铺 并不是所有人的眼光都和我们一样
{\fs11}We should've gone to an English shop, everyone would've been on our side.{\r}

1643
01:39:11,230 --> 01:39:13,230
- 要来杯淡酒吗？ - 不 谢谢
{\fs11}- Have a glass of port? - No, thank you.{\r}

1644
01:39:20,030 --> 01:39:23,870
你就这么有把握这姑娘能记住你给她填进去的一切？
{\fs11}Are you so sure this girl will retain everything you've hammered into her?{\r}

1645
01:39:24,790 --> 01:39:26,500
嗯 我们等着看吧
{\fs11}Well, we shall see.{\r}

1646
01:39:26,710 --> 01:39:28,670
要是她记不住呢？
{\fs11}Suppose she doesn't?{\r}

1647
01:39:29,580 --> 01:39:31,130
那我就赌输了
{\fs11}I lose my bet.{\r}

1648
01:39:31,340 --> 01:39:33,380
希金斯 在这件事上我最受不了你
{\fs11}Higgins, there's one thing I can't stand about you,{\r}

1649
01:39:33,590 --> 01:39:35,000
那就是你太过自以为是
{\fs11}that's your confounded complacency.{\r}

1650
01:39:35,210 --> 01:39:37,090
尤其是在这种时候 如此危急关头
{\fs11}At a moment like this, with so much at stake,{\r}

1651
01:39:37,300 --> 01:39:40,390
这太不礼貌了 你竟然拒绝来一杯淡酒
{\fs11}it's utterly indecent that you don't need a glass of port.{\r}

1652
01:39:42,300 --> 01:39:45,720
那姑娘怎么养了？从你的行为看好像她完全不重要
{\fs11}And what about the girl? You act as though she doesn't matter at all.{\r}

1653
01:39:46,180 --> 01:39:48,980
噢 胡说 皮克林 她当然重要
{\fs11}Oh, rubbish, Pickering. Of course she matters.{\r}

1654
01:39:49,190 --> 01:39:51,480
你以为这几个月我都在忙什么？
{\fs11}What do you think I've been doing all these months?{\r}

1655
01:39:51,690 --> 01:39:54,980
还有什么事情比得上将一个人
{\fs11}What could possibly matter more than to take a human being{\r}

1656
01:39:55,190 --> 01:39:56,900
通过改变她说话的声音
{\fs11}and change her into a different human being{\r}

1657
01:39:57,110 --> 01:39:59,360
将她变成一个完全不同的人更重要的？
{\fs11}by creating a new speech for her?{\r}

1658
01:39:59,570 --> 01:40:00,820
它将阶级与阶级之间还有灵魂与灵魂之间
{\fs11}lt's filling up the deepest gap{\r}

1659
01:40:01,030 --> 01:40:05,490
这道最深的鸿沟填补了起来
{\fs11}that separates class from class and soul from soul.{\r}

1660
01:40:05,700 --> 01:40:08,660
噢 她是如此重要
{\fs11}No, she matters immensely.{\r}

1661
01:40:08,870 --> 01:40:12,250
[脚步声]
{\fs11}[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]{\r}

1662
01:40:30,230 --> 01:40:32,690
杜利特小姐 你看起来真漂亮
{\fs11}Miss Doolittle, you look beautiful.{\r}

1663
01:40:32,900 --> 01:40:34,940
谢谢 皮克林上校
{\fs11}[WITHOUT COCKNEY ACCENT] Thank you, Colonel Pickering.{\r}

1664
01:40:35,150 --> 01:40:37,780
你不认为很漂亮吗 希金斯？
{\fs11}Don't you think so, Higgins?{\r}

1665
01:40:39,740 --> 01:40:43,530
不错 确实不错
{\fs11}Not bad. Not bad at all.{\r}

1666
01:41:35,670 --> 01:43:09,520
幕间休息（1MIN AND 30SECONDS）

1667
01:43:16,270 --> 01:43:19,230
男仆：休 德维尔夫妇
{\fs11}BUTLER: Mr. and Mrs. Hugh Deuvile.{\r}

1668
01:43:21,730 --> 01:43:25,940
名副其实的尊贵客人 詹姆士 克劳伦斯少将
{\fs11}Major General the right honorable Sir James Clarence.{\r}

1669
01:43:26,990 --> 01:43:29,950
格伦林侯爵夫妇
{\fs11}Marquis and Marquise of Glenning.{\r}

1670
01:43:31,280 --> 01:43:34,790
苏珊娜 德 隆利夫人
{\fs11}Lady Suzanna De Longly.{\r}

1671
01:43:35,910 --> 01:43:38,370
阿尔伯特爵士与德林夫人
{\fs11}Sir Albert and Lady Derring.{\r}

1672
01:43:39,000 --> 01:43:42,290
尊贵的阿奇博尔德爵士及凯瑟琳 赫琳夫人
{\fs11}Honorable Mr. Archibald and Lady Catherine Herring.{\r}

1673
01:43:42,500 --> 01:43:44,750
大师 大师
{\fs11}Maestro. Maestro.{\r}

1674
01:43:47,130 --> 01:43:50,050
- 您不记得我了吗？ - 不记得 你是谁啊？
{\fs11}- Don't you remember me? - No. Who the devil are you?{\r}

1675
01:43:50,260 --> 01:43:51,260
我是您的学生
{\fs11}I'm your pupil.{\r}

1676
01:43:51,470 --> 01:43:53,390
您的第一位 也是您最伟大的 最出色的学生
{\fs11}Your first, your greatest, your best pupil.{\r}

1677
01:43:53,600 --> 01:43:56,060
我是佐尔腾 卡帕西 那个天才儿童
{\fs11}I'm Zoltan Karpathy, that marvelous boy.{\r}

1678
01:43:56,270 --> 01:43:57,480
噢
{\fs11}Oh.{\r}

1679
01:43:57,680 --> 01:43:59,560
是我让您的名字传遍了整个欧洲
{\fs11}I made your name famous throughout Europe.{\r}

1680
01:43:59,770 --> 01:44:01,560
是您教我语音学的 您不可能把我忘了
{\fs11}You teach me phonetics, you cannot forget me.{\r}

1681
01:44:01,770 --> 01:44:03,520
你怎么不把你的头发剪短点儿？
{\fs11}Why don't you have your hair cut?{\r}

1682
01:44:03,730 --> 01:44:05,320
我可没有您那样仪表堂堂的外貌
{\fs11}I don't have your imposing appearance,{\r}

1683
01:44:05,530 --> 01:44:06,570
您那身材 还有面貌
{\fs11}your figure, your brow.{\r}

1684
01:44:06,780 --> 01:44:08,740
要是我把头发剪短了 就没人会注意我了
{\fs11}lf I had my hair cut, nobody would notice me.{\r}

1685
01:44:08,950 --> 01:44:10,660
你这些旧硬币是从哪弄来的
{\fs11}Where did you get all these old coins?{\r}

1686
01:44:10,860 --> 01:44:12,780
它们代表着各种语言
{\fs11}These are decorations for language.{\r}

1687
01:44:12,990 --> 01:44:14,870
特兰西瓦尼亚的女王今晚将要出席
{\fs11}The queen of Transylvania is here this evening.{\r}

1688
01:44:15,080 --> 01:44:18,080
出席这样的官方国际性的聚会 她可少不了我
{\fs11}I'm indispensable to her at these official international parties.{\r}

1689
01:44:18,290 --> 01:44:20,920
我会说32种语言 在欧洲的每个贵族我都认识
{\fs11}I speak 32 languages, I know everyone in Europe.{\r}

1690
01:44:21,120 --> 01:44:23,170
没有哪个冒牌货可以逃出我的眼睛
{\fs11}No impostor can escape my detection.{\r}

1691
01:44:23,380 --> 01:44:25,920
卡帕西教授
{\fs11}Professor Karpathy.{\r}

1692
01:44:27,420 --> 01:44:29,590
这位是希腊大使
{\fs11}The Greek ambassador.{\r}

1693
01:44:29,800 --> 01:44:30,930
希腊是我的故乡
{\fs11}Greek my foot.{\r}

1694
01:44:31,130 --> 01:44:33,640
他装作一点儿不会英语 可他骗不了我
{\fs11}He pretends not to know any English, but he cannot deceive me.{\r}

1695
01:44:33,850 --> 01:44:35,810
他是约克郡一个钟表匠的儿子
{\fs11}He's the son of a Yorkshire watchmaker.{\r}

1696
01:44:36,010 --> 01:44:37,060
[希金斯在笑]
{\fs11}[HIGGINS LAUGHS]{\r}

1697
01:44:37,270 --> 01:44:38,980
即便他故意将英语说得如此拙劣
{\fs11}He speaks English so villainously{\r}

1698
01:44:39,180 --> 01:44:42,650
他只要说出一个词儿就会暴露他的底细
{\fs11}that he cannot utter a word without betraying his origin.{\r}

1699
01:44:42,850 --> 01:44:45,150
我不会揭穿他 不过我要好好敲他一笔
{\fs11}I help him pretend, but I make him pay through the nose.{\r}

1700
01:44:45,360 --> 01:44:46,400
我要让那些冒牌货全都付出代价
{\fs11}I make them all pay.{\r}

1701
01:44:46,610 --> 01:44:48,190
抱歉 先生 有人请您上楼一趟
{\fs11}Excuse me, sir, you are wanted upstairs.{\r}

1702
01:44:48,400 --> 01:44:51,030
- 女王陛下要你过去 - 噢 失陪
{\fs11}- Her Excellency asked for you. - Oh, excuse me.{\r}

1703
01:45:09,800 --> 01:45:11,670
男仆：萨克森子爵夫妇
{\fs11}BUTLER: Viscount and Viscountess Saxon.{\r}

1704
01:45:15,050 --> 01:45:18,510
约克郡男爵夫妇
{\fs11}Baron and Baroness of Yorkshire.{\r}

1705
01:45:19,640 --> 01:45:23,140
盖伊爵士和斯科特 奥克兰夫人
{\fs11}Sir Guy and Lady Skot Ackland.{\r}

1706
01:45:42,250 --> 01:45:45,040
德梅鲁伯爵夫妇
{\fs11}The Count and Countess Demerau.{\r}

1707
01:45:45,250 --> 01:45:47,790
希尔雅德子爵夫妇
{\fs11}The Viscount and Viscountess Hillyard.{\r}

1708
01:45:48,000 --> 01:45:50,840
理查德 兰瑟爵士夫妇
{\fs11}Mr. and Mrs. Richard Lanser.{\r}

1709
01:45:51,380 --> 01:45:54,050
克兰德斯勋爵夫妇
{\fs11}Lord and Lady Clanders.{\r}

1710
01:45:55,700 --> 01:45:58,070
伊莉莎杜利特小姐 皮克林上校
{\fs11}Miss Eliza Doolittle, Colonel Pickering.{\r}

1711
01:45:58,210 --> 01:46:01,490
伊莉莎杜利特小姐 皮克林上校
{\fs11}Miss Eliza Doolittle, Colonel Pickering.{\r}

1712
01:46:01,730 --> 01:46:04,100
- 希金斯教授 - 晚上好 杜利特小姐
{\fs11}- Professor Higgins. - Good evening, Miss Doolittle.{\r}

1713
01:46:04,310 --> 01:46:05,350
女王陛下
{\fs11}Your Excellency.{\r}

1714
01:46:05,560 --> 01:46:07,690
- 杜利特小姐 - 您好吗？
{\fs11}- Miss Doolittle. - How do you do?{\r}

1715
01:46:07,900 --> 01:46:10,320
- 晚上好 上校 - 晚上好
{\fs11}- Good evening, colonel. - Good evening.{\r}

1716
01:46:10,530 --> 01:46:11,650
- 噢 上校 - 什么事？
{\fs11}- Oh, colonel. - What?{\r}

1717
01:46:11,860 --> 01:46:14,320
女士：今晚您身边的这位年轻女士可真迷人
{\fs11}LADY: What an enchanting young lady you have with you this evening.{\r}

1718
01:46:14,530 --> 01:46:16,110
- 谢谢 - 噢 她是谁？
{\fs11}PICKERING: Thank you. - Well, who is she?{\r}

1719
01:46:16,320 --> 01:46:20,620
噢 这是我同希金斯的一位表妹 抱歉
{\fs11}Oh, a cousin of mine. And Higgins. Excuse me.{\r}

1720
01:46:20,830 --> 01:46:21,990
希金斯教授
{\fs11}Professor Higgins.{\r}

1721
01:46:22,200 --> 01:46:26,500
远远地看一眼 她就如同生在花园中的花一样
{\fs11}Such a faraway look as if she's always lived in a garden.{\r}

1722
01:46:26,710 --> 01:46:29,880
说的没错 确实跟花园差不多
{\fs11}So she has, a sort of garden.{\r}

1723
01:46:35,930 --> 01:46:37,970
[聊天的声音]
{\fs11}[CHATTERING]{\r}

1724
01:46:46,310 --> 01:46:48,230
女1：那是她儿子吗？
{\fs11}WOMAN 1 : ls that her son?{\r}

1725
01:46:50,900 --> 01:46:52,900
女2：我可不相信...
{\fs11}WOMAN 2: I don't believe in...{\r}

1726
01:46:53,110 --> 01:46:55,110
女3：我要不行了
{\fs11}WOMAN 3: I shall die.{\r}

1727
01:46:55,320 --> 01:46:57,070
[几乎听不见的讲话声]
{\fs11}[SPEAKING INAUDIBLY]{\r}

1728
01:46:57,820 --> 01:47:01,080
亨利 必须马上带伊莉莎回去 这里有位语言专家
{\fs11}Henry must take Eliza home at once. There's a language expert here.{\r}

1729
01:47:01,280 --> 01:47:03,410
那种 你知道的 鉴伪专家
{\fs11}Sort of, you know, sort of impostorologist.{\r}

1730
01:47:03,620 --> 01:47:05,200
麻烦你再说一遍
{\fs11}I beg your pardon.{\r}

1731
01:47:05,410 --> 01:47:07,540
同皮克林上校一起的那位年轻女士
{\fs11}The young lady with Colonel Pickering.{\r}

1732
01:47:07,750 --> 01:47:09,670
去问问她是谁
{\fs11}Find out who she is.{\r}

1733
01:47:09,880 --> 01:47:11,130
遵命
{\fs11}With pleasure.{\r}

1734
01:47:11,340 --> 01:47:13,800
现在情况非常危险
{\fs11}The whole situation is highly explosive.{\r}

1735
01:47:16,510 --> 01:47:19,180
女1：我们只听最有权威的
{\fs11}WOMAN 1 : We heard on the best authority.{\r}

1736
01:47:19,800 --> 01:47:22,140
佐尔腾 再告诉我更多关于希腊大使的事
{\fs11}Tell me, Zoltan, some more about the Greek ambassador.{\r}

1737
01:47:22,350 --> 01:47:25,720
我很乐意 不过首先我想请你将我介绍给这位光彩照人的女士
{\fs11}Gladly, but first I would love you to present me to this glorious creature.{\r}

1738
01:47:25,930 --> 01:47:28,600
他真的是从约克郡来的吗？
{\fs11}Does he really come from Yorkshire?{\r}

1739
01:47:28,810 --> 01:47:32,440
[喇叭声]
{\fs11}[HORNS PLAYING]{\r}

1740
01:47:37,150 --> 01:47:40,070
男仆：尊贵的 特兰西瓦尼亚女王陛下
{\fs11}BUTLER: Her Majesty, the queen of Transylvania{\r}

1741
01:47:40,280 --> 01:47:44,240
同格雷戈尔王子殿下
{\fs11}and his Royal Highness, Prince Gregor.{\r}

1742
01:47:44,740 --> 01:47:47,790
[乐队演奏]
{\fs11}[BAND PLAYING]{\r}

1743
01:48:29,620 --> 01:48:32,830
很迷人 太迷人了
{\fs11}Charming. Quite charming.{\r}

1744
01:48:33,290 --> 01:48:35,500
这位是杜利特小姐 夫人
{\fs11}Miss Doolittle, ma'am.{\r}

1745
01:48:59,360 --> 01:49:01,150
男：真是个迷人的女孩儿
{\fs11}MAN: Such a charming girl.{\r}

1746
01:49:01,360 --> 01:49:04,490
女1：从她说话的时候我们就知道了
{\fs11}WOMAN 1 : We'II know when we hear her announced.{\r}

1747
01:49:04,700 --> 01:49:06,950
女2：看那身漂亮的舞会礼服
{\fs11}WOMAN 2: That's a beautiful ball gown.{\r}

1748
