02:00:17,750 --> 02:00:20,500
那样就够了吗 我想 我已经不再重要了
{\fs11}That's enough for you. I don't matter, I suppose.{\r}

1877
02:00:21,210 --> 02:00:24,090
你替我赢了赌？你这放肆的小人
{\fs11}You won my bet? You presumptuous insect.{\r}

1878
02:00:24,300 --> 02:00:26,630
是我自己赢的 你为什么朝我扔拖鞋？
{\fs11}I won it. What did you throw those slippers at me for?{\r}

1879
02:00:26,840 --> 02:00:29,800
因为我想砸烂你的脸 我要杀了你 你这个自私的畜牲
{\fs11}Because I wanted to smash your face. I could kill you, you selfish brute.{\r}

1880
02:00:30,010 --> 02:00:32,470
为什么你不把我丢回捡到我的那个贫民区去呢？
{\fs11}Why didn't you leave me where you picked me up in the gutter?{\r}

1881
02:00:32,680 --> 02:00:35,720
你该感谢这一切都结束了 你现在可以把我丢回那个地方了
{\fs11}You thank God it's all over now, you can throw me back again there.{\r}

1882
02:00:36,180 --> 02:00:38,890
噢 看看这个人发什么神经
{\fs11}Oh, so the creature's nervous after all.{\r}

1883
02:00:39,480 --> 02:00:41,390
[伊莉莎尖叫]
{\fs11}[ELIZA SCREAMING]{\r}

1884
02:00:42,400 --> 02:00:44,610
把你的爪子收起来 你这只猫 你怎么能朝着我挥爪子
{\fs11}Claws in, you cat. How dare you show your temper to me.{\r}

1885
02:00:44,820 --> 02:00:45,900
安静点儿坐下
{\fs11}Sit down and be quiet.{\r}

1886
02:00:46,110 --> 02:00:51,320
噢 我今后要怎么办？我今后要怎么办？
{\fs11}Oh, what's to become of me? What's to become of me?{\r}

1887
02:00:52,570 --> 02:00:55,530
我怎么知道你今后怎么样？这跟我有关系吗？
{\fs11}How do I know what's to become of you? What does it matter?{\r}

1888
02:00:55,740 --> 02:00:59,500
你就不关心吗 我就知道你不会关心的 就算我死了你也不会关心的
{\fs11}You don't care. I know you don't care. You wouldn't care if I was dead.{\r}

1889
02:00:59,710 --> 02:01:02,870
我对你来说什么都不是 甚至连这双拖鞋都比不上
{\fs11}I'm nothing to you. Not as much as them slippers.{\r}

1890
02:01:03,080 --> 02:01:05,420
- 这双拖鞋 - 这双拖鞋
{\fs11}- Those slippers. - Those slippers.{\r}

1891
02:01:05,630 --> 02:01:08,420
我并不认为这有什么区别
{\fs11}I didn't think it meant any difference now.{\r}

1892
02:01:11,090 --> 02:01:13,970
为什么你突然变得这个样子？
{\fs11}Why have you suddenly begun going on like this?{\r}

1893
02:01:14,180 --> 02:01:16,720
我能知道你这是在抱怨你在这里受到了虐待吗？
{\fs11}May I ask if you complain of your treatment here?{\r}

1894
02:01:16,930 --> 02:01:17,970
不是
{\fs11}No.{\r}

1895
02:01:18,180 --> 02:01:20,930
有人对你不好了？皮克林上校 皮尔斯太太？
{\fs11}Has anybody behaved badly? Colonel Pickering, Mrs. Pearce?{\r}

1896
02:01:21,140 --> 02:01:22,270
不是
{\fs11}No.{\r}

1897
02:01:22,480 --> 02:01:26,150
嗯 你不是在说我有对你不好吧？
{\fs11}Well, you don't pretend that I have treated you badly?{\r}

1898
02:01:26,570 --> 02:01:30,190
- 不是 - 不是 我很高兴听到你那么说
{\fs11}- No. - No. I'm glad to hear that.{\r}

1899
02:01:30,400 --> 02:01:33,740
也许经过紧张的一天你已经累了
{\fs11}Perhaps you're tired after the strain of the day.{\r}

1900
02:01:33,950 --> 02:01:36,530
你要来块巧克力吗？
{\fs11}Would you have a chocolate?{\r}

1901
02:01:36,740 --> 02:01:38,410
不要！
{\fs11}No!{\r}

1902
02:01:38,620 --> 02:01:39,700
谢谢
{\fs11}Thank you.{\r}

1903
02:01:41,330 --> 02:01:43,670
嗯 你会感到焦虑是自然的
{\fs11}Well, it's only natural that you should be anxious,{\r}

1904
02:01:43,870 --> 02:01:45,210
不过现在都结束了
{\fs11}but it's all over now.{\r}

1905
02:01:45,420 --> 02:01:47,170
再没有什么好担心的了
{\fs11}Nothing more to worry about.{\r}

1906
02:01:47,380 --> 02:01:51,210
不 是你再没有什么好担心的了
{\fs11}No, nothing more for you to worry about.{\r}

1907
02:01:51,590 --> 02:01:54,720
噢 上帝啊 我真希望自己死了才好
{\fs11}Oh, God, I wish I was dead.{\r}

1908
02:01:54,930 --> 02:01:58,180
为什么？究竟是为什么？
{\fs11}Why? In heaven's name, why?{\r}

1909
02:01:58,390 --> 02:02:02,230
现在 听我说 伊莉莎 所有的这些气话纯粹是你个人主观的想法
{\fs11}Now, listen to me, Eliza. AII this irritation is purely subjective.{\r}

1910
02:02:02,440 --> 02:02:04,600
我听不明白 我太无知了
{\fs11}I don't understand. I'm too ignorant.{\r}

1911
02:02:04,810 --> 02:02:08,190
只不过是你自己的想象 你什么都没做错 没人会伤害你
{\fs11}lt's just imagination. Nothing's wrong. Nobody's hurting you.{\r}

1912
02:02:08,400 --> 02:02:11,780
现在 上床去好好睡一觉吧 轻轻哭一场 念念你的祈祷词吧
{\fs11}Now, you go to bed and sleep it off. Have a little cry and say your prayers{\r}

1913
02:02:11,990 --> 02:02:14,320
这样你就会觉得舒服多了
{\fs11}and you'II feel very much more comfortable.{\r}

1914
02:02:14,530 --> 02:02:18,120
我听到了你的祈祷词“感谢上帝一切都结束了”
{\fs11}I heard your prayers, "Thank God it's all over."{\r}

1915
02:02:18,330 --> 02:02:19,910
噢 难道你不想感谢上帝一切都结束了？
{\fs11}Well, don't you thank God it's all over{\r}

1916
02:02:20,120 --> 02:02:22,410
现在你自由了 你可以去做自己喜欢的事了
{\fs11}and how you're free and you can do what you like.{\r}

1917
02:02:22,620 --> 02:02:26,000
噢 我适合做什么？你认为我适合做什么？
{\fs11}Oh, what am I fit for? What have you left me fit for?{\r}

1918
02:02:26,460 --> 02:02:29,670
我能去哪儿？我能做什么？
{\fs11}Where am I to go? What am I to do?{\r}

1919
02:02:29,880 --> 02:02:32,840
我以后要怎么办？
{\fs11}And what's to become of me?{\r}

1920
02:02:33,050 --> 02:02:37,140
噢 你在为这些烦恼 是吗？
{\fs11}Oh, that's what's worrying you, is it?{\r}

1921
02:02:37,510 --> 02:02:39,300
噢 换做是我 我就不会为这些事烦恼
{\fs11}Oh, I wouldn't worry about that if I were you.{\r}

1922
02:02:39,510 --> 02:02:40,970
我确信你可以毫不困难
{\fs11}I'm sure you won't have any difficulty{\r}

1923
02:02:41,180 --> 02:02:43,640
就能让自己找个地方安顿下来
{\fs11}in settling yourself somewhere or other.{\r}

1924
02:02:46,690 --> 02:02:49,270
我一直都没意识到你终要离去
{\fs11}I didn't quite realize you were going away.{\r}

1925
02:02:50,440 --> 02:02:52,530
要知道 你可以结婚的
{\fs11}You might marry, you know.{\r}

1926
02:02:52,740 --> 02:02:54,360
你看 伊莉莎 并不是所有的男人们
{\fs11}You see, Eliza, all men are not confirmed old bachelors{\r}

1927
02:02:55,570 --> 02:02:56,650
都像我还有上校这样是坚持独身主义的
{\fs11}like me and the colonel.{\r}

1928
02:02:56,860 --> 02:03:00,240
大多数男人还是会选择结婚的 可怜的家伙们
{\fs11}Most men are the marrying sort, poor devils.{\r}

1929
02:03:00,450 --> 02:03:01,530
你长得这么好看
{\fs11}And you're not bad-looking.{\r}

1930
02:03:01,740 --> 02:03:04,160
有时候你看起来真的很漂亮
{\fs11}You're really quite a pleasure to look at sometimes.{\r}

1931
02:03:04,370 --> 02:03:07,420
噢 可不现在 当你哭泣的时候真是相当难看
{\fs11}Well, not now. When you've been crying you look like the very devil.{\r}

1932
02:03:07,630 --> 02:03:09,710
我的意思是说 当你一切正常的时候
{\fs11}But I mean when you're all right and quite yourself,{\r}

1933
02:03:09,920 --> 02:03:13,670
连我都忍不住要称赞你的迷人
{\fs11}you're what I would call attractive.{\r}

1934
02:03:14,050 --> 02:03:15,840
好了 上床去吧 好好睡一觉
{\fs11}Now, you go to bed, have a good night's rest,{\r}

1935
02:03:16,050 --> 02:03:17,630
等你起来的时候 再好好看看自己
{\fs11}then get up and have a look at yourself.{\r}

1936
02:03:17,840 --> 02:03:20,050
你就不会那么难过了
{\fs11}You won't feel so bad.{\r}

1937
02:03:24,770 --> 02:03:28,400
我敢说我母亲会替你找到一些很不错的人
{\fs11}I daresay my mother might find some fellow or other who'd do very well.{\r}

1938
02:03:28,600 --> 02:03:30,650
我们可不是在科芬园 <font color=#FF7F00>[科芬园 伦敦的一个蔬菜花卉市场]</font>
{\fs11}We were above that at Covent Garden.{\r}

1939
02:03:30,860 --> 02:03:32,270
你什么意思？
{\fs11}What do you mean?{\r}

1940
02:03:32,480 --> 02:03:35,610
我卖的是花 可不是自己
{\fs11}I sold flowers, I didn't sell myself.{\r}

1941
02:03:35,820 --> 02:03:39,110
现在 你已经把我变成了一位淑女 我再也不能出去卖东西了
{\fs11}Now, you've made a lady of me, I'm not fit to sell anything else.{\r}

1942
02:03:39,320 --> 02:03:41,530
哦 胡说 伊莉莎 不要将人与人之间的关系
{\fs11}Oh, tosh, Eliza, don't insult human relations{\r}

1943
02:03:41,740 --> 02:03:44,740
曲解为买卖关系来侮辱它
{\fs11}by dragging all that cant about buying and selling into it.{\r}

1944
02:03:44,950 --> 02:03:46,790
要是你不愿意的话 你也可以不用嫁人
{\fs11}You don't have to marry if you don't want to.{\r}

1945
02:03:47,000 --> 02:03:50,460
- 那我还能做什么？ - 噢 还有好多事情
{\fs11}- What else am I to do? - Well, there are lots of things.{\r}

1946
02:03:50,670 --> 02:03:53,000
比如你原来想去的那家花店?
{\fs11}What about the old idea of a florist shop?{\r}

1947
02:03:53,210 --> 02:03:56,130
皮克林会替你安排一家 他相当富有
{\fs11}Pickering would set you up in one. He's got lots of money.{\r}

1948
02:03:56,340 --> 02:03:58,430
今晚你所穿的衣服全都是他付的钱
{\fs11}He paid for all those togs you're wearing tonight.{\r}

1949
02:03:58,630 --> 02:04:02,470
而租这些首饰至少要花上200镑
{\fs11}And that with the hire of the jewelry will make a big hole in 200 pounds.{\r}

1950
02:04:02,680 --> 02:04:05,180
噢 振作点儿 你会没事的
{\fs11}Oh, come on now. You'II be all right.{\r}

1951
02:04:06,180 --> 02:04:09,690
噢 我必须去睡觉了 我简直困得要死
{\fs11}Well, I must be off to bed. I'm really devilish sleepy.{\r}

1952
02:04:10,730 --> 02:04:12,730
我刚才好像要找什么东西 对吗？
{\fs11}I was looking for something. What was it?{\r}

1953
02:04:12,940 --> 02:04:14,070
你的拖鞋
{\fs11}Your slippers.{\r}

1954
02:04:14,820 --> 02:04:18,490
噢 是的 没错 你把它们扔给我了
{\fs11}Oh, yes, of course. You shied them at me.{\r}

1955
02:04:18,700 --> 02:04:22,870
- 在你临睡前 先生 - 嗯？
{\fs11}- Before you go, sir, - Hm?{\r}

1956
02:04:24,700 --> 02:04:27,910
我穿的衣服是属于我还是皮克林上校？
{\fs11}do my clothes belong to me or to Colonel Pickering?{\r}

1957
02:04:29,040 --> 02:04:30,870
皮克林把它们拿去有什么用？
{\fs11}What the devil use would they be to Pickering?{\r}

1958
02:04:31,080 --> 02:04:32,790
这么晚了你问这个干什么？
{\fs11}Why do you bother about that in the night?{\r}

1959
02:04:33,000 --> 02:04:34,750
我想知道我是不是可以把它们带走
{\fs11}I want to know what I may take away with me.{\r}

1960
02:04:34,960 --> 02:04:36,840
我可不想被指控为盗窃
{\fs11}I don't wanna be accused of stealing.{\r}

1961
02:04:37,800 --> 02:04:39,920
盗窃？
{\fs11}Stealing?{\r}

1962
02:04:40,130 --> 02:04:43,220
你不该那么说的 伊莉莎 那让人觉得你想要什么
{\fs11}You shouldn't have said that, Eliza. That shows a want of feeling.{\r}

1963
02:04:43,430 --> 02:04:47,430
抱歉 我不过是个平凡无知的女孩儿 从我的角度看 我还是小心点好
{\fs11}I'm sorry. I'm a common ignorant girl. ln my station, I have to be careful.{\r}

1964
02:04:47,640 --> 02:04:50,640
在你这样的人和我这样的人之间是不可能有什么感情的
{\fs11}There can't be any feelings between the likes of you and the likes of me.{\r}

1965
02:04:50,850 --> 02:04:53,860
所以 你能告诉我哪些属于我而哪些不是吗？
{\fs11}Please, will you tell me what belongs to me and what doesn't?{\r}

1966
02:04:55,020 --> 02:04:57,440
你想要的话 这该死的一屋子的东西你都可以拿走
{\fs11}Take the whole damned houseful if you want.{\r}

1967
02:04:57,650 --> 02:04:59,990
除了那些首饰 它们是租来的 你满意了吗？
{\fs11}Except the jewelry, that's hired. Will that satisfy you?{\r}

1968
02:05:00,200 --> 02:05:01,450
先别走
{\fs11}Stop, please.{\r}

1969
02:05:03,910 --> 02:05:07,450
你能把这些拿到你的房间去好好保管吗？
{\fs11}Will you take these to your room and keep them safe?{\r}

1970
02:05:07,660 --> 02:05:10,040
我可不想万一把它们弄不见了
{\fs11}I don't want to run the risk of them being missed.{\r}

1971
02:05:12,170 --> 02:05:13,540
把它们给我吧
{\fs11}Hand them over.{\r}

1972
02:05:13,750 --> 02:05:15,540
要是这些都属于我而不是珠宝商
{\fs11}lf these belonged to me and not the jeweler,{\r}

1973
02:05:15,750 --> 02:05:18,460
我就要把它们都灌进你那不领情的喉咙里
{\fs11}I'd ram them down your ungrateful throat.{\r}

1974
02:05:18,670 --> 02:05:23,800
这个戒指不是珠宝商的 这是你在布莱顿给我买的
{\fs11}The ring isn't the jeweler's. lt's the one you bought me in Brighton.{\r}

1975
02:05:24,010 --> 02:05:26,180
现在我再也不想要它了
{\fs11}I don't want it now.{\r}

1976
02:05:28,850 --> 02:05:30,770
不要拿它打我！
{\fs11}Don't you hit me!{\r}

1977
02:05:30,980 --> 02:05:34,100
打你？你这个混蛋 你怎么可以这样说？
{\fs11}Hit you? You infamous creature, how dare you suggest such a thing.{\r}

1978
02:05:34,310 --> 02:05:36,940
是你在打我 是你伤到了我的心
{\fs11}lt's you who've hit me. You've wounded me to the heart.{\r}

1979
02:05:37,150 --> 02:05:41,240
我真高兴 不管怎样我总算讨回了一点
{\fs11}I'm glad. I've got a little of my own back anyhow.{\r}

1980
02:05:41,900 --> 02:05:43,280
你快要让我发火了
{\fs11}You've caused me to lose my temper,{\r}

1981
02:05:43,490 --> 02:05:45,280
我以前很少发火
{\fs11}a thing that's hardly happened to me before.{\r}

1982
02:05:45,490 --> 02:05:47,990
今晚我不想再继续说下去了 我要睡了
{\fs11}I don't wish to discuss it further tonight. I'm going to bed.{\r}

1983
02:05:48,200 --> 02:05:50,830
你还是自己去给皮尔斯太太留咖啡的字条吧
{\fs11}You better leave your own note for Mrs. Pearce about the coffee{\r}

1984
02:05:51,040 --> 02:05:52,580
因为这不该我做
{\fs11}for it won't be done by me.{\r}

1985
02:05:52,790 --> 02:05:57,380
该死的皮尔斯太太 该死的咖啡 还有该死的你
{\fs11}Damn Mrs. Pearce, damn the coffee and damn you.{\r}

1986
02:05:57,590 --> 02:05:59,210
我自己也该死 因为我愚蠢的
{\fs11}And damn my own folly for having lavished{\r}

1987
02:05:59,420 --> 02:06:02,050
将自己辛苦积攒的学识还有最宝贵的注意力和
{\fs11}my hard-earned knowledge and the treasure of my regard{\r}

1988
02:06:02,260 --> 02:06:06,090
善良都浪费在了一个无情的贫民区女孩儿身上
{\fs11}and intimacy on a heartless guttersnipe.{\r}

1989
02:06:06,300 --> 02:06:09,560
[留声机上播放的哼元音的声音]
{\fs11}[VOICE SPEAKING VOWELS PLAYING ON GRAMOPHONE]{\r}

1990
02:06:10,560 --> 02:06:12,140
[留声机停止播放]
{\fs11}[GRAMOPHONE STOPS]{\r}

1991
02:06:56,230 --> 02:07:01,360
<i>你等着吧 亨利 希金斯 你等着吧</i>
{\fs11}[SINGING] Just you wait, Henry Higgins Just you wait{\r}

1992
02:07:02,820 --> 02:07:07,280
<i>你会后悔的 可到那时就算你哭得一塌糊涂也太晚了</i>
{\fs11}You'II be sorry But your tears'II be too late{\r}

1993
02:07:09,070 --> 02:07:12,120
<i>你就是个失败者</i>
{\fs11}You will be the one it's done to{\r}

1994
02:07:12,750 --> 02:07:16,250
<i>你将再也没有可以拥抱的人</i>
{\fs11}And you'II have no one to run to{\r}

1995
02:07:16,670 --> 02:07:18,500
<i>你等着吧</i>
{\fs11}Just you wait{\r}

1996
02:07:46,780 --> 02:07:52,080
<i>我过去常在 这条街上散步</i>
{\fs11}[SINGING] I have often walked Down this street before{\r}

1997
02:07:52,580 --> 02:07:57,910
<i>过去脚下的人行道 总是那样的平稳</i>
{\fs11}But the pavement always stayed Beneath my feet before{\r}

1998
02:07:58,370 --> 02:08:04,000
<i>可忽然间 我弹起几层楼高</i>
{\fs11}AII at once am I Several stories high{\r}

1999
02:08:04,210 --> 02:08:09,970
<i>只因为知道这条街上 有你住着</i>
{\fs11}Knowing I'm on the street Where you live{\r}

2000
02:08:10,180 --> 02:08:15,810
<i>市中心里 有丁香树吗？</i>
{\fs11}Are there lilac tress ln the heart of town?{\r}

2001
02:08:16,020 --> 02:08:21,810
<i>在市里的任一个地方 你能听到百灵的鸣叫吗？</i>
{\fs11}Can you hear a lark ln any other part of town?{\r}

2002
02:08:22,020 --> 02:08:27,610
<i>有什么地方会从每道门里 都弥散出诱人的魔力吗？</i>
{\fs11}Does enchantment pour Out of every door?{\r}

2003
02:08:27,820 --> 02:08:33,830
<i>没有 只有有在这条 有你住的街上</i>
{\fs11}No, it's just on the street Where you live{\r}

2004
02:08:34,030 --> 02:08:39,410
<i>噢 这飘然的感觉</i>
{\fs11}And, oh, the towering feeling{\r}

2005
