{\fs11}Did either of you frighten her last night?{\r}

2271
02:25:28,130 --> 02:25:29,970
我们根本就没对她说过一个词儿 你当时也在场的
{\fs11}We hardly said a word to her. You were there.{\r}

2272
02:25:30,170 --> 02:25:31,630
你就没在我睡了之后去欺负她了？
{\fs11}Did you bully her after I went to bed?{\r}

2273
02:25:31,840 --> 02:25:33,890
完全相反 她朝我扔拖鞋
{\fs11}The other way around. She threw the slippers at me.{\r}

2274
02:25:34,100 --> 02:25:35,800
我根本一点儿都没惹她
{\fs11}I never gave her the slightest provocation.{\r}

2275
02:25:36,010 --> 02:25:38,430
我还没开口 拖鞋就 BANG 的一声砸在我头上了
{\fs11}The slippers came, bang, at my head before I uttered a word.{\r}

2276
02:25:38,640 --> 02:25:40,600
还说了很多最难听的话 我当时都惊了
{\fs11}Used the most disgraceful language. I was shocked.{\r}

2277
02:25:40,810 --> 02:25:42,440
- 噢 我给弄糊涂了 - 我也不能理解
{\fs11}- Well, I'm dashed. - I don't understand.{\r}

2278
02:25:42,650 --> 02:25:44,150
我们替她考虑得很周全啊
{\fs11}We've given her every consideration.{\r}

2279
02:25:44,360 --> 02:25:46,150
- 她自己也承认的 - 噢 我给弄糊涂了
{\fs11}- She admitted it herself. - Well, I'm dashed.{\r}

2280
02:25:46,360 --> 02:25:48,980
噢 皮克林 看在上帝的面上 别再装糊涂了赶紧做点儿什么
{\fs11}Oh, Pickering, for God's sake, stop being dashed and do something.{\r}

2281
02:25:49,190 --> 02:25:50,490
- 什么？ - 好吧 打电话给警察
{\fs11}- What? - Well, phone the police.{\r}

2282
02:25:50,700 --> 02:25:52,320
不然要他们来干什么？
{\fs11}What are they there for in heaven's name?{\r}

2283
02:25:52,530 --> 02:25:54,660
希金斯先生 你不能把伊莉莎的名字给警察
{\fs11}Mr. Higgins, you can't give Eliza's name to the police{\r}

2284
02:25:54,870 --> 02:25:56,870
就像她是个小偷或是丢掉的一把伞
{\fs11}as if she were a thief or a lost umbrella.{\r}

2285
02:25:57,080 --> 02:25:58,830
为什么不能？我要找回这女孩儿
{\fs11}But why not? I want to find the girl.{\r}

2286
02:25:59,040 --> 02:26:01,870
她是属于我的 我为她花了5镑
{\fs11}She belongs to me. I paid 5 pounds for her.{\r}

2287
02:26:02,080 --> 02:26:04,880
安静点好吗 喂 请接苏格兰场
{\fs11}Quite right. Hello. Scotland Yard, please.{\r}

2288
02:26:05,080 --> 02:26:06,540
能给我端点儿咖啡来吗？
{\fs11}Get me some coffee, would you please?{\r}

2289
02:26:06,750 --> 02:26:07,960
- 好的 先生 谁啊？
{\fs11}- Yes, sir. MAN: Who's there?{\r}

2290
02:26:08,170 --> 02:26:11,470
苏格兰场吗？噢 太好了 抱歉
{\fs11}Scotland Yard? Yes, of course. I beg your pardon, yes.{\r}

2291
02:26:11,670 --> 02:26:15,180
我是皮克林上校 休 皮克林
{\fs11}This is Colonel Pickering speaking. Hugh Pickering.{\r}

2292
02:26:15,390 --> 02:26:18,600
- 住温珀街27A号 <i>- 温珀街27A号</i>
{\fs11}- 27A Wimpole Street. - 27A Wimpole Street.{\r}

2293
02:26:18,810 --> 02:26:21,520
- 我想报一个人口失踪案 <i>- 性别？</i>
{\fs11}- I want to report a missing person. - Male or female?{\r}

2294
02:26:21,730 --> 02:26:25,190
是一位名叫伊莉莎 杜利特的小姐 是的 约21岁
{\fs11}A Miss Eliza Doolittle, yeah. About 21 .{\r}

2295
02:26:25,400 --> 02:26:27,440
<i>身高呢？</i>
{\fs11}And her height?{\r}

2296
02:26:27,650 --> 02:26:30,690
- 我想应该是5英尺7英寸<font color=#FF7F00>[皮克林为赫本做的衣服]</font> <i>- 眼睛颜色呢？</i>
{\fs11}- I should say about 5'7". - What color eyes?{\r}

2297
02:26:30,900 --> 02:26:34,990
她的眼睛？噢 让我想想 她的眼睛 她的眼睛是
{\fs11}Her eyes? Oh, let me think now. Her eyes, her eyes.{\r}

2298
02:26:35,200 --> 02:26:37,780
- 棕色的 - 棕色的 对
{\fs11}- Brown. - Brown, yeah.{\r}

2299
02:26:37,990 --> 02:26:40,870
不 不 不是 她的头发？
{\fs11}No, no, no. Her hair?{\r}

2300
02:26:41,080 --> 02:26:42,290
噢 老天 让我...
{\fs11}Oh, good Lord. Let me...{\r}

2301
02:26:42,500 --> 02:26:44,210
噢 是那种偏中性介于--
{\fs11}Well, sort of nondescript neutral sort of--{\r}

2302
02:26:44,420 --> 02:26:46,040
棕色 棕色 棕色的
{\fs11}Brown, brown, brown.{\r}

2303
02:26:46,250 --> 02:26:48,750
你听到他说的了吧？棕色 棕色 棕色的 是的
{\fs11}You heard what he said? Brown, brown, brown, yes.{\r}

2304
02:26:48,960 --> 02:26:50,340
不 不 不是 这是她的住处
{\fs11}No, no, no, this is her residence.{\r}

2305
02:26:50,550 --> 02:26:52,550
27A号--对
{\fs11}27A-- Yeah.{\r}

2306
02:26:52,760 --> 02:26:55,760
我想应该在今早3到4点
{\fs11}About between 3 and 4 this morning, I understand.{\r}

2307
02:26:55,970 --> 02:26:57,510
好的 不 不 没有
{\fs11}Yes. No, no, no.{\r}

2308
02:26:57,720 --> 02:26:59,510
亲--不 她没有任何亲人 没有
{\fs11}Rela-- No, she's no relation, no.{\r}

2309
02:26:59,720 --> 02:27:03,730
什么？嗯 只能说是她的一位好朋友吧 是吧？
{\fs11}What? Well, just let's call her a good friend, shall we?{\r}

2310
02:27:03,940 --> 02:27:05,310
你说什么？
{\fs11}I beg your pardon?{\r}

2311
02:27:05,520 --> 02:27:08,310
听着 伙计 我可不喜欢你问话的口气
{\fs11}Listen to me, my man, I don't like the tenor of that question.{\r}

2312
02:27:08,520 --> 02:27:11,780
这姑娘在我们这里做什么是我们自己的事情
{\fs11}What the girl does here is our affair.{\r}

2313
02:27:11,980 --> 02:27:15,900
你们的事情就是把她找回来 这样她就能回来接着做自己的事情了
{\fs11}Your affair is to get her back so that she can continue doing it.{\r}

2314
02:27:16,110 --> 02:27:17,820
噢 我真给弄糊涂了
{\fs11}Well, I'm dashed.{\r}

2315
02:27:20,160 --> 02:27:22,990
<i>这是为什么 天呐 会使得她出走？</i>
{\fs11}[SINGING] What, in all in heaven, Can have prompted her to go?{\r}

2316
02:27:23,200 --> 02:27:26,000
<i>在舞会上她取得这样大的成功</i>
{\fs11}After such a triumph at the ball?{\r}

2317
02:27:26,210 --> 02:27:28,790
<i>是什么使她如此不开心？ 是什么能让她如此不开心？</i>
{\fs11}What could have depressed her? What could have possessed her?{\r}

2318
02:27:29,000 --> 02:27:32,550
<i>我完全弄不明白 这个可怜的人</i>
{\fs11}I cannot understand The wretch at all{\r}

2319
02:27:34,010 --> 02:27:36,800
希金斯 我有个老同学在内政部
{\fs11}Higgins, I have an old school chum at the Home Office.{\r}

2320
02:27:37,010 --> 02:27:40,180
也许他能帮忙 我打算给他打个电话
{\fs11}Perhaps he can help. Think I'II give him a ring.{\r}

2321
02:27:40,390 --> 02:27:41,930
<i>请说接线号码</i>
{\fs11}WOMAN [ON PHONE]: Number, please.{\r}

2322
02:27:42,140 --> 02:27:44,310
请接白厅 72 44
{\fs11}Whitehall 72-double 4, please.{\r}

2323
02:27:44,520 --> 02:27:46,810
<i>白厅 72 44</i>
{\fs11}Whitehall 72-double 4.{\r}

2324
02:27:47,020 --> 02:27:49,520
<i>女人都没有理性 这就是为什么</i>
{\fs11}[SINGING] Women are irrational That's all there is to that{\r}

2325
02:27:49,730 --> 02:27:52,570
<i>她们脑袋里尽是棉花 稻草还有破布</i>
{\fs11}Their heads are full of cotton Hay and rags{\r}

2326
02:27:52,780 --> 02:27:55,690
<i>她们就知道发脾气 敏感 优柔寡断</i>
{\fs11}They're nothing but exasperating lrritating, vacillating{\r}

2327
02:27:55,900 --> 02:27:59,910
<i>喜欢算计 容易焦虑 令人发狂 就是个让人发火的巫婆</i>
{\fs11}Calculating, agitating, maddening And infuriating hags{\r}

2328
02:28:00,120 --> 02:28:01,200
男：<i>这里是内政部</i>
{\fs11}MAN: The Home Office here.{\r}

2329
02:28:01,410 --> 02:28:03,950
噢 我想找布鲁斯特 巴金先生
{\fs11}Oh, I want to speak to Mr. Brewster Budgin, please.{\r}

2330
02:28:04,160 --> 02:28:07,580
<i>- 您能稍等一下吗 先生？</i> - 布鲁...好的 我会等的
{\fs11}- Would you hold on, sir? - Brew-- Yes, I'II wait.{\r}

2331
02:28:12,040 --> 02:28:13,500
皮克林
{\fs11}Pickering,{\r}

2332
02:28:13,710 --> 02:28:16,630
为什么女人就不能更像男人点儿？
{\fs11}why can't a woman be more like a man?{\r}

2333
02:28:16,840 --> 02:28:18,300
能再说一遍吗？
{\fs11}I beg your pardon?{\r}

2334
02:28:18,510 --> 02:28:22,470
<i>好的 为什么女人 就不能更像男人点儿？</i>
{\fs11}[SINGING] Yes, why can't a woman Be more like a man?{\r}

2335
02:28:22,680 --> 02:28:25,600
<i>男人是如此坦率 如此开诚布公</i>
{\fs11}Men are so honest So thoroughly square{\r}

2336
02:28:25,810 --> 02:28:29,020
<i>永远那么高尚 那么公平</i>
{\fs11}Eternally noble, historically fair{\r}

2337
02:28:29,230 --> 02:28:32,310
<i>当你成功的时候 他会轻轻的拍拍你的后背</i>
{\fs11}Who, when you win Will always give your back a pat{\r}

2338
02:28:32,520 --> 02:28:35,900
<i>噢 为什么女人 就不能那样？</i>
{\fs11}Well, why can't a woman Be like that?{\r}

2339
02:28:36,360 --> 02:28:39,570
<i>为什么所有人 都学着别人那样？</i>
{\fs11}Why does everyone Do what the others do?{\r}

2340
02:28:39,780 --> 02:28:42,570
<i>女人就不会学着 动动自己的脑子？</i>
{\fs11}Can't a woman learn To use her head?{\r}

2341
02:28:43,240 --> 02:28:45,870
<i>为什么她们做的每件事 都跟她们母亲一样？</i>
{\fs11}Why do they do everything Their mothers do?{\r}

2342
02:28:46,080 --> 02:28:49,370
<i>为什么她们就不能长得 噢 像她们的父亲呢？</i>
{\fs11}Why don't they grow up Well, like their father instead?{\r}

2343
02:28:49,580 --> 02:28:52,580
<i>为什么女人不能 学学男人？</i>
{\fs11}Why can't a woman Take after a man?{\r}

2344
02:28:52,790 --> 02:28:55,920
<i>男人是如此随和 如此容易满足</i>
{\fs11}Men are so pleasant So easy to please{\r}

2345
02:28:56,130 --> 02:28:59,220
<i>跟他们在一起的任何时候 你总会觉得轻松</i>
{\fs11}Whenever you're with them You're always at ease{\r}

2346
02:28:59,430 --> 02:29:01,720
<i>要是我好几小时不说话 你会不会觉得受到轻视？</i>
{\fs11}Would you be slighted lf I didn't speak for hours?{\r}

2347
02:29:01,930 --> 02:29:02,970
当然不会
{\fs11}Of course not.{\r}

2348
02:29:03,180 --> 02:29:04,890
<i>要是我喝了一两杯 你会不会觉得生气？</i>
{\fs11}Would you be livid lf I had a drink or two?{\r}

2349
02:29:05,100 --> 02:29:06,140
废话
{\fs11}Nonsense.{\r}

2350
02:29:06,350 --> 02:29:08,310
<i>要是我从不给你送花儿 你会不会觉得受伤？</i>
{\fs11}Would you be wounded lf I never sent you flowers?{\r}

2351
02:29:08,520 --> 02:29:09,560
绝对不会
{\fs11}Never.{\r}

2352
02:29:09,770 --> 02:29:12,190
<i>噢 为什么女人不能 像你一样？</i>
{\fs11}Well, why can't a woman Be like you?{\r}

2353
02:29:13,230 --> 02:29:15,770
<i>100万个男人站在一起 也不过是有点儿嘈杂</i>
{\fs11}One man in a million May shout a bit{\r}

2354
02:29:16,570 --> 02:29:19,280
<i>当然 总会有人有那么些许的缺点</i>
{\fs11}Now and then There's one with slight defects{\r}

2355
02:29:19,990 --> 02:29:22,320
<i>有个人 也许 对他的坦率 你会有些怀疑</i>
{\fs11}One, perhaps, whose truthfulness You doubt a bit{\r}

2356
02:29:22,530 --> 02:29:26,280
<i>但大体而言 我们都是了不起的男人</i>
{\fs11}But by and large We are a marvelous sex{\r}

2357
02:29:26,490 --> 02:29:29,450
<i>为什么女人不能 学学男人？</i>
{\fs11}Why can't a woman Take after a man?{\r}

2358
02:29:29,660 --> 02:29:32,670
<i>因为他们是如此友善 温厚而和蔼</i>
{\fs11}Because men are so friendly Good-natured and kind{\r}

2359
02:29:32,880 --> 02:29:35,840
<i>你再也找不到 一位比他更好的伙伴</i>
{\fs11}A better companion You never will find{\r}

2360
02:29:36,380 --> 02:29:38,800
<i>要是我回家用晚餐晚了几小时 你会不会大喊大叫？</i>
{\fs11}lf I were hours late for dinner Would you bellow?{\r}

2361
02:29:39,010 --> 02:29:40,050
当然不会
{\fs11}Of course not.{\r}

2362
02:29:40,260 --> 02:29:42,220
<i>要是我忘记了你那愚蠢的生日 你会不会发火？</i>
{\fs11}lf I forgot your silly birthday Would you fuss?{\r}

2363
02:29:42,430 --> 02:29:43,470
废话
{\fs11}Nonsense.{\r}

2364
02:29:43,680 --> 02:29:45,600
<i>要是我同别人外出 你会不会抱怨？</i>
{\fs11}Would you complain lf I took out another fellow?{\r}

2365
02:29:45,810 --> 02:29:46,550
绝对不会
{\fs11}Never.{\r}

2366
02:29:46,760 --> 02:29:49,140
<i>噢 为什么女人不能 像我们一样?</i>
{\fs11}Well, why can't a woman Be like us?{\r}

2367
02:29:51,810 --> 02:29:53,690
噢 您好 布鲁斯特 巴金先生 在吗？
{\fs11}Oh, hello. Mr. Brewster Budgin there?{\r}

2368
02:29:53,900 --> 02:29:56,270
<i>- 是的 我就是巴金</i> - 布鲁兹
{\fs11}- Yes, Budgin here. - Bruzzie.{\r}

2369
02:29:56,480 --> 02:29:58,980
噢 布鲁兹 你绝对猜不到我是谁
{\fs11}Oh, Bruzzie, you'II never never guess who this is.{\r}

2370
02:29:59,190 --> 02:30:00,610
<i>噢 别傻了 是皮克林啊</i>
{\fs11}Oh, don't be silly. lt's Pickering.{\r}

2371
02:30:00,820 --> 02:30:02,740
说的太对了 没错 是我 天呐
{\fs11}You're quite right, yes, it is. Good heavens.{\r}

2372
02:30:02,950 --> 02:30:05,410
以圣乔治之名起誓 你记性真好
{\fs11}By George, what a memory.{\r}

2373
02:30:05,620 --> 02:30:07,120
你好吗 布鲁兹？
{\fs11}How are you, Bruzzie?{\r}

2374
02:30:07,330 --> 02:30:09,240
很高兴能听到你说话
{\fs11}Nice to hear your voice.{\r}

2375
02:30:09,450 --> 02:30:12,790
什么？噢 不会吧 真的已经有30年了？天呐
{\fs11}What? Oh, don't say that. ls it already 30 years? Good heavens.{\r}

2376
02:30:13,000 --> 02:30:14,870
你说的没错 是啊 真是沧海桑田啊
{\fs11}You're quite right. Yes, oceans of water.{\r}

2377
02:30:15,080 --> 02:30:16,880
听我说 布鲁兹 我给你打电话是有事要你帮忙
{\fs11}Listen, Bruzzie, I'II tell you why I rang up.{\r}

2378
02:30:17,090 --> 02:30:20,340
发生了一件不太愉快的事 我能同你见个面吗？
{\fs11}Something rather unpleasant's happened. Could I come and see you?{\r}

2379
02:30:20,550 --> 02:30:22,470
嗯 我会的 好的 就现在 马上来
{\fs11}Well, I could. Yes, now, straight away.{\r}

2380
02:30:22,680 --> 02:30:24,130
很 噢 好的 谢谢 谢谢
{\fs11}Right-o, good. Thank you, thank you.{\r}

2381
02:30:24,340 --> 02:30:26,590
再见 布鲁兹 非常感谢
{\fs11}Goodbye, Bruzzie. Thank you very much.{\r}

2382
02:30:33,480 --> 02:30:36,770
噢 皮尔斯太太 我要去趟内政部
{\fs11}Oh, Mrs. Pearce, I'm going along to the Home Office.{\r}

2383
02:30:36,980 --> 02:30:39,190
噢 我真希望您能找到他 皮克林上校
{\fs11}Oh, I do hope you find her, Colonel Pickering.{\r}

2384
02:30:39,400 --> 02:30:41,070
希金斯先生会想念她的
{\fs11}Mr. Higgins will miss her.{\r}

2385
02:30:41,280 --> 02:30:42,740
希金斯先生会想念她 嗯？
{\fs11}Mr. Higgins will miss her, eh?{\r}

2386
02:30:42,950 --> 02:30:46,160
去他的希金斯先生 是我会想念她
{\fs11}Blast Mr. Higgins. I'II miss her.{\r}

2387
02:30:47,580 --> 02:30:49,120
希金斯：皮克林？
{\fs11}HIGGINS: Pickering?{\r}

2388
02:30:51,250 --> 02:30:53,040
皮克林？
{\fs11}Pickering?{\r}

2389
02:30:56,960 --> 02:30:58,330
噢 皮尔斯太太？
{\fs11}Oh, Mrs. Pearce?{\r}

2390
02:30:58,540 --> 02:31:00,420
皮尔斯：- 什么事 先生？ - 上校去哪儿了？
{\fs11}PEARCE: Yes, sir? - Where's the colonel?{\r}

2391
02:31:00,630 --> 02:31:02,210
他去内政部了 先生
{\fs11}He's gone to the Home Office, sir.{\r}

2392
02:31:03,380 --> 02:31:04,840
噢 你在这儿
{\fs11}Oh, there you are.{\r}

2393
02:31:05,050 --> 02:31:10,180
我心里很乱而他出去找人帮忙 现在 这儿就有一位令人感到亲切的人
{\fs11}I'm disturbed and he runs for help. Now, there's a good fellow.{\r}

2394
02:31:10,560 --> 02:31:14,020
皮尔斯太太 你也是女人
{\fs11}Mrs. Pearce, you're a woman.{\r}

2395
02:31:14,230 --> 02:31:17,730
<i>为什么女人 就不能更像男人点儿？</i>
{\fs11}[SINGING] Why can't a woman Be more like a man?{\r}

2396
02:31:17,940 --> 02:31:20,980
<i>男人是如此正派 如此衣着得体</i>
{\fs11}Men are so decent Such regular chaps{\r}

2397
02:31:21,190 --> 02:31:24,190
<i>随时准备帮助你 度过任何灾难</i>
{\fs11}Ready to help you Through any mishaps{\r}

2398
02:31:24,400 --> 02:31:27,410
<i>随时准备帮助你 在你阴郁的时候重新振作</i>
{\fs11}Ready to buck you up Whenever you are glum{\r}

2399
02:31:27,620 --> 02:31:30,740
<i>为什么女人就不能同男人成为亲密的朋友？</i>
{\fs11}Why can't a woman be a chum?{\r}

2400
02:31:31,580 --> 02:31:34,160
<i>为什么思考这件事 有些女人永远都不会做？</i>
{\fs11}Why is thinking Something women never do?{\r}

2401
02:31:34,960 --> 02:31:37,710
<i>为什么她们从不试着去梳清条理？</i>
{\fs11}Why is logic never even tried?{\r}

2402
02:31:38,170 --> 02:31:41,000
<i>而梳理她们的头发 就是她们唯一做的事情</i>
{\fs11}Straightening up their hair Is all they ever do{\r}

2403
02:31:41,210 --> 02:31:44,550
<i>为什么她们就不能理清 她们脑子里的那团乱麻？</i>
{\fs11}Why don't they straighten up The mess that's inside?{\r}

2404
02:31:44,760 --> 02:31:47,550
<i>为什么女人 举止不能像个男人？</i>
{\fs11}Why can't a woman Behave like a man?{\r}

2405
02:31:48,050 --> 02:31:51,100
<i>如果我是个女人 我才不会参加什么舞会</i>
{\fs11}lf I was a woman Who'd been to a ball{\r}

2406
02:31:51,310 --> 02:31:54,350
<i>被所有人 赞为公主一般</i>
{\fs11}Been hailed as a princess By one and by all{\r}

2407
02:31:54,560 --> 02:31:57,520
<i>我就要激动的哭得 像个溢满水的浴缸？</i>
{\fs11}Would I start weeping Like a bathtub overflowing?{\r}

2408
02:31:57,730 --> 02:32:00,650
<i>或者换句话说 要是我的家就像一棵树的话？</i>
{\fs11}Or carry on As if my home were in a tree?{\r}

2409
02:32:00,860 --> 02:32:03,530
<i>我会匆忙跑掉 甚至都不跟自己说一声要去什么地方吗？</i>
{\fs11}Would I run off And never tell me where I'm going?{\r}

2410
02:32:04,110 --> 02:32:07,610
<i>为什么女人不能像我一样？</i>
{\fs11}Why can't a woman be like me?{\r}

2411
02:32:11,370 --> 02:32:12,990
你是说你为他们做了
{\fs11}Do you mean to say that after you'd done{\r}

2412
02:32:13,200 --> 02:32:15,700
这么了不起的事 没出一点错
{\fs11}this wonderful thing for them without making a single mistake,{\r}

2413
02:32:15,910 --> 02:32:17,870
而他们就坐在那里 一个词儿也没对你说吗？
{\fs11}they just sat there, never said a word to you?{\r}

2414
02:32:18,080 --> 02:32:21,670
既没有喜欢你 也没有赞美你 或是对你说你真的是太优秀了？
{\fs11}Never petted you, or admired you, or told you how splendid you'd been?{\r}

2415
02:32:21,880 --> 02:32:24,920
一个词儿都没有 他们只是坐在那里互相道贺
{\fs11}Not a word. They just sat there congratulating each other{\r}

2416
02:32:25,130 --> 02:32:26,380
他们取得了多么非凡的成就
{\fs11}on how marvelous they'd been.{\r}

2417
02:32:26,590 --> 02:32:30,180
他们有多高兴这一切都结束了 这应该得到怎样的奖励
{\fs11}How glad they were it was all over and what a bore it had all been.{\r}

2418
02:32:30,390 --> 02:32:31,590
真是令人惊讶
{\fs11}This is simply appalling.{\r}

2419
02:32:31,800 --> 02:32:33,560
是我的话我不会朝他扔拖鞋的
{\fs11}I should not have thrown my slippers at him,{\r}

2420
02:32:33,760 --> 02:32:35,600
我会朝他扔烙铁
{\fs11}I should've thrown the fire irons.{\r}

2421
02:32:35,810 --> 02:32:37,180
希金斯：- 噢 母亲你在吗？ - 是谁啊？
{\fs11}HIGGINS: Oh, is mother in? - What's that?{\r}

2422
02:32:37,390 --> 02:32:38,690
亨利
{\fs11}Henry.{\r}

2423
02:32:38,890 --> 02:32:41,440
我知道这不会很久
{\fs11}I knew it wouldn't be too long.{\r}

2424
02:32:41,650 --> 02:32:43,610
现在 你要记住
{\fs11}Now, remember,{\r}

2425
02:32:43,820 --> 02:32:45,900
你昨晚并不只是同王子跳了支舞
{\fs11}you not only danced with a prince last night,{\r}

2426
02:32:46,110 --> 02:32:48,950
是你表现得就像个公主
{\fs11}you behaved like a princess.{\r}

2427
02:32:54,990 --> 02:32:58,080
母亲 这事情真是太奇怪了 你也会...？
{\fs11}Mother, the most confounded thing. Do you...?{\r}

2428
02:33:01,250 --> 02:33:02,420
是你？
{\fs11}You?{\r}

2429
02:33:03,040 --> 02:33:05,920
下午好 希金斯教授 您还好吗？
{\fs11}Good afternoon, Professor Higgins. Are you quite well?{\r}

2430
02:33:07,130 --> 02:33:08,720
- 问我吗？ - 当然是问您
{\fs11}- Am I--? - Of course you are.{\r}

2431
02:33:08,920 --> 02:33:12,300
您从来都不得病的 您要来点儿茶吗？
{\fs11}You are never ill. Would you care for some tea?{\r}

2432
02:33:12,510 --> 02:33:15,470
你怎么敢跟我玩这种游戏 是我教你的
{\fs11}Don't you dare try that game on me. I taught it to you.{\r}

2433
02:33:15,680 --> 02:33:17,600
现在 起身跟我回去 别再犯傻了
{\fs11}Now, get up and come home and stop being a fool.{\r}

2434
02:33:17,810 --> 02:33:19,100
你给我惹的麻烦够多了
{\fs11}You've caused me enough trouble.{\r}

2435
02:33:19,310 --> 02:33:20,940
真是非常漂亮的出击 亨利 <font color=#FF7F00>[这老太太的台词太犀利了]</font>
{\fs11}Very nicely put indeed, Henry.{\r}

2436
02:33:21,150 --> 02:33:22,900
有哪个女人可以拒绝这样的邀请
{\fs11}No woman could resist such an invitation.{\r}

2437
02:33:23,110 --> 02:33:25,060
这个货物是怎么到这儿来的 居然还待为上宾？
{\fs11}How did this baggage get here in the first place?{\r}

2438
02:33:25,270 --> 02:33:27,900
伊莉莎今早来看我 我也很高兴她来
{\fs11}Eliza came to see me this morning and I was delighted to have her.{\r}

2439
02:33:28,110 --> 02:33:30,650
要是你再不规矩点儿 我就只有请你离开
{\fs11}And if you don't promise to behave, I must ask you to leave.{\r}

2440
02:33:30,860 --> 02:33:32,780
你是说我穿上自己的周日礼服
{\fs11}You mean to say I'm to put on my Sunday manners{\r}

2441
02:33:32,990 --> 02:33:35,620
就为了这个自己从科芬园的一匹烂菜叶
{\fs11}for this thing that I created out of the squashed cabbage leaves{\r}

2442
02:33:35,830 --> 02:33:36,870
打造出来的东西？
{\fs11}of Covent Garden?{\r}

2443
02:33:37,080 --> 02:33:38,200
我正是这个意思
{\fs11}That's precisely what I mean.{\r}

2444
02:33:38,410 --> 02:33:40,080
噢 那我要先请她滚出去
{\fs11}Well, I'II see her damned first.{\r}

2445
02:33:40,290 --> 02:33:43,210
你是怎么从我儿子那里学到这么好的礼仪呢？
{\fs11}However did you learn good manners with my son around?{\r}

2446
02:33:43,420 --> 02:33:45,250
说起来真的很难啊
{\fs11}lt was very difficult.{\r}

2447
02:33:45,460 --> 02:33:47,840
我可能永远都不知道淑女与绅士应有怎样的举止
{\fs11}I should never have known how ladies and gentlemen behave{\r}

2448
02:33:48,050 --> 02:33:50,760
要不是因为皮克林上校
{\fs11}if it hadn't been for Colonel Pickering.{\r}

2449
02:33:52,050 --> 02:33:54,180
他一直都让我感到他对我的感觉和思维
{\fs11}He always showed me that he felt and thought about me{\r}

2450
02:33:54,390 --> 02:33:57,760
都只不过比普通卖花女稍好一点儿罢了
{\fs11}as if I were something better than a common flower girl.{\r}

2451
02:34:00,350 --> 02:34:04,150
您也看见了 希金斯夫人 抛开装扮来看
{\fs11}You see, Mrs. Higgins, apart from the things one can pick up,{\r}

2452
02:34:04,360 --> 02:34:06,230
一位淑女同卖花女的区别
{\fs11}the difference between a lady and a flower girl{\r}

2453
02:34:06,440 --> 02:34:09,280
并不在于她的举止 而在于她受到怎样的对待
{\fs11}is not how she behaves, but how she is treated.{\r}

2454
02:34:12,700 --> 02:34:14,780
对希金斯教授来说我永远都是个卖花女
{\fs11}I shall always be a flower girl to Professor Higgins{\r}

2455
02:34:14,990 --> 02:34:17,950
因为他一直并将永远把我当卖花女一样对待
{\fs11}because he always treats me as a flower girl and always will.{\r}

2456
02:34:19,370 --> 02:34:22,040
可我知道 对皮克林上校来说我永远都是位淑女
{\fs11}But I know I shall always be a lady to Colonel Pickering{\r}

2457
02:34:22,250 --> 02:34:25,540
因为他一直并将永远把我当淑女一样对待
{\fs11}because he always treats me as a lady and always will.{\r}

2458
02:34:28,250 --> 02:34:29,590
[咆哮]
{\fs11}[GROWLS]{\r}

2459
02:34:29,920 --> 02:34:31,300
亨利 别在那里咬牙
{\fs11}Henry, don't grind your teeth.{\r}

2460
02:34:31,510 --> 02:34:34,130
主教大人来了 夫人 我先请他去花园吗？
{\fs11}The bishop is here, madam. Shall I show him into the garden?{\r}

2461
02:34:34,340 --> 02:34:36,760
主教大人还有这位教授？天呐 绝对不行
{\fs11}The bishop and the professor? Good heavens, no.{\r}

2462
02:34:36,970 --> 02:34:41,560
我会被开除教籍的 我在书房里见他
{\fs11}I should be excommunicated. I'II see him in the library.{\r}

2463
02:34:41,770 --> 02:34:44,390
伊莉莎 要是我儿子敢摔东西 <font color=#FF7F00>[英国人果然喜欢搞不平等条约 赫本可以砸…这就开始护着媳妇了]</font>
{\fs11}Eliza, if my son starts breaking up things,{\r}

2464
02:34:44,600 --> 02:34:47,150
我全权授予你 你可以把他赶出去
{\fs11}I give you full permission to have him evicted.{\r}

2465
02:34:47,360 --> 02:34:50,230
亨利 亲爱的 我建议你只谈两个话题：
{\fs11}Henry, dear, I suggest you stick to two subjects:{\r}

2466
02:34:50,440 --> 02:34:52,780
天气还有你的健康
{\fs11}The weather and your health.{\r}

2467
02:35:19,430 --> 02:35:21,680
噢 你已经讨回了一点了 就像你说的那样
{\fs11}Well, you've had a bit of your own back, as you call it.{\r}

2468
02:35:21,890 --> 02:35:24,020
要是你已经闹够了 你总该冷静下来
{\fs11}Have you had enough and are you going to be reasonable{\r}

2469
02:35:24,230 --> 02:35:25,270
或者你还想要什么？
{\fs11}or do you want any more?{\r}

2470
02:35:25,480 --> 02:35:27,270
你要我回去不过是替你捡拖鞋
{\fs11}You want me back only to pick up your slippers{\r}

2471
02:35:27,480 --> 02:35:30,060
继续忍受你对我发脾气 还要不断的伺候你
{\fs11}and put up with your tempers and fetch and carry for you.{\r}

2472
02:35:30,270 --> 02:35:32,400
- 我根本就没说我想要你回去 - 噢 是吗？
{\fs11}- I didn't say I wanted you back at all. - Oh, indeed?{\r}

2473
02:35:32,610 --> 02:35:35,360
- 那我们还谈什么？ - 嗯 谈关于你的事 而不是关于我的事
{\fs11}- Then what are we talking about? - Well, about you, not about me.{\r}

2474
02:35:35,570 --> 02:35:38,200
如果你回来 你得到的还会跟原来一样
{\fs11}lf you come back, you'II be treated as you've always been treated.{\r}

2475
02:35:38,410 --> 02:35:40,870
我不可能改变我的性格 我也不打算改变我的礼仪
{\fs11}I can't change my nature. I don't intend to change my manners.{\r}

2476
02:35:41,080 --> 02:35:43,290
我的礼仪同皮克林上校的是完全一样的
{\fs11}My manners are exactly the same as Colonel Pickering's.{\r}

2477
02:35:43,500 --> 02:35:44,540
不是那样的
{\fs11}That's not true.{\r}

2478
02:35:44,750 --> 02:35:47,120
他对一个卖花女就像对待一位公爵夫人
{\fs11}He treats a flower girl as if she were a duchess.{\r}

2479
02:35:47,330 --> 02:35:49,420
噢 我对待一位公爵夫人就像对待卖花女一样
{\fs11}Well, I treat a duchess as if she was a flower girl.{\r}

2480
02:35:49,630 --> 02:35:50,960
噢 我明白了 你对谁都是这样
{\fs11}Oh, I see. The same to everybody.{\r}

2481
02:35:51,170 --> 02:35:52,250
是那样
{\fs11}Just so.{\r}

2482
02:35:52,460 --> 02:35:55,170
要知道 最关键问题 伊莉莎 并不在于良好的礼仪
{\fs11}You see, the great secret, Eliza, is not a question of good manners{\r}

2483
02:35:55,380 --> 02:35:58,840
或是不好的礼仪 或是别的什么礼仪
{\fs11}or bad manners or any particular sort of manners,{\r}

2484
02:35:59,050 --> 02:36:04,140
而是对所有人都是同样的礼仪
{\fs11}but having the same manner for all human souls.{\r}

2485
02:36:04,350 --> 02:36:06,560
问题不在于我对你是否粗暴
{\fs11}The question is not whether I treat you rudely,{\r}

2486
02:36:06,770 --> 02:36:10,100
或是你是否听说我有对谁更好过
{\fs11}whether you've ever heard me treat anyone else better.{\r}

2487
02:36:10,310 --> 02:36:12,360
我才不在乎你怎么对待我
{\fs11}I don't care how you treat me.{\r}

2488
02:36:12,570 --> 02:36:13,980
我不在乎你骂我
{\fs11}I don't mind your swearing at me.{\r}

2489
02:36:14,190 --> 02:36:16,490
也不在乎你对我冷淡 我过去已经受够了
{\fs11}I shouldn't mind a black eye. I've had one before this.{\r}

2490
02:36:16,700 --> 02:36:18,570
可你不能这样抛弃我
{\fs11}But I won't be passed over.{\r}

2491
02:36:18,780 --> 02:36:20,990
噢 别缠着我 我是不会为你停下脚步的
{\fs11}Well, then get out of my way, for I won't stop for you.{\r}

2492
02:36:21,200 --> 02:36:22,990
你谈起我就好像我是辆公共汽车
{\fs11}You talk about me as though I was a motor bus.{\r}

2493
02:36:23,200 --> 02:36:24,240
你就是辆公共汽车
{\fs11}So you are a motor bus.{\r}

2494
02:36:24,450 --> 02:36:27,290
只知道摁着喇叭向前冲 根本不考虑搭任何人
{\fs11}AII bounce and go and no consideration for anybody.{\r}

2495
02:36:27,500 --> 02:36:30,250
就算我没有你我也能生活 你别以为我不行
{\fs11}But I can get along without you. Don't you think I can't.{\r}

2496
02:36:30,460 --> 02:36:33,250
我知道你行 我也说过你可以
{\fs11}I know you can. I told you you could.{\r}

2497
02:36:36,130 --> 02:36:41,010
我想 你从没想过 没有你我是否也能生活
{\fs11}You've never wondered, I suppose whether I could get along without you.{\r}

2498
02:36:42,390 --> 02:36:44,510
你这不是要缠着我吧
{\fs11}Don't you try to get around me.{\r}

2499
02:36:44,720 --> 02:36:45,850
是你自找的
{\fs11}You'II have to.{\r}

2500
02:36:46,600 --> 02:36:49,980
我当然可以 即便没有你或是这世上任何人
{\fs11}So I can, without you or any soul on earth.{\r}

2501
02:36:52,440 --> 02:36:54,150
我会想你的 伊莉莎
{\fs11}I shall miss you, Eliza.{\r}

2502
02:36:54,360 --> 02:36:57,070
我已经从你那愚蠢的观点中有所收获
{\fs11}I've learned something from your idiotic notions.{\r}

2503
02:36:57,280 --> 02:37:00,320
我得谦逊与感激的承认这一点
{\fs11}I confess that, humbly and gratefully.{\r}

2504
02:37:02,830 --> 02:37:05,120
噢 在你的留声机里有我的声音
{\fs11}Well, you have my voice on your gramophone.{\r}

2505
02:37:05,330 --> 02:37:07,660
当你没有我在身旁感到孤独的时候 你可以打开它
{\fs11}When you feel lonely without me, you can turn it on.{\r}

2506
02:37:07,870 --> 02:37:09,410
它没有感情可以让你伤害
{\fs11}lt has no feelings to hurt.{\r}

2507
02:37:11,330 --> 02:37:14,670
噢 但我不能打开你的灵魂
{\fs11}Well, I can't turn your soul on.{\r}

2508
02:37:16,840 --> 02:37:19,670
噢 你真是个魔鬼
{\fs11}Ooh. You are a devil.{\r}

2509
02:37:19,880 --> 02:37:22,340
你轻易伤害一个女孩儿的心
{\fs11}You can twist the heart in a girl just as easily{\r}

2510
02:37:22,550 --> 02:37:24,890
就像扭伤自己的手臂一样容易
{\fs11}as someone can twist her arms to hurt her.{\r}

2511
02:37:25,100 --> 02:37:26,850
我为什么要回去？
{\fs11}What am I to come back for?{\r}

2512
02:37:27,060 --> 02:37:29,230
因为你很有趣 这就是为什么我要带你回去
{\fs11}For the fun of it. That's why I took you on.{\r}

2513
02:37:29,440 --> 02:37:32,400
要是我没有满足你的要求 也许你明天就会把我丢出去
{\fs11}And you may throw me out tomorrow if I don't do everything you want me to.{\r}

2514
02:37:32,600 --> 02:37:35,650
好吧 要是我没有满足你的要求 你明天就可以走
{\fs11}Yes, and you may walk out tomorrow if I don't do everything you want me to.{\r}

2515
02:37:35,860 --> 02:37:36,900
去跟我父亲一起生活？
{\fs11}And live with my father?{\r}

2516
02:37:37,110 --> 02:37:39,400
是的 要么卖花儿 要么你愿意的话就嫁给皮克林？
{\fs11}Yes, or sell flowers. Or would you rather marry Pickering?{\r}

2517
02:37:39,610 --> 02:37:41,070
就算你求我 我也不会嫁给你
{\fs11}I wouldn't marry you if you asked me,{\r}

2518
02:37:41,280 --> 02:37:42,910
就算你比他年轻
{\fs11}and you're nearer my age than what he is.{\r}

2519
02:37:43,120 --> 02:37:44,820
- 比他年轻 - 我爱怎么说就怎么说
{\fs11}- Than he is. - I'II talk as I like.{\r}

2520
02:37:45,030 --> 02:37:46,580
你已经不是我的老师了
{\fs11}You're not my teacher now.{\r}

2521
02:37:46,790 --> 02:37:49,540
我才没那么想过 你不要乱想
{\fs11}That's not what I want, and you don't think it is.{\r}

2522
02:37:49,750 --> 02:37:51,790
愿意追我的绅士太多了
{\fs11}I've always had chaps enough wanting me that way.{\r}

2523
02:37:52,000 --> 02:37:54,080
弗雷迪 希尔一天每天都给我写两三封信
{\fs11}Freddy Hill writes me twice and three times a day.{\r}

2524
02:37:54,290 --> 02:37:55,750
一页接着一页
{\fs11}Sheets and sheets.{\r}

2525
02:37:55,960 --> 02:37:58,420
简单点儿说 你要我也像他那样对你迷得一塌糊涂
{\fs11}ln short, you want me to be as infatuated about you as he is.{\r}

2526
02:37:58,630 --> 02:38:00,550
- 是想那样吗？ - 不 我不想
{\fs11}- Is that it? - No, I don't.{\r}

2527
02:38:00,760 --> 02:38:04,140
我想从你那里得到的不是那样的感觉
{\fs11}That's not the sort of feeling I want from you.{\r}

2528
02:38:04,340 --> 02:38:06,510
我只想你对我亲柔一点
{\fs11}I want a little kindness.{\r}

2529
02:38:06,720 --> 02:38:09,850
我知道自己不过是个平凡无知的女孩儿 而你是位博学的绅士
{\fs11}I know I'm a common ignorant girl and you're a book-learned gentleman.{\r}

2530
02:38:10,060 --> 02:38:12,600
可我也不是你脚下的尘土
{\fs11}But I'm not dirt under your feet.{\r}

2531
02:38:12,810 --> 02:38:14,230
我所做的--
{\fs11}What I done--{\r}

2532
02:38:14,440 --> 02:38:17,980
我所做的 不是为了能坐出租车还有穿好衣服
{\fs11}What I did was not for the taxis and the dresses,{\r}

2533
02:38:18,190 --> 02:38:21,440
而是因为我们在一起是如此快乐 所以我开始--
{\fs11}but because we were pleasant together and I've come to--{\r}

2534
02:38:21,650 --> 02:38:25,030
开始喜欢你
{\fs11}Came to care for you.{\r}

2535
02:38:25,240 --> 02:38:26,620
不是为了要你向我表达爱意
{\fs11}Not to want you to make love to me{\r}

2536
02:38:26,830 --> 02:38:28,620
也不是忘记了我们之间的差距
{\fs11}and not forgetting the difference between us,{\r}

2537
02:38:28,830 --> 02:38:32,330
而是能更像朋友一些
{\fs11}but more friendly-like.{\r}

2538
02:38:33,960 --> 02:38:36,630
嗯 当然 我也这样想
{\fs11}Well, of course. That's how I feel.{\r}

2539
02:38:36,840 --> 02:38:39,500
皮克林也是
{\fs11}And how Pickering feels.{\r}

2540
02:38:39,710 --> 02:38:41,920
- 伊莉莎 你这个傻瓜 - 这不是我要的回答
{\fs11}- Eliza, you're a fool. - That's not the proper answer.{\r}

2541
02:38:42,130 --> 02:38:44,090
你别再犯傻了 这是唯一的答案
{\fs11}lt's the only answer till you stop being an idiot.{\r}

2542
02:38:44,300 --> 02:38:46,260
要是你是位女士 就不能有被忽视的感觉
{\fs11}lf you're a lady, give up feeling neglected{\r}

2543
02:38:46,470 --> 02:38:48,350
如果你所认识的那些男人不花上他们一半的时间
{\fs11}if the men you know don't spend half their time{\r}

2544
02:38:48,560 --> 02:38:51,020
为你落泪而另一半时间又对你冷淡
{\fs11}sniveling over you and the other half giving you black eyes.{\r}

2545
02:38:51,230 --> 02:38:53,640
你认为我冷酷 无情 自私 对吗？
{\fs11}You find me cold, unfeeling, selfish, don't you?{\r}

2546
02:38:53,850 --> 02:38:55,730
那就找你喜欢的那种人去吧
{\fs11}Be off with you to the sort of people you like.{\r}

2547
02:38:55,940 --> 02:38:57,730
嫁给一个有钱的 情感丰富的肥猪
{\fs11}Marry some sentimental hog with lots of money{\r}

2548
02:38:57,940 --> 02:39:00,980
用肥厚的嘴唇吻你 用厚重的靴子踢你
{\fs11}and a thick pair of lips to kiss you and a thick pair of boots to kick you.{\r}

2549
02:39:01,190 --> 02:39:04,200
既然你不感激你所拥有的一切 那就找你喜欢的去吧
{\fs11}lf you can't appreciate what you've got, get what you can appreciate.{\r}

2550
02:39:04,400 --> 02:39:05,570
噢 我不和你谈了
{\fs11}Oh, I can't talk to you.{\r}

2551
02:39:05,780 --> 02:39:09,030
我永远说不过你 永远都是我不对
{\fs11}You always turn everything against me. I'm always in the wrong.{\r}

2552
02:39:09,240 --> 02:39:11,370
但你别太过自信自己已经把我踩在脚下
{\fs11}But don't be too sure that you have me under your feet{\r}

2553
02:39:11,580 --> 02:39:13,250
任你践踏和说教
{\fs11}to be trampled on and talked down.{\r}

2554
02:39:13,460 --> 02:39:16,290
我会嫁给 弗雷迪 我会的 当我能够供养他的时候
{\fs11}I'II marry, Freddy, I will, soon as I'm able to support him.{\r}

2555
02:39:17,290 --> 02:39:18,750
弗雷迪？
{\fs11}Freddy?{\r}

2556
02:39:18,960 --> 02:39:21,170
那个可怜的家伙甚至连个跑腿的工作都找不到
{\fs11}That poor devil who couldn't get a job as an errand boy{\r}

2557
02:39:21,380 --> 02:39:23,090
就算这样他还有胆量要娶你？
{\fs11}even if he had the guts to try for it?{\r}

2558
02:39:23,300 --> 02:39:26,970
我说你这个女人 你还不明白吗？ 我把你变得足够嫁给国王
{\fs11}Woman, don't you understand? I've made you a consort for a king.{\r}

2559
02:39:27,180 --> 02:39:30,100
弗雷迪爱我 因为他爱我 所以足够做我的国王
{\fs11}Freddy loves me. That makes him king enough for me.{\r}

2560
02:39:30,310 --> 02:39:33,180
我不要他去工作 他跟我长大的环境是不一样的
{\fs11}I don't want him to work. He wasn't brought up to it as I was.{\r}

2561
02:39:33,390 --> 02:39:34,980
我可以做一名教师
{\fs11}I'II go and be a teacher.{\r}

2562
02:39:35,520 --> 02:39:37,060
天呐 你能教什么？
{\fs11}What will you teach, in heaven's name?{\r}

2563
02:39:37,560 --> 02:39:40,060
你教给我的东西 我会教语音学
{\fs11}What you taught me. I'II teach phonetics.{\r}

2564
02:39:41,110 --> 02:39:43,610
哈 哈 哈
{\fs11}Ha, ha, ha.{\r}

2565
02:39:44,190 --> 02:39:48,950
我可以自荐做那位了不起的匈牙利人的助手
{\fs11}I'II offer myself as an assistant to that brilliant Hungarian.{\r}

2566
02:39:49,660 --> 02:39:53,490
什么 那个冒牌货？那个骗子？那个只知谄媚的不学无术的家伙？
{\fs11}What, that impostor? That humbug? That toadying ignoramus?{\r}

2567
02:39:53,700 --> 02:39:55,710
把我的方法 我的发明都教给他？
{\fs11}Teach him my methods, my discoveries?{\r}

2568
02:39:55,910 --> 02:39:58,870
你要敢朝那个方向迈出一步 我就要拧断你的脖子
{\fs11}You take one step in that direction and I'II wring your neck.{\r}

2569
02:39:59,080 --> 02:40:03,420
拧啊 我还怕吗？我就知道你有一天会打死我的
{\fs11}Wring away. What do I care? I knew you'd strike me one day.{\r}

2570
02:40:06,010 --> 02:40:08,220
你不敢了吧 亨利 希金斯 对吧
{\fs11}That's done you, Henry Higgins, it has.{\r}

2571
02:40:08,430 --> 02:40:12,510
现在 我再也不会在意你的欺负还有你的大话了
{\fs11}Now, I don't care that for your bullying and your big talk.{\r}

2572
02:40:12,720 --> 02:40:16,390
<i>我曾经多么傻 多么容易被人操纵</i>
{\fs11}[SINGING] What a fool I was What a dominated fool{\r}

2573
02:40:16,600 --> 02:40:19,810
<i>竟以为你就是我的天与地</i>
{\fs11}To think you were the earth and sky{\r}

2574
02:40:20,020 --> 02:40:23,520
<i>我曾经多么傻 多么容易被人哄骗</i>
{\fs11}What a fool I was What an elevated fool{\r}

2575
02:40:23,730 --> 02:40:27,490
<i>我曾经就像一个长了羊脑袋的傻瓜</i>
{\fs11}What a mutton-headed dolt was I{\r}

2576
02:40:28,160 --> 02:40:31,820
<i>不 我爱斗嘴的朋友</i>
{\fs11}No, my reverberating friend{\r}

2577
02:40:32,030 --> 02:40:36,660
<i>你既不是开始 也不是结束</i>
{\fs11}You are not the beginning And the end{\r}

2578
02:40:38,960 --> 02:40:40,540
你这放肆的泼妇
{\fs11}You impudent hussy.{\r}

2579
02:40:40,750 --> 02:40:43,250
你脑子里没有一点儿思想 嘴里也没有一个词儿
{\fs11}There's not an idea in your head or a word in your mouth{\r}

2580
02:40:43,460 --> 02:40:44,960
这都是我给你的
{\fs11}that I haven't put there.{\r}

2581
02:40:46,630 --> 02:40:51,890
<i>春天依然会来 即便没有你</i>
{\fs11}There'II be spring every year Without you{\r}

2582
02:40:52,100 --> 02:40:55,720
<i>英格兰依然存在 即便没有你</i>
{\fs11}England still will be here Without you{\r}

2583
02:40:55,930 --> 02:40:59,520
<i>树上依然会结果 海滩也依然还在海边</i>
{\fs11}There'II be fruit on the tree And a shore by the sea{\r}

2584
02:40:59,730 --> 02:41:03,360
<i>依然会有煎饼和茶 即便没有你</i>
{\fs11}There'II be crumpets and tea Without you{\r}

2585
02:41:03,570 --> 02:41:07,190
<i>美术与音乐仍将繁盛 即便没有你</i>
{\fs11}Art and music will thrive Without you{\r}

2586
02:41:07,400 --> 02:41:10,950
<i>诗人依然会存在 即便没有你</i>
{\fs11}Somehow Keats will survive Without you{\r}

2587
02:41:11,160 --> 02:41:14,910
<i>还有雨依然会落在 西班牙的平原上</i>
{\fs11}And there still will be rain On that plain down in Spain{\r}

2588
02:41:15,120 --> 02:41:18,700
<i>既然他们都能依然存在 即便没有你</i>
{\fs11}Even that will remain Without you{\r}

2589
02:41:18,910 --> 02:41:22,630
<i>我也可以</i>
{\fs11}I can do{\r}

2590
02:41:22,830 --> 02:41:24,340
<i>即便没有你</i>
{\fs11}Without you{\r}

2591
02:41:25,300 --> 02:41:27,880
<i>噢 亲爱的朋友</i>
{\fs11}You, dear friend{\r}

2592
02:41:28,090 --> 02:41:31,970
<i>你说的太好了</i>
{\fs11}Who talk so well{\r}

2593
02:41:32,590 --> 02:41:39,430
<i>你可以去 哈特福德 赫里福德还有汉普郡</i> <font color=#FF7F00>[即离开伦敦]</font>
{\fs11}You can go to Hartford, Hereford and Hampshire{\r}

2594
02:41:39,640 --> 02:41:43,060
<i>他们依然可以统治这片土地 即便没有你</i>
{\fs11}They can still rule the land Without you{\r}

2595
02:41:43,270 --> 02:41:46,860
<i>温莎堡依然矗立 即便没有你</i>
{\fs11}Windsor Castle will stand Without you{\r}

2596
02:41:47,070 --> 02:41:48,780
<i>不必太过惊慌</i>
{\fs11}And without much ado{\r}

2597
02:41:48,990 --> 02:41:51,860
<i>我们也能应付过去 即便没有你</i>
{\fs11}We can all muddle through Without you{\r}

2598
02:41:52,860 --> 02:41:54,870
你这无耻的泼妇
{\fs11}You brazen hussy.{\r}

2599
02:41:55,370 --> 02:41:59,290
<i>用不着你推动 潮水依然会涨</i>
{\fs11}Without your pulling it The tide comes in{\r}

2600
02:41:59,500 --> 02:42:03,460
<i>用不着你拨动 地球依然会转</i>
{\fs11}Without your twirling it The Earth can spin{\r}

2601
02:42:03,670 --> 02:42:08,710
<i>用不着你牵动 云彩依然会飘</i>
{\fs11}Without your pushing them The clouds roll by{\r}

2602
02:42:08,920 --> 02:42:14,140
<i>既然没有你他们都可以 那太好了 我也可以</i>
{\fs11}lf they can do without you Ducky, so can I{\r}

2603
02:42:14,340 --> 02:42:17,850
<i>我不会感到孤独 即便没有你</i>
{\fs11}I shall not feel alone Without you{\r}

2604
02:42:18,060 --> 02:42:21,560
<i>我可以靠自己生活 即便没有你</i>
{\fs11}I can stand on my own Without you{\r}

2605
02:42:21,770 --> 02:42:25,860
<i>所以回到你的龟壳子里去吧 我可以做得相当好</i>
{\fs11}So go back in your shell I can do bloody well{\r}

2606
02:42:26,060 --> 02:42:28,900
<i>-即便没有-- 以圣乔治之名起誓 我真的办到了</i>
{\fs11}- Without-- [SINGING] By George, I really did it{\r}

2607
02:42:29,110 --> 02:42:30,150
<i>我办到了 我办到了</i>
{\fs11}I did it, I did it{\r}

2608
02:42:30,360 --> 02:42:32,780
<i>我说过我要创造一个女人 我确实办到了</i>
{\fs11}I said I'd make a woman And indeed I did{\r}

2609
02:42:32,990 --> 02:42:35,610
<i>我知道我可以办到 我就知道 我就知道</i>
{\fs11}I knew that I could do it I knew it, I knew it{\r}

2610
02:42:35,820 --> 02:42:38,530
<i>我说过我要创造一个女人 我成功了</i>
{\fs11}I said I'd make a woman And succeed I did{\r}

2611
02:42:38,740 --> 02:42:40,700
伊莉莎 你真是太美了
{\fs11}Eliza, you're magnificent.{\r}

2612
02:42:40,910 --> 02:42:43,330
5分钟前 你还像绕在我脖子上的一块石头
{\fs11}Five minutes ago, you were a millstone around my neck{\r}

2613
02:42:43,540 --> 02:42:45,420
可现在你却像矗立的高塔
{\fs11}and now you're a tower of strength.{\r}

2614
02:42:45,630 --> 02:42:48,420
一艘全副武装的战舰
{\fs11}A consort battleship.{\r}

2615
02:42:48,630 --> 02:42:50,460
我喜欢你这样
{\fs11}I like you this way.{\r}

2616
02:42:52,470 --> 02:42:54,340
再见 希金斯教授
{\fs11}Goodbye, Professor Higgins.{\r}

2617
02:42:54,550 --> 02:42:57,220
你再也不会见到我了
{\fs11}You shall not be seeing me again.{\r}

2618
02:43:09,940 --> 02:43:13,530
母亲！
{\fs11}Mother!{\r}

2619
02:43:14,320 --> 02:43:16,410
怎么了 亨利？出什么事了？
{\fs11}What is it, Henry? What's happened?{\r}

2620
02:43:18,160 --> 02:43:19,240
她走了
{\fs11}She's gone.{\r}

2621
02:43:19,450 --> 02:43:21,790
噢 当然了 亲爱的 你以为会怎样？
{\fs11}Well, of course, dear. What did you expect?{\r}

2622
02:43:23,250 --> 02:43:24,710
噢...
{\fs11}Well...{\r}

2623
02:43:25,790 --> 02:43:28,250
- 我该怎么办？ - 将就过吧 我想
{\fs11}- What am I to do? - Do without, I suppose.{\r}

2624
02:43:30,340 --> 02:43:33,340
我会的
{\fs11}And so I shall.{\r}

2625
02:43:35,380 --> 02:43:38,390
如果希金斯的氧气会让她那狭小的肺燃烧
{\fs11}lf the Higgins' oxygen burns up her little lungs,{\r}

2626
02:43:38,600 --> 02:43:41,760
那就让她去找那些适合她的惰性气体
{\fs11}let her seek some stuffiness that suits her.{\r}

2627
02:43:41,970 --> 02:43:45,890
她就像只猫头鹰让我原本充满阳光的生活变得阴森 <font color=#FF7F00>[呵呵 每天扯着嗓子练到那么晚]</font>
{\fs11}She's an owl sickened by a few days of my sunshine.{\r}

2628
02:43:46,100 --> 02:43:47,900
那好吧 就随她去吧 没有她我可以的
{\fs11}Very well, let her go. I can do without her.{\r}

2629
02:43:48,100 --> 02:43:50,310
没有任何人我都可以 我还有自己的灵魂
{\fs11}I can do without anyone. I have my own soul.{\r}

2630
02:43:50,520 --> 02:43:54,570
我自己神圣的火焰迸发出的火花
{\fs11}My own spark of divine fire.{\r}

2631
02:43:57,530 --> 02:43:59,820
太精彩了 伊莉莎
{\fs11}Bravo, Eliza.{\r}

2632
02:44:19,390 --> 02:44:22,720
<i>该死 该死 该死 该死</i>
{\fs11}[SINGING] Damn, damn, damn, damn{\r}

2633
02:44:24,890 --> 02:44:26,930
<i>我已经看惯了她的脸庞</i>
{\fs11}I've grown accustomed to her face{\r}

2634
02:44:30,810 --> 02:44:32,900
<i>仿佛是她让新一天开始</i>
{\fs11}She almost makes the day begin{\r}

2635
02:44:34,030 --> 02:44:37,240
<i>我已经听惯了她的音调 那些她日夜练习的音调</i>
{\fs11}I've grown accustomed to the tune That she whistles night and noon{\r}

2636
02:44:37,450 --> 02:44:41,120
<i>她的一颦 一笑 她的快乐与忧伤</i>
{\fs11}Her smiles, her frowns Her ups, her downs{\r}

2637
02:44:41,320 --> 02:44:43,240
<i>如今已渗入我的习惯</i>
{\fs11}Are second nature to me now{\r}

2638
02:44:44,490 --> 02:44:46,700
<i>就像呼吸一样</i>
{\fs11}Like breathing out and breathing in{\r}

2639
02:44:47,830 --> 02:44:51,630
<i>我曾过着平静的独身生活 这样的生活在我们见面之前我很满足</i>
{\fs11}I was serenely independent And content before we met{\r}

2640
02:44:51,840 --> 02:44:55,050
<i>当然我还是可以 重回那样的生活</i>
{\fs11}Surely I could always Be that way again{\r}

2641
02:44:56,800 --> 02:45:00,800
<i>可现在我已经习惯了 她的模样</i>
{\fs11}And yet I've grown accustomed To her look{\r}

2642
02:45:01,390 --> 02:45:03,220
<i>听惯了她的声音</i>
{\fs11}Accustomed to her voice{\r}

2643
02:45:03,890 --> 02:45:08,310
<i>看惯了她的脸庞</i>
{\fs11}Accustomed to her face{\r}

2644
02:45:22,490 --> 02:45:25,450
嫁给弗雷迪 多么幼稚的想法
{\fs11}Marry Freddy. What an infantile idea.{\r}

2645
02:45:25,660 --> 02:45:28,870
这是多么无情 可恶 不明智的做法
{\fs11}What a heartless, wicked, brainless thing to do.{\r}

2646
02:45:29,080 --> 02:45:32,290
她会后悔的 她一定会后悔的
{\fs11}But she'II regret it. She'II regret it.{\r}

2647
02:45:32,500 --> 02:45:36,300
甚至他们还没念结婚誓词前 就已经结束了
{\fs11}lt's doomed before they even take the vow.{\r}

2648
02:45:36,800 --> 02:45:40,470
<i>我现在就能看到她 弗雷迪 埃恩斯福德-希尔夫人</i>
{\fs11}[SINGING] I can see her now Mrs. Freddy Eynsford-Hill{\r}

2649
02:45:40,680 --> 02:45:43,220
<i>住在一个可怜的小公寓里 就在一家商店楼上</i>
{\fs11}ln a wretched little flat Above a store{\r}

2650
02:45:43,800 --> 02:45:46,560
<i>我现在就能看到她 放钱的抽屉里一个便士也没有</i>
{\fs11}I can see her now Not a penny in the till{\r}

2651
02:45:46,770 --> 02:45:49,270
<i>一位收债人 正在敲门</i>
{\fs11}And a bill collector Beating at the door{\r}

2652
02:45:49,890 --> 02:45:52,270
<i>她试过教授那些 我教给她的东西</i>
{\fs11}She'II try to teach the things I taught her{\r}

2653
02:45:52,770 --> 02:45:55,110
<i>可最后还是只能去卖花儿</i>
{\fs11}And end up selling flowers instead{\r}

2654
02:45:55,770 --> 02:45:58,070
<i>为了面包和水而乞讨</i>
{\fs11}Begging for her bread and water{\r}

2655
02:45:58,280 --> 02:46:01,610
<i>而她的丈夫 却在床上吃早餐</i>
{\fs11}While her husband Has his breakfast in bed{\r}

2656
02:46:04,620 --> 02:46:08,870
<i>要不了一年 当她的头发变得花白</i>
{\fs11}In a year or so When she's prematurely grey{\r}

2657
02:46:09,080 --> 02:46:12,620
<i>脸颊上的红晕 也变得惨白</i>
