2658
02:46:12,830 --> 02:46:14,380
<i>当她回到家 却</i>
{\fs11}She'II come home, and lo{\r}

2659
02:46:14,580 --> 02:46:16,040
<i>发现他早已起床</i>
{\fs11}He'II have upped and run away{\r}

2660
02:46:16,250 --> 02:46:19,000
<i>跟一个纽约来的 暴发户的女儿逃得无影无踪</i>
{\fs11}With a social-climbing heiress From New York{\r}

2661
02:46:19,210 --> 02:46:20,510
<i>可怜的伊莉莎</i>
{\fs11}Poor Eliza{\r}

2662
02:46:20,720 --> 02:46:22,220
<i>多么可怕</i>
{\fs11}How simply frightful{\r}

2663
02:46:22,430 --> 02:46:24,470
<i>多么丢人</i>
{\fs11}How humiliating{\r}

2664
02:46:24,680 --> 02:46:26,430
<i>多么解气</i>
{\fs11}How delightful{\r}

2665
02:46:28,970 --> 02:46:31,810
<i>那将是多么辛辣的讽刺 在那个必然的夜晚</i>
{\fs11}How poignant it'II be On that inevitable night{\r}

2666
02:46:32,020 --> 02:46:34,850
<i>当她敲打着我的房门 用破布擦着眼泪</i>
{\fs11}When she hammers on my door ln tears and rags{\r}

2667
02:46:35,270 --> 02:46:38,520
<i>悲惨又孤独 后悔并向我认错的时候</i>
{\fs11}Miserable and lonely Repentant and contrite{\r}

2668
02:46:39,150 --> 02:46:41,650
<i>我该让她进来 还是把她丢给那些色狼？</i>
{\fs11}Will I take her in Or hurl her to the wolves?{\r}

2669
02:46:41,860 --> 02:46:44,860
<i>是温柔待她 还是给她应有的惩罚？</i>
{\fs11}Give her kindness Or the treatment she deserves?{\r}

2670
02:46:45,070 --> 02:46:48,660
<i>我该让她回来 还是把这个货物扔出去？</i>
{\fs11}Will I take her back Or throw the baggage out?{\r}

2671
02:46:51,330 --> 02:46:53,540
<i>噢 我真是个最宽容的人</i>
{\fs11}Well, I'm a most forgiving man{\r}

2672
02:46:54,040 --> 02:46:56,880
<i>那种永远不能 也不愿</i>
{\fs11}The sort who never could Ever would{\r}

2673
02:46:57,090 --> 02:47:00,840
<i>认准了立场 就坚定不移</i>
{\fs11}Take a position And staunchly never budge{\r}

2674
02:47:03,680 --> 02:47:05,800
<i>一个最宽容的人</i>
{\fs11}A most forgiving man{\r}

2675
02:47:08,720 --> 02:47:11,100
<i>不过我再也不会让她回来</i>
{\fs11}But I shall never take her back{\r}

2676
02:47:11,980 --> 02:47:13,890
<i>就算她爬着求我</i>
{\fs11}lf she were crawling on her knees{\r}

2677
02:47:14,730 --> 02:47:17,310
<i>任她答应赎罪 任她颤抖 任她呻吟</i>
{\fs11}Let her promise to atone Let her shiver, let her moan{\r}

2678
02:47:17,520 --> 02:47:21,610
<i>我也会关上门 任这个泼妇被冻死</i>
{\fs11}I'II slam the door And let the hellcat freeze{\r}

2679
02:47:24,280 --> 02:47:27,780
嫁给弗雷迪 哈！
{\fs11}Marry Freddy. Ha!{\r}

2680
02:47:40,800 --> 02:47:46,130
<i>可我已经如此听惯了她 每天对我说早上好</i>
{\fs11}But I'm so used to hear her say Good morning every day{\r}

2681
02:47:46,340 --> 02:47:51,560
<i>她的一颦 一笑 她的快乐与忧伤</i>
{\fs11}Her joys, her woes Her highs, her lows{\r}

2682
02:47:51,770 --> 02:47:54,220
<i>如今已渗入我的习惯</i>
{\fs11}Are second nature to me now{\r}

2683
02:47:55,730 --> 02:47:58,230
<i>就像呼吸一样</i>
{\fs11}Like breathing out and breathing in{\r}

2684
02:47:59,860 --> 02:48:01,770
<i>我很庆幸她是个女人</i>
{\fs11}I'm very grateful she's a woman{\r}

2685
02:48:01,980 --> 02:48:03,780
<i>太容易忘记了</i>
{\fs11}And so easy to forget{\r}

2686
02:48:04,440 --> 02:48:08,280
<i>就像是个坏习惯 总能改掉</i>
{\fs11}Rather like a habit One can always break{\r}

2687
02:48:10,370 --> 02:48:15,500
<i>可我已经习惯 嗅到</i>
{\fs11}And yet I've grown Accustomed to the trace{\r}

2688
02:48:15,710 --> 02:48:18,620
<i>空气中的某种味道</i>
{\fs11}Of something in the air{\r}

2689
02:48:19,630 --> 02:48:24,920
<i>看惯了她的脸庞</i>
{\fs11}Accustomed to her face{\r}

2690
02:50:02,100 --> 02:50:03,770
<i>噢 我们都是有自尊心的</i>
{\fs11}ELIZA [ON RECORDING]: Oh, we are proud.{\r}

2691
02:50:03,980 --> 02:50:07,110
<i>噢 他不打算给教我了 他反悔了 他之前说要教我的</i>
{\fs11}He ain't above giving lessons, not him. I heard him say so.{\r}

2692
02:50:07,320 --> 02:50:09,320
<i>好吧 我可不是来这儿 听你们说这些客气话的</i>
{\fs11}Well, I ain't come here to ask for any compliment,{\r}

2693
02:50:09,530 --> 02:50:12,450
<i>要不是因为我的钱不够的话 我也不会来这儿</i>
{\fs11}and if my money's not good enough, I can go elsewhere.{\r}

2694
02:50:12,660 --> 02:50:13,860
希金斯：<i>不够什么？</i>
{\fs11}HIGGINS: Good enough for what?{\r}

2695
02:50:14,070 --> 02:50:15,530
伊莉莎：<i>付你的还是够了</i>
{\fs11}ELIZA: Good enough for you.{\r}

2696
02:50:15,740 --> 02:50:16,870
<i>现在 你明白了吗？</i>
{\fs11}Now you know, don't you?{\r}

2697
02:50:17,080 --> 02:50:19,370
<i>我是来学习的 听清楚了 我还会付学费</i>
{\fs11}I'm come to have lessons, I am, and to pay for them too,{\r}

2698
02:50:19,580 --> 02:50:20,620
<i>别搞错了</i>
{\fs11}make no mistake.{\r}

2699
02:50:20,830 --> 02:50:22,120
<i>你为什么要这样做呢 小姑娘？</i>
{\fs11}PICKERING: What is it you want, my girl?{\r}

2700
02:50:22,330 --> 02:50:25,130
伊莉莎：<i>我希望自己能像一位女士一样在花店里工作</i>
{\fs11}ELIZA: I want to be a lady in a flower shop{\r}

2701
02:50:25,340 --> 02:50:28,300
<i>而不是在托特纳姆考特路的街角卖花</i>
{\fs11}instead of selling at the corner of Tottenham Court Road.{\r}

2702
02:50:28,500 --> 02:50:31,470
<i>但除非我说话能更有教养些 否则他们是不会要我的</i>
{\fs11}But they won't take me unless I can talk more genteel.{\r}

2703
02:50:31,670 --> 02:50:33,510
<i>他说过他会教我</i>
{\fs11}He said he could teach me.{\r}

2704
02:50:33,720 --> 02:50:34,760
<i>所以 我就来了</i>
{\fs11}Well, here I am.{\r}

2705
02:50:34,970 --> 02:50:36,930
<i>我准备付钱给他 也不要他白教我</i>
{\fs11}Ready to pay, not asking any favor.{\r}

2706
02:50:37,140 --> 02:50:39,140
<i>可他却当我是垃圾一样的对待我</i>
{\fs11}And he treats me as if I was dirt.{\r}

2707
02:50:39,350 --> 02:50:43,640
<i>我知道你上课收多少钱 我愿意掏钱</i>
{\fs11}I know what lessons cost as well as you do, and I'm ready to pay.{\r}

2708
02:50:43,850 --> 02:50:46,900
<i>我最多出1个先令 随便你要不要</i>
{\fs11}I won't give more than a schilling. Take it or leave it.{\r}

2709
02:50:47,110 --> 02:50:51,440
希金斯：<i>这赌注很难拒绝 她的品味如此低俗</i>
{\fs11}HIGGINS: lt's almost irresistible. She's so deliciously low.{\r}

2710
02:50:52,070 --> 02:50:53,780
<i>如此肮脏可怖</i>
{\fs11}So horribly dirty.{\r}

2711
02:50:53,990 --> 02:50:55,160
<i>我愿意同您打这个赌</i>
{\fs11}I'II take it.{\r}

2712
02:50:55,370 --> 02:50:58,780
